52 namespace clang {

55 /// A semantic tree transformation that allows one to transform one
56 /// abstract syntax tree into another.
57 ///
58 /// A new tree transformation is defined by creating a new subclass \c X of
59 /// \c TreeTransform<X> and then overriding certain operations to provide
60 /// behavior specific to that transformation. For example, template
61 /// instantiation is implemented as a tree transformation where the
62 /// transformation of TemplateTypeParmType nodes involves substituting the
63 /// template arguments for their corresponding template parameters; a similar
64 /// transformation is performed for non-type template parameters and
65 /// template template parameters.
66 ///
67 /// This tree-transformation template uses static polymorphism to allow
68 /// subclasses to customize any of its operations. Thus, a subclass can
69 /// override any of the transformation or rebuild operators by providing an
70 /// operation with the same signature as the default implementation. The
71 /// overriding function should not be virtual.
72 ///
73 /// Semantic tree transformations are split into two stages, either of which
74 /// can be replaced by a subclass. The "transform" step transforms an AST node
75 /// or the parts of an AST node using the various transformation functions,
76 /// then passes the pieces on to the "rebuild" step, which constructs a new AST
77 /// node of the appropriate kind from the pieces. The default transformation
78 /// routines recursively transform the operands to composite AST nodes (e.g.,
79 /// the pointee type of a PointerType node) and, if any of those operand nodes
80 /// were changed by the transformation, invokes the rebuild operation to create
81 /// a new AST node.
82 ///
83 /// Subclasses can customize the transformation at various levels. The
84 /// most coarse-grained transformations involve replacing TransformType(),
85 /// TransformExpr(), TransformDecl(), TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
86 /// TransformTemplateName(), or TransformTemplateArgument() with entirely
87 /// new implementations.
88 ///
89 /// For more fine-grained transformations, subclasses can replace any of the
90 /// \c TransformXXX functions (where XXX is the name of an AST node, e.g.,
91 /// PointerType, StmtExpr) to alter the transformation. As mentioned previously,
92 /// replacing TransformTemplateTypeParmType() allows template instantiation
93 /// to substitute template arguments for their corresponding template
94 /// parameters. Additionally, subclasses can override the \c RebuildXXX
95 /// functions to control how AST nodes are rebuilt when their operands change.
96 /// By default, \c TreeTransform will invoke semantic analysis to rebuild
97 /// AST nodes. However, certain other tree transformations (e.g, cloning) may
98 /// be able to use more efficient rebuild steps.
99 ///
100 /// There are a handful of other functions that can be overridden, allowing one
101 /// to avoid traversing nodes that don't need any transformation
102 /// (\c AlreadyTransformed()), force rebuilding AST nodes even when their
103 /// operands have not changed (\c AlwaysRebuild()), and customize the
104 /// default locations and entity names used for type-checking
105 /// (\c getBaseLocation(), \c getBaseEntity()).
106 template<typename Derived>
107 class TreeTransform {
108  /// Private RAII object that helps us forget and then re-remember
109  /// the template argument corresponding to a partially-substituted parameter
110  /// pack.
111  class ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII {
112  Derived &Self;
113  TemplateArgument Old;
114 
115  public:
116  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII(Derived &Self) : Self(Self) {
117  Old = Self.ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPack();
118  }
119 
120  ~ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII() {
121  Self.RememberPartiallySubstitutedPack(Old);
122  }
123  };
124 
125 protected:
126  Sema &SemaRef;
127 
128  /// The set of local declarations that have been transformed, for
129  /// cases where we are forced to build new declarations within the transformer
130  /// rather than in the subclass (e.g., lambda closure types).
131  llvm::DenseMap<Decl *, Decl *> TransformedLocalDecls;
132 
133 public:
134  /// Initializes a new tree transformer.
135  TreeTransform(Sema &SemaRef) : SemaRef(SemaRef) { }
136 
137  /// Retrieves a reference to the derived class.
138  Derived &getDerived() { return static_cast<Derived&>(*this); }
139 
140  /// Retrieves a reference to the derived class.
141  const Derived &getDerived() const {
142  return static_cast<const Derived&>(*this);
143  }
144 
145  static inline ExprResult Owned(Expr *E) { return E; }
146  static inline StmtResult Owned(Stmt *S) { return S; }
147 
148  /// Retrieves a reference to the semantic analysis object used for
149  /// this tree transform.
150  Sema &getSema() const { return SemaRef; }
151 
152  /// Whether the transformation should always rebuild AST nodes, even
153  /// if none of the children have changed.
154  ///
155  /// Subclasses may override this function to specify when the transformation
156  /// should rebuild all AST nodes.
157  ///
158  /// We must always rebuild all AST nodes when performing variadic template
159  /// pack expansion, in order to avoid violating the AST invariant that each
160  /// statement node appears at most once in its containing declaration.
161  bool AlwaysRebuild() { return SemaRef.ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndex != -1; }
162 
163  /// Whether the transformation is forming an expression or statement that
164  /// replaces the original. In this case, we'll reuse mangling numbers from
165  /// existing lambdas.
166  bool ReplacingOriginal() { return false; }
167 
168  /// Wether CXXConstructExpr can be skipped when they are implicit.
169  /// They will be reconstructed when used if needed.
170  /// This is useful when the user that cause rebuilding of the
171  /// CXXConstructExpr is outside of the expression at which the TreeTransform
172  /// started.
173  bool AllowSkippingCXXConstructExpr() { return true; }
174 
175  /// Returns the location of the entity being transformed, if that
176  /// information was not available elsewhere in the AST.
177  ///
178  /// By default, returns no source-location information. Subclasses can
179  /// provide an alternative implementation that provides better location
180  /// information.
181  SourceLocation getBaseLocation() { return SourceLocation(); }
182 
183  /// Returns the name of the entity being transformed, if that
184  /// information was not available elsewhere in the AST.
185  ///
186  /// By default, returns an empty name. Subclasses can provide an alternative
187  /// implementation with a more precise name.
188  DeclarationName getBaseEntity() { return DeclarationName(); }
189 
190  /// Sets the "base" location and entity when that
191  /// information is known based on another transformation.
192  ///
193  /// By default, the source location and entity are ignored. Subclasses can
194  /// override this function to provide a customized implementation.
195  void setBase(SourceLocation Loc, DeclarationName Entity) { }
196 
197  /// RAII object that temporarily sets the base location and entity
198  /// used for reporting diagnostics in types.
199  class TemporaryBase {
200  TreeTransform &Self;
201  SourceLocation OldLocation;
202  DeclarationName OldEntity;
203 
204  public:
205  TemporaryBase(TreeTransform &Self, SourceLocation Location,
206  DeclarationName Entity) : Self(Self) {
207  OldLocation = Self.getDerived().getBaseLocation();
208  OldEntity = Self.getDerived().getBaseEntity();
209 
210  if (Location.isValid())
211  Self.getDerived().setBase(Location, Entity);
212  }
213 
214  ~TemporaryBase() {
215  Self.getDerived().setBase(OldLocation, OldEntity);
216  }
217  };
218 
219  /// Determine whether the given type \p T has already been
220  /// transformed.
221  ///
222  /// Subclasses can provide an alternative implementation of this routine
223  /// to short-circuit evaluation when it is known that a given type will
224  /// not change. For example, template instantiation need not traverse
225  /// non-dependent types.
226  bool AlreadyTransformed(QualType T) {
227  return T.isNull();
228  }
229 
230  /// Transform a template parameter depth level.
231  ///
232  /// During a transformation that transforms template parameters, this maps
233  /// an old template parameter depth to a new depth.
234  unsigned TransformTemplateDepth(unsigned Depth) {
235  return Depth;
236  }
237 
238  /// Determine whether the given call argument should be dropped, e.g.,
239  /// because it is a default argument.
240  ///
241  /// Subclasses can provide an alternative implementation of this routine to
242  /// determine which kinds of call arguments get dropped. By default,
243  /// CXXDefaultArgument nodes are dropped (prior to transformation).
244  bool DropCallArgument(Expr *E) {
245  return E->isDefaultArgument();
246  }
247 
248  /// Determine whether we should expand a pack expansion with the
249  /// given set of parameter packs into separate arguments by repeatedly
250  /// transforming the pattern.
251  ///
252  /// By default, the transformer never tries to expand pack expansions.
253  /// Subclasses can override this routine to provide different behavior.
254  ///
255  /// \param EllipsisLoc The location of the ellipsis that identifies the
256  /// pack expansion.
257  ///
258  /// \param PatternRange The source range that covers the entire pattern of
259  /// the pack expansion.
260  ///
261  /// \param Unexpanded The set of unexpanded parameter packs within the
262  /// pattern.
263  ///
264  /// \param ShouldExpand Will be set to \c true if the transformer should
265  /// expand the corresponding pack expansions into separate arguments. When
266  /// set, \c NumExpansions must also be set.
267  ///
268  /// \param RetainExpansion Whether the caller should add an unexpanded
269  /// pack expansion after all of the expanded arguments. This is used
270  /// when extending explicitly-specified template argument packs per
271  /// C++0x [temp.arg.explicit]p9.
272  ///
273  /// \param NumExpansions The number of separate arguments that will be in
274  /// the expanded form of the corresponding pack expansion. This is both an
275  /// input and an output parameter, which can be set by the caller if the
276  /// number of expansions is known a priori (e.g., due to a prior substitution)
277  /// and will be set by the callee when the number of expansions is known.
278  /// The callee must set this value when \c ShouldExpand is \c true; it may
279  /// set this value in other cases.
280  ///
281  /// \returns true if an error occurred (e.g., because the parameter packs
282  /// are to be instantiated with arguments of different lengths), false
283  /// otherwise. If false, \c ShouldExpand (and possibly \c NumExpansions)
284  /// must be set.
285  bool TryExpandParameterPacks(SourceLocation EllipsisLoc,
286  SourceRange PatternRange,
287  ArrayRef<UnexpandedParameterPack> Unexpanded,
288  bool &ShouldExpand, bool &RetainExpansion,
289  std::optional<unsigned> &NumExpansions) {
290  ShouldExpand = false;
291  return false;
292  }
293 
294  /// "Forget" about the partially-substituted pack template argument,
295  /// when performing an instantiation that must preserve the parameter pack
296  /// use.
297  ///
298  /// This routine is meant to be overridden by the template instantiator.
299  TemplateArgument ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPack() {
300  return TemplateArgument();
301  }
302 
303  /// "Remember" the partially-substituted pack template argument
304  /// after performing an instantiation that must preserve the parameter pack
305  /// use.
306  ///
307  /// This routine is meant to be overridden by the template instantiator.
308  void RememberPartiallySubstitutedPack(TemplateArgument Arg) { }
309 
310  /// Note to the derived class when a function parameter pack is
311  /// being expanded.
312  void ExpandingFunctionParameterPack(ParmVarDecl *Pack) { }
313 
314  /// Transforms the given type into another type.
315  ///
316  /// By default, this routine transforms a type by creating a
317  /// TypeSourceInfo for it and delegating to the appropriate
318  /// function. This is expensive, but we don't mind, because
319  /// this method is deprecated anyway; all users should be
320  /// switched to storing TypeSourceInfos.
321  ///
322  /// \returns the transformed type.
323  QualType TransformType(QualType T);
324 
325  /// Transforms the given type-with-location into a new
326  /// type-with-location.
327  ///
328  /// By default, this routine transforms a type by delegating to the
329  /// appropriate TransformXXXType to build a new type. Subclasses
330  /// may override this function (to take over all type
331  /// transformations) or some set of the TransformXXXType functions
332  /// to alter the transformation.
333  TypeSourceInfo *TransformType(TypeSourceInfo *DI);
334 
335  /// Transform the given type-with-location into a new
336  /// type, collecting location information in the given builder
337  /// as necessary.
338  ///
339  QualType TransformType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB, TypeLoc TL);
340 
341  /// Transform a type that is permitted to produce a
342  /// DeducedTemplateSpecializationType.
343  ///
344  /// This is used in the (relatively rare) contexts where it is acceptable
345  /// for transformation to produce a class template type with deduced
346  /// template arguments.
347  /// @{
348  QualType TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(QualType T);
349  TypeSourceInfo *TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(TypeSourceInfo *DI);
350  /// @}
351 
352  /// The reason why the value of a statement is not discarded, if any.
353  enum StmtDiscardKind {
354  SDK_Discarded,
355  SDK_NotDiscarded,
356  SDK_StmtExprResult,
357  };
358 
359  /// Transform the given statement.
360  ///
361  /// By default, this routine transforms a statement by delegating to the
362  /// appropriate TransformXXXStmt function to transform a specific kind of
363  /// statement or the TransformExpr() function to transform an expression.
364  /// Subclasses may override this function to transform statements using some
365  /// other mechanism.
366  ///
367  /// \returns the transformed statement.
368  StmtResult TransformStmt(Stmt *S, StmtDiscardKind SDK = SDK_Discarded);
369 
370  /// Transform the given statement.
371  ///
372  /// By default, this routine transforms a statement by delegating to the
373  /// appropriate TransformOMPXXXClause function to transform a specific kind
374  /// of clause. Subclasses may override this function to transform statements
375  /// using some other mechanism.
376  ///
377  /// \returns the transformed OpenMP clause.
378  OMPClause *TransformOMPClause(OMPClause *S);
379 
380  /// Transform the given attribute.
381  ///
382  /// By default, this routine transforms a statement by delegating to the
383  /// appropriate TransformXXXAttr function to transform a specific kind
384  /// of attribute. Subclasses may override this function to transform
385  /// attributed statements/types using some other mechanism.
386  ///
387  /// \returns the transformed attribute
388  const Attr *TransformAttr(const Attr *S);
389 
390  // Transform the given statement attribute.
391  //
392  // Delegates to the appropriate TransformXXXAttr function to transform a
393  // specific kind of statement attribute. Unlike the non-statement taking
394  // version of this, this implements all attributes, not just pragmas.
395  const Attr *TransformStmtAttr(const Stmt *OrigS, const Stmt *InstS,
396  const Attr *A);
397 
398  // Transform the specified attribute.
399  //
400  // Subclasses should override the transformation of attributes with a pragma
401  // spelling to transform expressions stored within the attribute.
402  //
403  // \returns the transformed attribute.
404 #define ATTR(X) \
405  const X##Attr *Transform##X##Attr(const X##Attr *R) { return R; }
406 #include "clang/Basic/AttrList.inc"
407 
408  // Transform the specified attribute.
409  //
410  // Subclasses should override the transformation of attributes to do
411  // transformation and checking of statement attributes. By default, this
412  // delegates to the non-statement taking version.
413  //
414  // \returns the transformed attribute.
415 #define ATTR(X) \
416  const X##Attr *TransformStmt##X##Attr(const Stmt *, const Stmt *, \
417  const X##Attr *A) { \
418  return getDerived().Transform##X##Attr(A); \
419  }
420 #include "clang/Basic/AttrList.inc"

422  /// Transform the given expression.
423  ///
424  /// By default, this routine transforms an expression by delegating to the
425  /// appropriate TransformXXXExpr function to build a new expression.
426  /// Subclasses may override this function to transform expressions using some
427  /// other mechanism.
428  ///
429  /// \returns the transformed expression.
430  ExprResult TransformExpr(Expr *E);
431 
432  /// Transform the given initializer.
433  ///
434  /// By default, this routine transforms an initializer by stripping off the
435  /// semantic nodes added by initialization, then passing the result to
436  /// TransformExpr or TransformExprs.
437  ///
438  /// \returns the transformed initializer.
439  ExprResult TransformInitializer(Expr *Init, bool NotCopyInit);
440 
441  /// Transform the given list of expressions.
442  ///
443  /// This routine transforms a list of expressions by invoking
444  /// \c TransformExpr() for each subexpression. However, it also provides
445  /// support for variadic templates by expanding any pack expansions (if the
446  /// derived class permits such expansion) along the way. When pack expansions
447  /// are present, the number of outputs may not equal the number of inputs.
448  ///
449  /// \param Inputs The set of expressions to be transformed.
450  ///
451  /// \param NumInputs The number of expressions in \c Inputs.
452  ///
453  /// \param IsCall If \c true, then this transform is being performed on
454  /// function-call arguments, and any arguments that should be dropped, will
455  /// be.
456  ///
457  /// \param Outputs The transformed input expressions will be added to this
458  /// vector.
459  ///
460  /// \param ArgChanged If non-NULL, will be set \c true if any argument changed
461  /// due to transformation.
462  ///
463  /// \returns true if an error occurred, false otherwise.
464  bool TransformExprs(Expr *const *Inputs, unsigned NumInputs, bool IsCall,
465  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Outputs,
466  bool *ArgChanged = nullptr);
467 
468  /// Transform the given declaration, which is referenced from a type
469  /// or expression.
470  ///
471  /// By default, acts as the identity function on declarations, unless the
472  /// transformer has had to transform the declaration itself. Subclasses
473  /// may override this function to provide alternate behavior.
474  Decl *TransformDecl(SourceLocation Loc, Decl *D) {
475  llvm::DenseMap<Decl *, Decl *>::iterator Known
476  = TransformedLocalDecls.find(D);
477  if (Known != TransformedLocalDecls.end())
478  return Known->second;
479 
480  return D;
481  }
482 
483  /// Transform the specified condition.
484  ///
485  /// By default, this transforms the variable and expression and rebuilds
486  /// the condition.
487  Sema::ConditionResult TransformCondition(SourceLocation Loc, VarDecl *Var,
488  Expr *Expr,
489  Sema::ConditionKind Kind);
490 
491  /// Transform the attributes associated with the given declaration and
492  /// place them on the new declaration.
493  ///
494  /// By default, this operation does nothing. Subclasses may override this
495  /// behavior to transform attributes.
496  void transformAttrs(Decl *Old, Decl *New) { }
497 
498  /// Note that a local declaration has been transformed by this
499  /// transformer.
500  ///
501  /// Local declarations are typically transformed via a call to
502  /// TransformDefinition. However, in some cases (e.g., lambda expressions),
503  /// the transformer itself has to transform the declarations. This routine
504  /// can be overridden by a subclass that keeps track of such mappings.
505  void transformedLocalDecl(Decl *Old, ArrayRef<Decl *> New) {
506  assert(New.size() == 1 &&
507  "must override transformedLocalDecl if performing pack expansion");
508  TransformedLocalDecls[Old] = New.front();
509  }
510 
511  /// Transform the definition of the given declaration.
512  ///
513  /// By default, invokes TransformDecl() to transform the declaration.
514  /// Subclasses may override this function to provide alternate behavior.
515  Decl *TransformDefinition(SourceLocation Loc, Decl *D) {
516  return getDerived().TransformDecl(Loc, D);
517  }
518 
519  /// Transform the given declaration, which was the first part of a
520  /// nested-name-specifier in a member access expression.
521  ///
522  /// This specific declaration transformation only applies to the first
523  /// identifier in a nested-name-specifier of a member access expression, e.g.,
524  /// the \c T in \c x->T::member
525  ///
526  /// By default, invokes TransformDecl() to transform the declaration.
527  /// Subclasses may override this function to provide alternate behavior.
528  NamedDecl *TransformFirstQualifierInScope(NamedDecl *D, SourceLocation Loc) {
529  return cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(Loc, D));
530  }

547  /// Transform the given declaration name.
548  ///
549  /// By default, transforms the types of conversion function, constructor,

551  /// Identifiers and selectors are returned unmodified. Subclasses may

566  /// Transform the given template name.
567  ///
568  /// \param SS The nested-name-specifier that qualifies the template
569  /// name. This nested-name-specifier must already have been transformed.
570  ///
571  /// \param Name The template name to transform.
572  ///
573  /// \param NameLoc The source location of the template name.
574  ///
575  /// \param ObjectType If we're translating a template name within a member
576  /// access expression, this is the type of the object whose member template
577  /// is being referenced.
578  ///
579  /// \param FirstQualifierInScope If the first part of a nested-name-specifier
580  /// also refers to a name within the current (lexical) scope, this is the
581  /// declaration it refers to.
582  ///
583  /// By default, transforms the template name by transforming the declarations
584  /// and nested-name-specifiers that occur within the template name.
585  /// Subclasses may override this function to provide alternate behavior.
586  TemplateName
587  TransformTemplateName(CXXScopeSpec &SS, TemplateName Name,
588  SourceLocation NameLoc,

590  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr,
591  bool AllowInjectedClassName = false);
592 
593  /// Transform the given template argument.
594  ///
595  /// By default, this operation transforms the type, expression, or
596  /// declaration stored within the template argument and constructs a
597  /// new template argument from the transformed result. Subclasses may
598  /// override this function to provide alternate behavior.
599  ///
600  /// Returns true if there was an error.
601  bool TransformTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgumentLoc &Input,
602  TemplateArgumentLoc &Output,
603  bool Uneval = false);
604 
605  /// Transform the given set of template arguments.
606  ///
607  /// By default, this operation transforms all of the template arguments
608  /// in the input set using \c TransformTemplateArgument(), and appends
609  /// the transformed arguments to the output list.
610  ///
611  /// Note that this overload of \c TransformTemplateArguments() is merely
612  /// a convenience function. Subclasses that wish to override this behavior
613  /// should override the iterator-based member template version.
614  ///
615  /// \param Inputs The set of template arguments to be transformed.
616  ///
617  /// \param NumInputs The number of template arguments in \p Inputs.
618  ///
619  /// \param Outputs The set of transformed template arguments output by this
620  /// routine.
621  ///
622  /// Returns true if an error occurred.
623  bool TransformTemplateArguments(const TemplateArgumentLoc *Inputs,
624  unsigned NumInputs,
625  TemplateArgumentListInfo &Outputs,
626  bool Uneval = false) {
627  return TransformTemplateArguments(Inputs, Inputs + NumInputs, Outputs,
628  Uneval);
629  }
630 
631  /// Transform the given set of template arguments.
632  ///
633  /// By default, this operation transforms all of the template arguments
634  /// in the input set using \c TransformTemplateArgument(), and appends
635  /// the transformed arguments to the output list.
636  ///
637  /// \param First An iterator to the first template argument.
638  ///
639  /// \param Last An iterator one step past the last template argument.
640  ///
641  /// \param Outputs The set of transformed template arguments output by this
642  /// routine.
643  ///
644  /// Returns true if an error occurred.
645  template<typename InputIterator>

711  /// variables vector are acceptable.

735  /// Transforms the parameters of a requires expresison into the given vectors.
736  ///
737  /// The result vectors should be kept in sync; null entries in the
738  /// variables vector are acceptable.
739  ///
740  /// Returns an unset ExprResult on success. Returns an ExprResult the 'not
741  /// satisfied' RequiresExpr if subsitution failed, OR an ExprError, both of
742  /// which are cases where transformation shouldn't continue.
743  ExprResult TransformRequiresTypeParams(
744  SourceLocation KWLoc, SourceLocation RBraceLoc, const RequiresExpr *RE,
745  RequiresExprBodyDecl *Body, ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params,
746  SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &PTypes,

750  KWLoc, Params, /*ParamTypes=*/nullptr,
751  /*ParamInfos=*/nullptr, PTypes, &TransParams, PInfos))
752  return ExprError();
753 
754  return ExprResult{};
755  }

1109  /// Build a new qualified name type.
1110  ///
1111  /// By default, builds a new ElaboratedType type from the keyword,
1112  /// the nested-name-specifier and the named type.
1113  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
1114  QualType RebuildElaboratedType(SourceLocation KeywordLoc,
1115  ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
1116  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc,
1117  QualType Named) {
1118  return SemaRef.Context.getElaboratedType(Keyword,
1119  QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier(),
1120  Named);
1121  }
1122 
1123  /// Build a new typename type that refers to a template-id.
1124  ///
1125  /// By default, builds a new DependentNameType type from the
1126  /// nested-name-specifier and the given type. Subclasses may override
1127  /// this routine to provide different behavior.
1128  QualType RebuildDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
1129  ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
1130  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc,
1131  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc,
1132  const IdentifierInfo *Name,
1133  SourceLocation NameLoc,
1134  TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
1135  bool AllowInjectedClassName) {
1136  // Rebuild the template name.
1137  // TODO: avoid TemplateName abstraction
1138  CXXScopeSpec SS;
1139  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
1140  TemplateName InstName = getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(
1141  SS, TemplateKWLoc, *Name, NameLoc, QualType(), nullptr,
1142  AllowInjectedClassName);
1143 
1144  if (InstName.isNull())
1145  return QualType();
1146 
1147  // If it's still dependent, make a dependent specialization.
1148  if (InstName.getAsDependentTemplateName())
1149  return SemaRef.Context.getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
1150  Keyword, QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier(), Name,
1151  Args.arguments());
1152 
1153  // Otherwise, make an elaborated type wrapping a non-dependent
1154  // specialization.
1155  QualType T =
1156  getDerived().RebuildTemplateSpecializationType(InstName, NameLoc, Args);
1157  if (T.isNull())
1158  return QualType();
1159  return SemaRef.Context.getElaboratedType(
1160  Keyword, QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier(), T);
1161  }
1162 
1163  /// Build a new typename type that refers to an identifier.
1164  ///
1165  /// By default, performs semantic analysis when building the typename type
1166  /// (or elaborated type). Subclasses may override this routine to provide
1167  /// different behavior.
1168  QualType RebuildDependentNameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
1169  SourceLocation KeywordLoc,
1170  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc,
1171  const IdentifierInfo *Id,
1172  SourceLocation IdLoc,
1173  bool DeducedTSTContext) {
1174  CXXScopeSpec SS;
1175  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
1176 
1177  if (QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier()->isDependent()) {
1178  // If the name is still dependent, just build a new dependent name type.
1179  if (!SemaRef.computeDeclContext(SS))
1180  return SemaRef.Context.getDependentNameType(Keyword,
1181  QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier(),
1182  Id);
1183  }
1184 
1185  if (Keyword == ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None ||
1186  Keyword == ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Typename) {
1187  return SemaRef.CheckTypenameType(Keyword, KeywordLoc, QualifierLoc,
1188  *Id, IdLoc, DeducedTSTContext);
1189  }
1190 
1191  TagTypeKind Kind = TypeWithKeyword::getTagTypeKindForKeyword(Keyword);
1192 
1193  // We had a dependent elaborated-type-specifier that has been transformed
1194  // into a non-dependent elaborated-type-specifier. Find the tag we're
1195  // referring to.
1196  LookupResult Result(SemaRef, Id, IdLoc, Sema::LookupTagName);
1197  DeclContext *DC = SemaRef.computeDeclContext(SS, false);
1198  if (!DC)
1199  return QualType();
1200 
1201  if (SemaRef.RequireCompleteDeclContext(SS, DC))
1202  return QualType();
1203 
1204  TagDecl *Tag = nullptr;
1205  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Result, DC);
1206  switch (Result.getResultKind()) {
1207  case LookupResult::NotFound:
1208  case LookupResult::NotFoundInCurrentInstantiation:
1209  break;
1210 
1211  case LookupResult::Found:
1212  Tag = Result.getAsSingle<TagDecl>();
1213  break;
1214 
1215  case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded:
1216  case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue:
1217  llvm_unreachable("Tag lookup cannot find non-tags");
1218 
1219  case LookupResult::Ambiguous:
1220  // Let the LookupResult structure handle ambiguities.
1221  return QualType();
1222  }
1223 
1224  if (!Tag) {
1225  // Check where the name exists but isn't a tag type and use that to emit
1226  // better diagnostics.
1227  LookupResult Result(SemaRef, Id, IdLoc, Sema::LookupTagName);
1228  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Result, DC);
1229  switch (Result.getResultKind()) {
1230  case LookupResult::Found:
1231  case LookupResult::FoundOverloaded:
1232  case LookupResult::FoundUnresolvedValue: {
1233  NamedDecl *SomeDecl = Result.getRepresentativeDecl();
1234  Sema::NonTagKind NTK = SemaRef.getNonTagTypeDeclKind(SomeDecl, Kind);
1235  SemaRef.Diag(IdLoc, diag::err_tag_reference_non_tag)
1236  << SomeDecl << NTK << llvm::to_underlying(Kind);
1237  SemaRef.Diag(SomeDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_declared_at);
1238  break;
1239  }
1240  default:
1241  SemaRef.Diag(IdLoc, diag::err_not_tag_in_scope)
1242  << llvm::to_underlying(Kind) << Id << DC
1243  << QualifierLoc.getSourceRange();
1244  break;
1245  }
1246  return QualType();
1247  }
1248 
1249  if (!SemaRef.isAcceptableTagRedeclaration(Tag, Kind, /*isDefinition*/false,
1250  IdLoc, Id)) {
1251  SemaRef.Diag(KeywordLoc, diag::err_use_with_wrong_tag) << Id;
1252  SemaRef.Diag(Tag->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_use);
1253  return QualType();
1254  }
1255 
1256  // Build the elaborated-type-specifier type.
1257  QualType T = SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(Tag);
1258  return SemaRef.Context.getElaboratedType(Keyword,

1260  T);
1261  }

1556  /// Build a new co_await expression.
1557  ///
1558  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
1559  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
1560  ExprResult RebuildCoawaitExpr(SourceLocation CoawaitLoc, Expr *Operand,
1561  UnresolvedLookupExpr *OpCoawaitLookup,
1562  bool IsImplicit) {
1563  // This function rebuilds a coawait-expr given its operator.
1564  // For an explicit coawait-expr, the rebuild involves the full set
1565  // of transformations performed by BuildUnresolvedCoawaitExpr(),
1566  // including calling await_transform().
1567  // For an implicit coawait-expr, we need to rebuild the "operator
1568  // coawait" but not await_transform(), so use BuildResolvedCoawaitExpr().
1569  // This mirrors how the implicit CoawaitExpr is originally created
1570  // in Sema::ActOnCoroutineBodyStart().
1571  if (IsImplicit) {
1572  ExprResult Suspend = getSema().BuildOperatorCoawaitCall(
1573  CoawaitLoc, Operand, OpCoawaitLookup);
1574  if (Suspend.isInvalid())
1575  return ExprError();
1576  return getSema().BuildResolvedCoawaitExpr(CoawaitLoc, Operand,
1577  Suspend.get(), true);
1578  }
1579 
1580  return getSema().BuildUnresolvedCoawaitExpr(CoawaitLoc, Operand,
1581  OpCoawaitLookup);
1582  }
1583 
1584  /// Build a new co_await expression.
1585  ///
1586  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
1587  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
1588  ExprResult RebuildDependentCoawaitExpr(SourceLocation CoawaitLoc,
1589  Expr *Result,
1590  UnresolvedLookupExpr *Lookup) {
1591  return getSema().BuildUnresolvedCoawaitExpr(CoawaitLoc, Result, Lookup);
1592  }

2573  /// Build a new C++0x range-based for statement.
2574  ///
2575  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new statement.
2576  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
2577  StmtResult RebuildCXXForRangeStmt(
2578  SourceLocation ForLoc, SourceLocation CoawaitLoc, Stmt *Init,
2579  SourceLocation ColonLoc, Stmt *Range, Stmt *Begin, Stmt *End, Expr *Cond,
2580  Expr *Inc, Stmt *LoopVar, SourceLocation RParenLoc,
2581  ArrayRef<MaterializeTemporaryExpr *> LifetimeExtendTemps) {
2582  // If we've just learned that the range is actually an Objective-C
2583  // collection, treat this as an Objective-C fast enumeration loop.
2584  if (DeclStmt *RangeStmt = dyn_cast<DeclStmt>(Range)) {
2585  if (RangeStmt->isSingleDecl()) {
2586  if (VarDecl *RangeVar = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(RangeStmt->getSingleDecl())) {
2587  if (RangeVar->isInvalidDecl())
2588  return StmtError();
2589 
2590  Expr *RangeExpr = RangeVar->getInit();
2591  if (!RangeExpr->isTypeDependent() &&
2592  RangeExpr->getType()->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
2593  // FIXME: Support init-statements in Objective-C++20 ranged for
2594  // statement.
2595  if (Init) {
2596  return SemaRef.Diag(Init->getBeginLoc(),
2597  diag::err_objc_for_range_init_stmt)
2598  << Init->getSourceRange();
2599  }
2600  return getSema().ActOnObjCForCollectionStmt(ForLoc, LoopVar,
2601  RangeExpr, RParenLoc);
2602  }
2603  }
2604  }
2605  }
2606 
2607  return getSema().BuildCXXForRangeStmt(
2608  ForLoc, CoawaitLoc, Init, ColonLoc, Range, Begin, End, Cond, Inc,
2609  LoopVar, RParenLoc, Sema::BFRK_Rebuild, LifetimeExtendTemps);
2610  }

2849  /// Build a new member access expression.
2850  ///
2851  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
2852  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
2853  ExprResult RebuildMemberExpr(Expr *Base, SourceLocation OpLoc,
2854  bool isArrow,
2855  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc,
2856  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc,
2857  const DeclarationNameInfo &MemberNameInfo,
2858  ValueDecl *Member,
2859  NamedDecl *FoundDecl,
2860  const TemplateArgumentListInfo *ExplicitTemplateArgs,
2861  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope) {
2862  ExprResult BaseResult = getSema().PerformMemberExprBaseConversion(Base,
2863  isArrow);
2864  if (!Member->getDeclName()) {
2865  // We have a reference to an unnamed field. This is always the
2866  // base of an anonymous struct/union member access, i.e. the
2867  // field is always of record type.
2868  assert(Member->getType()->isRecordType() &&
2869  "unnamed member not of record type?");
2870 
2871  BaseResult =
2872  getSema().PerformObjectMemberConversion(BaseResult.get(),
2873  QualifierLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier(),
2874  FoundDecl, Member);
2875  if (BaseResult.isInvalid())
2876  return ExprError();
2877  Base = BaseResult.get();
2878 
2879  CXXScopeSpec EmptySS;
2880  return getSema().BuildFieldReferenceExpr(
2881  Base, isArrow, OpLoc, EmptySS, cast<FieldDecl>(Member),
2882  DeclAccessPair::make(FoundDecl, FoundDecl->getAccess()), MemberNameInfo);
2883  }
2884 
2885  CXXScopeSpec SS;
2886  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
2887 
2888  Base = BaseResult.get();
2889  QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
2890 
2891  if (isArrow && !BaseType->isPointerType())
2892  return ExprError();
2893 
2894  // FIXME: this involves duplicating earlier analysis in a lot of
2895  // cases; we should avoid this when possible.
2896  LookupResult R(getSema(), MemberNameInfo, Sema::LookupMemberName);
2897  R.addDecl(FoundDecl);
2898  R.resolveKind();
2899 
2900  if (getSema().isUnevaluatedContext() && Base->isImplicitCXXThis() &&
2901  isa<FieldDecl, IndirectFieldDecl, MSPropertyDecl>(Member)) {
2902  if (auto *ThisClass = cast<CXXThisExpr>(Base)
2903  ->getType()
2904  ->getPointeeType()
2905  ->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
2906  auto *Class = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Member->getDeclContext());
2907  // In unevaluated contexts, an expression supposed to be a member access
2908  // might reference a member in an unrelated class.
2909  if (!ThisClass->Equals(Class) && !ThisClass->isDerivedFrom(Class))
2910  return getSema().BuildDeclRefExpr(Member, Member->getType(),
2911  VK_LValue, Member->getLocation());
2912  }
2913  }
2914 
2915  return getSema().BuildMemberReferenceExpr(Base, BaseType, OpLoc, isArrow,
2916  SS, TemplateKWLoc,
2917  FirstQualifierInScope,
2918  R, ExplicitTemplateArgs,
2919  /*S*/nullptr);
2920  }
2921 
2922  /// Build a new binary operator expression.
2923  ///
2924  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
2925  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
2926  ExprResult RebuildBinaryOperator(SourceLocation OpLoc,
2927  BinaryOperatorKind Opc,
2928  Expr *LHS, Expr *RHS) {
2929  return getSema().BuildBinOp(/*Scope=*/nullptr, OpLoc, Opc, LHS, RHS);
2930  }

2943  /// Build a new conditional operator expression.
2944  ///
2945  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
2946  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
2947  ExprResult RebuildConditionalOperator(Expr *Cond,
2948  SourceLocation QuestionLoc,
2949  Expr *LHS,
2950  SourceLocation ColonLoc,

3134  /// Build a new C++ "named" cast expression, such as static_cast or
3135  /// reinterpret_cast.
3136  ///
3137  /// By default, this routine dispatches to one of the more-specific routines
3138  /// for a particular named case, e.g., RebuildCXXStaticCastExpr().
3139  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
3140  ExprResult RebuildCXXNamedCastExpr(SourceLocation OpLoc,
3141  Stmt::StmtClass Class,
3142  SourceLocation LAngleLoc,
3143  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo,
3144  SourceLocation RAngleLoc,
3145  SourceLocation LParenLoc,
3146  Expr *SubExpr,
3147  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
3148  switch (Class) {
3149  case Stmt::CXXStaticCastExprClass:
3150  return getDerived().RebuildCXXStaticCastExpr(OpLoc, LAngleLoc, TInfo,
3151  RAngleLoc, LParenLoc,
3152  SubExpr, RParenLoc);
3153 
3154  case Stmt::CXXDynamicCastExprClass:
3155  return getDerived().RebuildCXXDynamicCastExpr(OpLoc, LAngleLoc, TInfo,
3156  RAngleLoc, LParenLoc,
3157  SubExpr, RParenLoc);
3158 
3159  case Stmt::CXXReinterpretCastExprClass:
3160  return getDerived().RebuildCXXReinterpretCastExpr(OpLoc, LAngleLoc, TInfo,
3161  RAngleLoc, LParenLoc,
3162  SubExpr,
3163  RParenLoc);
3164 
3165  case Stmt::CXXConstCastExprClass:
3166  return getDerived().RebuildCXXConstCastExpr(OpLoc, LAngleLoc, TInfo,
3167  RAngleLoc, LParenLoc,
3168  SubExpr, RParenLoc);
3169 
3170  case Stmt::CXXAddrspaceCastExprClass:
3171  return getDerived().RebuildCXXAddrspaceCastExpr(
3172  OpLoc, LAngleLoc, TInfo, RAngleLoc, LParenLoc, SubExpr, RParenLoc);
3173 
3174  default:
3175  llvm_unreachable("Invalid C++ named cast");
3176  }
3177  }

3274  MultiExprArg(&Sub, 1), RParenLoc,

3512  /// Build a new object-construction expression.
3513  ///
3514  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
3515  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
3516  ExprResult RebuildCXXConstructExpr(
3517  QualType T, SourceLocation Loc, CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor,
3518  bool IsElidable, MultiExprArg Args, bool HadMultipleCandidates,
3519  bool ListInitialization, bool StdInitListInitialization,
3520  bool RequiresZeroInit, CXXConstructionKind ConstructKind,
3521  SourceRange ParenRange) {
3522  // Reconstruct the constructor we originally found, which might be
3523  // different if this is a call to an inherited constructor.
3524  CXXConstructorDecl *FoundCtor = Constructor;
3525  if (Constructor->isInheritingConstructor())
3526  FoundCtor = Constructor->getInheritedConstructor().getConstructor();
3527 
3528  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> ConvertedArgs;
3529  if (getSema().CompleteConstructorCall(FoundCtor, T, Args, Loc,
3530  ConvertedArgs))
3531  return ExprError();
3532 
3533  return getSema().BuildCXXConstructExpr(Loc, T, Constructor,
3534  IsElidable,
3535  ConvertedArgs,
3536  HadMultipleCandidates,
3537  ListInitialization,
3538  StdInitListInitialization,
3539  RequiresZeroInit, ConstructKind,
3540  ParenRange);
3541  }

3908  /// Build a new shuffle vector expression.
3909  ///
3910  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build the new expression.
3911  /// Subclasses may override this routine to provide different behavior.
3912  ExprResult RebuildShuffleVectorExpr(SourceLocation BuiltinLoc,
3913  MultiExprArg SubExprs,
3914  SourceLocation RParenLoc) {
3915  // Find the declaration for __builtin_shufflevector
3916  const IdentifierInfo &Name
3917  = SemaRef.Context.Idents.get("__builtin_shufflevector");
3918  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = SemaRef.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
3919  DeclContext::lookup_result Lookup = TUDecl->lookup(DeclarationName(&Name));
3920  assert(!Lookup.empty() && "No __builtin_shufflevector?");
3921 
3922  // Build a reference to the __builtin_shufflevector builtin
3923  FunctionDecl *Builtin = cast<FunctionDecl>(Lookup.front());
3924  Expr *Callee = new (SemaRef.Context)
3925  DeclRefExpr(SemaRef.Context, Builtin, false,
3926  SemaRef.Context.BuiltinFnTy, VK_PRValue, BuiltinLoc);
3927  QualType CalleePtrTy = SemaRef.Context.getPointerType(Builtin->getType());
3928  Callee = SemaRef.ImpCastExprToType(Callee, CalleePtrTy,
3929  CK_BuiltinFnToFnPtr).get();
3930 
3931  // Build the CallExpr
3932  ExprResult TheCall = CallExpr::Create(
3933  SemaRef.Context, Callee, SubExprs, Builtin->getCallResultType(),
3934  Expr::getValueKindForType(Builtin->getReturnType()), RParenLoc,
3935  FPOptionsOverride());
3936 
3937  // Type-check the __builtin_shufflevector expression.
3938  return SemaRef.BuiltinShuffleVector(cast<CallExpr>(TheCall.get()));
3939  }

3948  /// Build a new template argument pack expansion.
3949  ///
3950  /// By default, performs semantic analysis to build a new pack expansion
3951  /// for a template argument. Subclasses may override this routine to provide
3952  /// different behavior.
3953  TemplateArgumentLoc
3954  RebuildPackExpansion(TemplateArgumentLoc Pattern, SourceLocation EllipsisLoc,
3955  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions) {
3956  switch (Pattern.getArgument().getKind()) {
3957  case TemplateArgument::Expression: {
3958  ExprResult Result
3959  = getSema().CheckPackExpansion(Pattern.getSourceExpression(),
3960  EllipsisLoc, NumExpansions);
3961  if (Result.isInvalid())
3962  return TemplateArgumentLoc();
3963 
3964  return TemplateArgumentLoc(Result.get(), Result.get());
3965  }
3966 
3967  case TemplateArgument::Template:
3968  return TemplateArgumentLoc(
3969  SemaRef.Context,
3970  TemplateArgument(Pattern.getArgument().getAsTemplate(),
3971  NumExpansions),
3972  Pattern.getTemplateQualifierLoc(), Pattern.getTemplateNameLoc(),
3973  EllipsisLoc);
3974 
3975  case TemplateArgument::Null:
3976  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
3977  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
3978  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue:
3979  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
3980  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
3981  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
3982  llvm_unreachable("Pack expansion pattern has no parameter packs");
3983 
3984  case TemplateArgument::Type:
3985  if (TypeSourceInfo *Expansion
3986  = getSema().CheckPackExpansion(Pattern.getTypeSourceInfo(),
3987  EllipsisLoc,
3988  NumExpansions))
3989  return TemplateArgumentLoc(TemplateArgument(Expansion->getType()),
3990  Expansion);
3991  break;
3992  }
3993 
3994  return TemplateArgumentLoc();
3995  }
3996

4004  return getSema().CheckPackExpansion(Pattern, EllipsisLoc, NumExpansions);

4088 template <typename Derived>
4089 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformStmt(Stmt *S, StmtDiscardKind SDK) {
4090  if (!S)
4091  return S;
4092 
4093  switch (S->getStmtClass()) {
4094  case Stmt::NoStmtClass: break;
4095 
4096  // Transform individual statement nodes
4097  // Pass SDK into statements that can produce a value
4098 #define STMT(Node, Parent) \
4099  case Stmt::Node##Class: return getDerived().Transform##Node(cast<Node>(S));
4100 #define VALUESTMT(Node, Parent) \
4101  case Stmt::Node##Class: \
4102  return getDerived().Transform##Node(cast<Node>(S), SDK);
4103 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Node)
4104 #define EXPR(Node, Parent)
4105 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
4106 
4107  // Transform expressions by calling TransformExpr.
4108 #define STMT(Node, Parent)
4109 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Stmt)
4110 #define EXPR(Node, Parent) case Stmt::Node##Class:
4111 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
4112  {
4113  ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(S));
4114 
4115  if (SDK == SDK_StmtExprResult)
4116  E = getSema().ActOnStmtExprResult(E);
4117  return getSema().ActOnExprStmt(E, SDK == SDK_Discarded);
4118  }
4119  }
4120 
4121  return S;
4122 }
4123 
4124 template<typename Derived>
4125 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPClause(OMPClause *S) {
4126  if (!S)
4127  return S;
4128 
4129  switch (S->getClauseKind()) {
4130  default: break;
4131  // Transform individual clause nodes
4132 #define GEN_CLANG_CLAUSE_CLASS
4133 #define CLAUSE_CLASS(Enum, Str, Class) \
4134  case Enum: \
4135  return getDerived().Transform##Class(cast<Class>(S));
4136 #include "llvm/Frontend/OpenMP/OMP.inc"
4137  }
4138 
4139  return S;
4140 }
4141 
4142 
4143 template<typename Derived>
4144 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExpr(Expr *E) {
4145  if (!E)
4146  return E;
4147 
4148  switch (E->getStmtClass()) {
4149  case Stmt::NoStmtClass: break;
4150 #define STMT(Node, Parent) case Stmt::Node##Class: break;
4151 #define ABSTRACT_STMT(Stmt)
4152 #define EXPR(Node, Parent) \
4153  case Stmt::Node##Class: return getDerived().Transform##Node(cast<Node>(E));
4154 #include "clang/AST/StmtNodes.inc"
4155  }
4156 
4157  return E;
4158 }
4159 
4160 template<typename Derived>
4161 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformInitializer(Expr *Init,
4162  bool NotCopyInit) {
4163  // Initializers are instantiated like expressions, except that various outer
4164  // layers are stripped.
4165  if (!Init)
4166  return Init;
4167 
4168  if (auto *FE = dyn_cast<FullExpr>(Init))
4169  Init = FE->getSubExpr();
4170 
4171  if (auto *AIL = dyn_cast<ArrayInitLoopExpr>(Init)) {
4172  OpaqueValueExpr *OVE = AIL->getCommonExpr();
4173  Init = OVE->getSourceExpr();
4174  }
4175 
4176  if (MaterializeTemporaryExpr *MTE = dyn_cast<MaterializeTemporaryExpr>(Init))
4177  Init = MTE->getSubExpr();
4178 
4179  while (CXXBindTemporaryExpr *Binder = dyn_cast<CXXBindTemporaryExpr>(Init))
4180  Init = Binder->getSubExpr();
4181 
4182  if (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Init))
4183  Init = ICE->getSubExprAsWritten();
4184 
4185  if (CXXStdInitializerListExpr *ILE =
4186  dyn_cast<CXXStdInitializerListExpr>(Init))
4187  return TransformInitializer(ILE->getSubExpr(), NotCopyInit);
4188 
4189  // If this is copy-initialization, we only need to reconstruct
4190  // InitListExprs. Other forms of copy-initialization will be a no-op if
4191  // the initializer is already the right type.
4192  CXXConstructExpr *Construct = dyn_cast<CXXConstructExpr>(Init);
4193  if (!NotCopyInit && !(Construct && Construct->isListInitialization()))
4194  return getDerived().TransformExpr(Init);
4195 
4196  // Revert value-initialization back to empty parens.
4197  if (CXXScalarValueInitExpr *VIE = dyn_cast<CXXScalarValueInitExpr>(Init)) {
4198  SourceRange Parens = VIE->getSourceRange();
4199  return getDerived().RebuildParenListExpr(Parens.getBegin(), std::nullopt,
4200  Parens.getEnd());
4201  }
4202 
4203  // FIXME: We shouldn't build ImplicitValueInitExprs for direct-initialization.
4204  if (isa<ImplicitValueInitExpr>(Init))
4205  return getDerived().RebuildParenListExpr(SourceLocation(), std::nullopt,
4206  SourceLocation());
4207 
4208  // Revert initialization by constructor back to a parenthesized or braced list
4209  // of expressions. Any other form of initializer can just be reused directly.
4210  if (!Construct || isa<CXXTemporaryObjectExpr>(Construct))
4211  return getDerived().TransformExpr(Init);
4212 
4213  // If the initialization implicitly converted an initializer list to a
4214  // std::initializer_list object, unwrap the std::initializer_list too.
4215  if (Construct && Construct->isStdInitListInitialization())
4216  return TransformInitializer(Construct->getArg(0), NotCopyInit);
4217 
4218  // Enter a list-init context if this was list initialization.
4219  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
4220  getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
4221  Construct->isListInitialization());
4222 
4223  getSema().keepInLifetimeExtendingContext();
4224  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> NewArgs;
4225  bool ArgChanged = false;
4226  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(Construct->getArgs(), Construct->getNumArgs(),
4227  /*IsCall*/true, NewArgs, &ArgChanged))
4228  return ExprError();
4229 
4230  // If this was list initialization, revert to syntactic list form.
4231  if (Construct->isListInitialization())
4232  return getDerived().RebuildInitList(Construct->getBeginLoc(), NewArgs,
4233  Construct->getEndLoc());
4234 
4235  // Build a ParenListExpr to represent anything else.
4236  SourceRange Parens = Construct->getParenOrBraceRange();
4237  if (Parens.isInvalid()) {
4238  // This was a variable declaration's initialization for which no initializer
4239  // was specified.
4240  assert(NewArgs.empty() &&
4241  "no parens or braces but have direct init with arguments?");
4242  return ExprEmpty();
4243  }
4244  return getDerived().RebuildParenListExpr(Parens.getBegin(), NewArgs,
4245  Parens.getEnd());
4246 }
4247 
4248 template<typename Derived>
4249 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExprs(Expr *const *Inputs,
4250  unsigned NumInputs,
4251  bool IsCall,
4252  SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Outputs,
4253  bool *ArgChanged) {
4254  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumInputs; ++I) {
4255  // If requested, drop call arguments that need to be dropped.
4256  if (IsCall && getDerived().DropCallArgument(Inputs[I])) {
4257  if (ArgChanged)
4258  *ArgChanged = true;
4259 
4260  break;
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (PackExpansionExpr *Expansion = dyn_cast<PackExpansionExpr>(Inputs[I])) {
4264  Expr *Pattern = Expansion->getPattern();
4265 
4266  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
4267  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
4268  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
4269 
4270  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
4271  // be expanded.
4272  bool Expand = true;
4273  bool RetainExpansion = false;
4274  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions = Expansion->getNumExpansions();
4275  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
4276  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(Expansion->getEllipsisLoc(),
4277  Pattern->getSourceRange(),
4278  Unexpanded,
4279  Expand, RetainExpansion,
4280  NumExpansions))
4281  return true;
4282 
4283  if (!Expand) {
4284  // The transform has determined that we should perform a simple
4285  // transformation on the pack expansion, producing another pack
4286  // expansion.
4287  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
4288  ExprResult OutPattern = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
4289  if (OutPattern.isInvalid())
4290  return true;
4291 
4292  ExprResult Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(OutPattern.get(),
4293  Expansion->getEllipsisLoc(),
4294  NumExpansions);
4295  if (Out.isInvalid())
4296  return true;
4297 
4298  if (ArgChanged)
4299  *ArgChanged = true;
4300  Outputs.push_back(Out.get());
4301  continue;
4302  }
4303 
4304  // Record right away that the argument was changed. This needs
4305  // to happen even if the array expands to nothing.
4306  if (ArgChanged) *ArgChanged = true;
4307 
4308  // The transform has determined that we should perform an elementwise
4309  // expansion of the pattern. Do so.
4310  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
4311  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
4312  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
4313  if (Out.isInvalid())
4314  return true;
4315 
4316  if (Out.get()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
4317  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(
4318  Out.get(), Expansion->getEllipsisLoc(), OrigNumExpansions);
4319  if (Out.isInvalid())
4320  return true;
4321  }
4322 
4323  Outputs.push_back(Out.get());
4324  }
4325 
4326  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
4327  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
4328  if (RetainExpansion) {
4329  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
4330 
4331  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
4332  if (Out.isInvalid())
4333  return true;
4334 
4335  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(
4336  Out.get(), Expansion->getEllipsisLoc(), OrigNumExpansions);
4337  if (Out.isInvalid())
4338  return true;
4339 
4340  Outputs.push_back(Out.get());
4341  }
4342 
4343  continue;
4344  }
4345 
4346  ExprResult Result =
4347  IsCall ? getDerived().TransformInitializer(Inputs[I], /*DirectInit*/false)
4348  : getDerived().TransformExpr(Inputs[I]);
4349  if (Result.isInvalid())
4350  return true;
4351 
4352  if (Result.get() != Inputs[I] && ArgChanged)
4353  *ArgChanged = true;
4354 
4355  Outputs.push_back(Result.get());
4356  }
4357 
4358  return false;
4359 }
4360 
4361 template <typename Derived>
4362 Sema::ConditionResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCondition(
4363  SourceLocation Loc, VarDecl *Var, Expr *Expr, Sema::ConditionKind Kind) {
4364  if (Var) {
4365  VarDecl *ConditionVar = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(
4366  getDerived().TransformDefinition(Var->getLocation(), Var));
4367 
4368  if (!ConditionVar)
4369  return Sema::ConditionError();
4370 
4371  return getSema().ActOnConditionVariable(ConditionVar, Loc, Kind);
4372  }
4373 
4374  if (Expr) {
4375  ExprResult CondExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(Expr);
4376 
4377  if (CondExpr.isInvalid())
4378  return Sema::ConditionError();
4379 
4380  return getSema().ActOnCondition(nullptr, Loc, CondExpr.get(), Kind,
4381  /*MissingOK=*/true);
4382  }
4383 
4384  return Sema::ConditionResult();
4385 }
4386 
4387 template <typename Derived>
4388 NestedNameSpecifierLoc TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(
4389  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS, QualType ObjectType,
4390  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope) {
4391  SmallVector<NestedNameSpecifierLoc, 4> Qualifiers;
4392 
4393  auto insertNNS = [&Qualifiers](NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNS) {
4394  for (NestedNameSpecifierLoc Qualifier = NNS; Qualifier;
4395  Qualifier = Qualifier.getPrefix())
4396  Qualifiers.push_back(Qualifier);
4397  };
4398  insertNNS(NNS);
4399 
4400  CXXScopeSpec SS;
4401  while (!Qualifiers.empty()) {
4402  NestedNameSpecifierLoc Q = Qualifiers.pop_back_val();
4403  NestedNameSpecifier *QNNS = Q.getNestedNameSpecifier();
4404 
4405  switch (QNNS->getKind()) {
4406  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier: {
4407  Sema::NestedNameSpecInfo IdInfo(QNNS->getAsIdentifier(),
4408  Q.getLocalBeginLoc(), Q.getLocalEndLoc(),
4409  ObjectType);
4410  if (SemaRef.BuildCXXNestedNameSpecifier(/*Scope=*/nullptr, IdInfo, false,
4411  SS, FirstQualifierInScope, false))
4412  return NestedNameSpecifierLoc();
4413  break;
4414  }
4415 
4416  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace: {
4417  NamespaceDecl *NS =
4418  cast_or_null<NamespaceDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
4419  Q.getLocalBeginLoc(), QNNS->getAsNamespace()));
4420  SS.Extend(SemaRef.Context, NS, Q.getLocalBeginLoc(), Q.getLocalEndLoc());
4421  break;
4422  }
4423 
4424  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias: {
4425  NamespaceAliasDecl *Alias =
4426  cast_or_null<NamespaceAliasDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
4427  Q.getLocalBeginLoc(), QNNS->getAsNamespaceAlias()));
4428  SS.Extend(SemaRef.Context, Alias, Q.getLocalBeginLoc(),
4429  Q.getLocalEndLoc());
4430  break;
4431  }
4432 
4433  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
4434  // There is no meaningful transformation that one could perform on the
4435  // global scope.
4436  SS.MakeGlobal(SemaRef.Context, Q.getBeginLoc());
4437  break;
4438 
4439  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super: {
4440  CXXRecordDecl *RD =
4441  cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
4442  SourceLocation(), QNNS->getAsRecordDecl()));
4443  SS.MakeSuper(SemaRef.Context, RD, Q.getBeginLoc(), Q.getEndLoc());
4444  break;
4445  }
4446 
4447  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
4448  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec: {
4449  TypeLoc TL = TransformTypeInObjectScope(Q.getTypeLoc(), ObjectType,
4450  FirstQualifierInScope, SS);
4451 
4452  if (!TL)
4453  return NestedNameSpecifierLoc();
4454 
4455  QualType T = TL.getType();
4456  if (T->isDependentType() || T->isRecordType() ||
4457  (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 && T->isEnumeralType())) {
4458  if (T->isEnumeralType())
4459  SemaRef.Diag(TL.getBeginLoc(),
4460  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_enum_nested_name_spec);
4461 
4462  if (const auto ETL = TL.getAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>()) {
4463  SS.Adopt(ETL.getQualifierLoc());
4464  TL = ETL.getNamedTypeLoc();
4465  }
4466 
4467  SS.Extend(SemaRef.Context, TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc(), TL,
4468  Q.getLocalEndLoc());
4469  break;
4470  }
4471  // If the nested-name-specifier is an invalid type def, don't emit an
4472  // error because a previous error should have already been emitted.
4473  TypedefTypeLoc TTL = TL.getAsAdjusted<TypedefTypeLoc>();
4474  if (!TTL || !TTL.getTypedefNameDecl()->isInvalidDecl()) {
4475  SemaRef.Diag(TL.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_nested_name_spec_non_tag)
4476  << T << SS.getRange();
4477  }
4478  return NestedNameSpecifierLoc();
4479  }
4480  }
4481 
4482  // The qualifier-in-scope and object type only apply to the leftmost entity.
4483  FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr;
4484  ObjectType = QualType();
4485  }
4486 
4487  // Don't rebuild the nested-name-specifier if we don't have to.
4488  if (SS.getScopeRep() == NNS.getNestedNameSpecifier() &&
4489  !getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
4490  return NNS;
4491 
4492  // If we can re-use the source-location data from the original
4493  // nested-name-specifier, do so.
4494  if (SS.location_size() == NNS.getDataLength() &&
4495  memcmp(SS.location_data(), NNS.getOpaqueData(), SS.location_size()) == 0)
4496  return NestedNameSpecifierLoc(SS.getScopeRep(), NNS.getOpaqueData());
4497 
4498  // Allocate new nested-name-specifier location information.
4499  return SS.getWithLocInContext(SemaRef.Context);
4500 }
4501 
4502 template<typename Derived>
4503 DeclarationNameInfo
4504 TreeTransform<Derived>
4505 ::TransformDeclarationNameInfo(const DeclarationNameInfo &NameInfo) {
4506  DeclarationName Name = NameInfo.getName();
4507  if (!Name)
4508  return DeclarationNameInfo();
4509 
4510  switch (Name.getNameKind()) {
4511  case DeclarationName::Identifier:
4512  case DeclarationName::ObjCZeroArgSelector:
4513  case DeclarationName::ObjCOneArgSelector:
4514  case DeclarationName::ObjCMultiArgSelector:
4515  case DeclarationName::CXXOperatorName:
4516  case DeclarationName::CXXLiteralOperatorName:
4517  case DeclarationName::CXXUsingDirective:
4518  return NameInfo;
4519 
4520  case DeclarationName::CXXDeductionGuideName: {
4521  TemplateDecl *OldTemplate = Name.getCXXDeductionGuideTemplate();
4522  TemplateDecl *NewTemplate = cast_or_null<TemplateDecl>(
4523  getDerived().TransformDecl(NameInfo.getLoc(), OldTemplate));
4524  if (!NewTemplate)
4525  return DeclarationNameInfo();
4526 
4527  DeclarationNameInfo NewNameInfo(NameInfo);
4528  NewNameInfo.setName(
4529  SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDeductionGuideName(NewTemplate));
4530  return NewNameInfo;
4531  }
4532 
4533  case DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName:
4534  case DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName:
4535  case DeclarationName::CXXConversionFunctionName: {
4536  TypeSourceInfo *NewTInfo;
4537  CanQualType NewCanTy;
4538  if (TypeSourceInfo *OldTInfo = NameInfo.getNamedTypeInfo()) {
4539  NewTInfo = getDerived().TransformType(OldTInfo);
4540  if (!NewTInfo)
4541  return DeclarationNameInfo();
4542  NewCanTy = SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(NewTInfo->getType());
4543  }
4544  else {
4545  NewTInfo = nullptr;
4546  TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, NameInfo.getLoc(), Name);
4547  QualType NewT = getDerived().TransformType(Name.getCXXNameType());
4548  if (NewT.isNull())
4549  return DeclarationNameInfo();
4550  NewCanTy = SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(NewT);
4551  }
4552 
4553  DeclarationName NewName
4554  = SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXSpecialName(Name.getNameKind(),
4555  NewCanTy);
4556  DeclarationNameInfo NewNameInfo(NameInfo);
4557  NewNameInfo.setName(NewName);
4558  NewNameInfo.setNamedTypeInfo(NewTInfo);
4559  return NewNameInfo;
4560  }
4561  }
4562 
4563  llvm_unreachable("Unknown name kind.");
4564 }
4565 
4566 template<typename Derived>
4567 TemplateName
4568 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTemplateName(CXXScopeSpec &SS,
4569  TemplateName Name,
4570  SourceLocation NameLoc,
4571  QualType ObjectType,
4572  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope,
4573  bool AllowInjectedClassName) {
4574  if (QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = Name.getAsQualifiedTemplateName()) {
4575  TemplateDecl *Template = QTN->getUnderlyingTemplate().getAsTemplateDecl();
4576  assert(Template && "qualified template name must refer to a template");
4577 
4578  TemplateDecl *TransTemplate
4579  = cast_or_null<TemplateDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(NameLoc,
4580  Template));
4581  if (!TransTemplate)
4582  return TemplateName();
4583 
4584  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
4585  SS.getScopeRep() == QTN->getQualifier() &&
4586  TransTemplate == Template)
4587  return Name;
4588 
4589  return getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(SS, QTN->hasTemplateKeyword(),
4590  TransTemplate);
4591  }
4592 
4593  if (DependentTemplateName *DTN = Name.getAsDependentTemplateName()) {
4594  if (SS.getScopeRep()) {
4595  // These apply to the scope specifier, not the template.
4596  ObjectType = QualType();
4597  FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr;
4598  }
4599 
4600  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
4601  SS.getScopeRep() == DTN->getQualifier() &&
4602  ObjectType.isNull())
4603  return Name;
4604 
4605  // FIXME: Preserve the location of the "template" keyword.
4606  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = NameLoc;
4607 
4608  if (DTN->isIdentifier()) {
4609  return getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(SS,
4610  TemplateKWLoc,
4611  *DTN->getIdentifier(),
4612  NameLoc,
4613  ObjectType,
4614  FirstQualifierInScope,
4615  AllowInjectedClassName);
4616  }
4617 
4618  return getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(SS, TemplateKWLoc,
4619  DTN->getOperator(), NameLoc,
4620  ObjectType, AllowInjectedClassName);
4621  }
4622 
4623  if (TemplateDecl *Template = Name.getAsTemplateDecl()) {
4624  TemplateDecl *TransTemplate
4625  = cast_or_null<TemplateDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(NameLoc,
4626  Template));
4627  if (!TransTemplate)
4628  return TemplateName();
4629 
4630  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
4631  TransTemplate == Template)
4632  return Name;
4633 
4634  return TemplateName(TransTemplate);
4635  }
4636 
4637  if (SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *SubstPack
4638  = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack()) {
4639  return getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(
4640  SubstPack->getArgumentPack(), SubstPack->getAssociatedDecl(),
4641  SubstPack->getIndex(), SubstPack->getFinal());
4642  }
4643 
4644  // These should be getting filtered out before they reach the AST.
4645  llvm_unreachable("overloaded function decl survived to here");
4646 }

4648 template<typename Derived>
4649 void TreeTransform<Derived>::InventTemplateArgumentLoc(
4650  const TemplateArgument &Arg,
4651  TemplateArgumentLoc &Output) {
4652  Output = getSema().getTrivialTemplateArgumentLoc(
4653  Arg, QualType(), getDerived().getBaseLocation());
4654 }
4655 
4656 template <typename Derived>
4657 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTemplateArgument(
4658  const TemplateArgumentLoc &Input, TemplateArgumentLoc &Output,
4659  bool Uneval) {
4660  const TemplateArgument &Arg = Input.getArgument();
4661  switch (Arg.getKind()) {
4662  case TemplateArgument::Null:
4663  case TemplateArgument::Pack:
4664  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected TemplateArgument");
4665 
4666  case TemplateArgument::Integral:
4667  case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
4668  case TemplateArgument::Declaration:
4669  case TemplateArgument::StructuralValue: {
4670  // Transform a resolved template argument straight to a resolved template
4671  // argument. We get here when substituting into an already-substituted
4672  // template type argument during concept satisfaction checking.
4673  QualType T = Arg.getNonTypeTemplateArgumentType();
4674  QualType NewT = getDerived().TransformType(T);
4675  if (NewT.isNull())
4676  return true;
4677 
4678  ValueDecl *D = Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Declaration
4679  ? Arg.getAsDecl()
4680  : nullptr;
4681  ValueDecl *NewD = D ? cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
4682  getDerived().getBaseLocation(), D))
4683  : nullptr;
4684  if (D && !NewD)
4685  return true;
4686 
4687  if (NewT == T && D == NewD)
4688  Output = Input;
4689  else if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Integral)
4690  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(
4691  TemplateArgument(getSema().Context, Arg.getAsIntegral(), NewT),
4692  TemplateArgumentLocInfo());
4693  else if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::NullPtr)
4694  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(TemplateArgument(NewT, /*IsNullPtr=*/true),
4695  TemplateArgumentLocInfo());
4696  else if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Declaration)
4697  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(TemplateArgument(NewD, NewT),
4698  TemplateArgumentLocInfo());
4699  else if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::StructuralValue)
4700  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(
4701  TemplateArgument(getSema().Context, NewT, Arg.getAsStructuralValue()),
4702  TemplateArgumentLocInfo());
4703  else
4704  llvm_unreachable("unexpected template argument kind");
4705 
4706  return false;
4707  }
4708 
4709  case TemplateArgument::Type: {
4710  TypeSourceInfo *DI = Input.getTypeSourceInfo();
4711  if (!DI)
4712  DI = InventTypeSourceInfo(Input.getArgument().getAsType());
4713 
4714  DI = getDerived().TransformType(DI);
4715  if (!DI)
4716  return true;
4717 
4718  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(TemplateArgument(DI->getType()), DI);
4719  return false;
4720  }
4721 
4722  case TemplateArgument::Template: {
4723  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = Input.getTemplateQualifierLoc();
4724  if (QualifierLoc) {
4725  QualifierLoc = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
4726  if (!QualifierLoc)
4727  return true;
4728  }
4729 
4730  CXXScopeSpec SS;
4731  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
4732  TemplateName Template = getDerived().TransformTemplateName(
4733  SS, Arg.getAsTemplate(), Input.getTemplateNameLoc());
4734  if (Template.isNull())
4735  return true;
4736 
4737  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(SemaRef.Context, TemplateArgument(Template),
4738  QualifierLoc, Input.getTemplateNameLoc());
4739  return false;
4740  }
4741 
4742  case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
4743  llvm_unreachable("Caller should expand pack expansions");
4744 
4745  case TemplateArgument::Expression: {
4746  // Template argument expressions are constant expressions.
4747  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
4748  getSema(),
4749  Uneval ? Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated
4750  : Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated,
4751  Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl, /*ExprContext=*/
4752  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_TemplateArgument);
4753 
4754  Expr *InputExpr = Input.getSourceExpression();
4755  if (!InputExpr)
4756  InputExpr = Input.getArgument().getAsExpr();
4757 
4758  ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(InputExpr);
4759  E = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(E);
4760  if (E.isInvalid())
4761  return true;
4762  Output = TemplateArgumentLoc(TemplateArgument(E.get()), E.get());
4763  return false;
4764  }
4765  }
4766 
4767  // Work around bogus GCC warning
4768  return true;
4769 }

4771 /// Iterator adaptor that invents template argument location information
4772 /// for each of the template arguments in its underlying iterator.
4773 template<typename Derived, typename InputIterator>
4774 class TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator {
4775  TreeTransform<Derived> &Self;
4776  InputIterator Iter;
4777 
4778 public:
4779  typedef TemplateArgumentLoc value_type;
4780  typedef TemplateArgumentLoc reference;
4781  typedef typename std::iterator_traits<InputIterator>::difference_type
4782  difference_type;
4783  typedef std::input_iterator_tag iterator_category;
4784 
4785  class pointer {
4786  TemplateArgumentLoc Arg;
4787 
4788  public:
4789  explicit pointer(TemplateArgumentLoc Arg) : Arg(Arg) { }
4790 
4791  const TemplateArgumentLoc *operator->() const { return &Arg; }
4792  };
4793 
4794  explicit TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator(TreeTransform<Derived> &Self,
4795  InputIterator Iter)
4796  : Self(Self), Iter(Iter) { }
4797 
4798  TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator &operator++() {
4799  ++Iter;
4800  return *this;
4801  }
4802 
4803  TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator operator++(int) {
4804  TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator Old(*this);
4805  ++(*this);
4806  return Old;
4807  }
4808 
4809  reference operator*() const {
4810  TemplateArgumentLoc Result;
4811  Self.InventTemplateArgumentLoc(*Iter, Result);
4812  return Result;
4813  }
4814 
4815  pointer operator->() const { return pointer(**this); }
4816 
4817  friend bool operator==(const TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator &X,
4818  const TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator &Y) {
4819  return X.Iter == Y.Iter;
4820  }
4821 
4822  friend bool operator!=(const TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator &X,
4823  const TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator &Y) {
4824  return X.Iter != Y.Iter;
4825  }
4826 };
4827 
4828 template<typename Derived>
4829 template<typename InputIterator>
4830 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTemplateArguments(
4831  InputIterator First, InputIterator Last, TemplateArgumentListInfo &Outputs,
4832  bool Uneval) {
4833  for (; First != Last; ++First) {
4834  TemplateArgumentLoc Out;
4835  TemplateArgumentLoc In = *First;
4836 
4837  if (In.getArgument().getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack) {
4838  // When building the deduction guides, we rewrite the argument packs
4839  // instead of unpacking.
4840  if (getSema().CodeSynthesisContexts.back().Kind ==
4841  Sema::CodeSynthesisContext::BuildingDeductionGuides) {
4842  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(In, Out, Uneval))
4843  return true;
4844  continue;
4845  }
4846  // Unpack argument packs, which we translate them into separate
4847  // arguments.
4848  // FIXME: We could do much better if we could guarantee that the
4849  // TemplateArgumentLocInfo for the pack expansion would be usable for
4850  // all of the template arguments in the argument pack.
4851  typedef TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator<Derived,
4852  TemplateArgument::pack_iterator>
4853  PackLocIterator;
4854  if (TransformTemplateArguments(PackLocIterator(*this,
4855  In.getArgument().pack_begin()),
4856  PackLocIterator(*this,
4857  In.getArgument().pack_end()),
4858  Outputs, Uneval))
4859  return true;
4860 
4861  continue;
4862  }
4863 
4864  if (In.getArgument().isPackExpansion()) {
4865  // We have a pack expansion, for which we will be substituting into
4866  // the pattern.
4867  SourceLocation Ellipsis;
4868  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions;
4869  TemplateArgumentLoc Pattern
4870  = getSema().getTemplateArgumentPackExpansionPattern(
4871  In, Ellipsis, OrigNumExpansions);
4872 
4873  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
4874  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
4875  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
4876 
4877  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
4878  // be expanded.
4879  bool Expand = true;
4880  bool RetainExpansion = false;
4881  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
4882  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(Ellipsis,
4883  Pattern.getSourceRange(),
4884  Unexpanded,
4885  Expand,
4886  RetainExpansion,
4887  NumExpansions))
4888  return true;
4889 
4890  if (!Expand) {
4891  // The transform has determined that we should perform a simple
4892  // transformation on the pack expansion, producing another pack
4893  // expansion.
4894  TemplateArgumentLoc OutPattern;
4895  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
4896  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(Pattern, OutPattern, Uneval))
4897  return true;
4898 
4899  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(OutPattern, Ellipsis,
4900  NumExpansions);
4901  if (Out.getArgument().isNull())
4902  return true;
4903 
4904  Outputs.addArgument(Out);
4905  continue;
4906  }
4907 
4908  // The transform has determined that we should perform an elementwise
4909  // expansion of the pattern. Do so.
4910  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
4911  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
4912 
4913  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(Pattern, Out, Uneval))
4914  return true;
4915 
4916  if (Out.getArgument().containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
4917  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(Out, Ellipsis,
4918  OrigNumExpansions);
4919  if (Out.getArgument().isNull())
4920  return true;
4921  }
4922 
4923  Outputs.addArgument(Out);
4924  }
4925 
4926  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
4927  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
4928  if (RetainExpansion) {
4929  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
4930 
4931  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(Pattern, Out, Uneval))
4932  return true;
4933 
4934  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(Out, Ellipsis,
4935  OrigNumExpansions);
4936  if (Out.getArgument().isNull())
4937  return true;
4938 
4939  Outputs.addArgument(Out);
4940  }
4941 
4942  continue;
4943  }
4944 
4945  // The simple case:
4946  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(In, Out, Uneval))
4947  return true;
4948 
4949  Outputs.addArgument(Out);
4950  }
4951 
4952  return false;
4953 
4954 }
4955 
4956 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
4957 // Type transformation
4958 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

4960 template<typename Derived>
4961 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformType(QualType T) {
4962  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(T))
4963  return T;
4964 
4965  // Temporary workaround. All of these transformations should
4966  // eventually turn into transformations on TypeLocs.
4967  TypeSourceInfo *DI = getSema().Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T,
4968  getDerived().getBaseLocation());
4969 
4970  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI = getDerived().TransformType(DI);
4971 
4972  if (!NewDI)
4973  return QualType();
4974 
4975  return NewDI->getType();
4976 }
4977 
4978 template<typename Derived>
4979 TypeSourceInfo *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformType(TypeSourceInfo *DI) {
4980  // Refine the base location to the type's location.
4981  TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, DI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
4982  getDerived().getBaseEntity());
4983  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(DI->getType()))
4984  return DI;
4985 
4986  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
4987 
4988  TypeLoc TL = DI->getTypeLoc();
4989  TLB.reserve(TL.getFullDataSize());
4990 
4991  QualType Result = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL);
4992  if (Result.isNull())
4993  return nullptr;
4994 
4995  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, Result);
4996 }
4997 
4998 template<typename Derived>
4999 QualType
5000 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB, TypeLoc T) {
5001  switch (T.getTypeLocClass()) {
5002 #define ABSTRACT_TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT)
5003 #define TYPELOC(CLASS, PARENT) \
5004  case TypeLoc::CLASS: \
5005  return getDerived().Transform##CLASS##Type(TLB, \
5006  T.castAs<CLASS##TypeLoc>());
5007 #include "clang/AST/TypeLocNodes.def"
5008  }
5009 
5010  llvm_unreachable("unhandled type loc!");
5011 }
