5013 template<typename Derived>
5014 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(QualType T) {
5015  if (!isa<DependentNameType>(T))
5016  return TransformType(T);
5017 
5018  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(T))
5019  return T;
5020  TypeSourceInfo *DI = getSema().Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T,
5021  getDerived().getBaseLocation());
5022  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI = getDerived().TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(DI);
5023  return NewDI ? NewDI->getType() : QualType();
5024 }
5025 
5026 template<typename Derived>
5027 TypeSourceInfo *
5028 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(TypeSourceInfo *DI) {
5029  if (!isa<DependentNameType>(DI->getType()))
5030  return TransformType(DI);
5031 
5032  // Refine the base location to the type's location.
5033  TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, DI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
5034  getDerived().getBaseEntity());
5035  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(DI->getType()))
5036  return DI;
5037 
5038  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
5039 
5040  TypeLoc TL = DI->getTypeLoc();
5041  TLB.reserve(TL.getFullDataSize());
5042 
5043  auto QTL = TL.getAs<QualifiedTypeLoc>();
5044  if (QTL)
5045  TL = QTL.getUnqualifiedLoc();
5046 
5047  auto DNTL = TL.castAs<DependentNameTypeLoc>();
5048 
5049  QualType Result = getDerived().TransformDependentNameType(
5050  TLB, DNTL, /*DeducedTSTContext*/true);
5051  if (Result.isNull())
5052  return nullptr;
5053 
5054  if (QTL) {
5055  Result = getDerived().RebuildQualifiedType(Result, QTL);
5056  if (Result.isNull())
5057  return nullptr;
5058  TLB.TypeWasModifiedSafely(Result);
5059  }
5060 
5061  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, Result);
5062 }
5063 
5064 template<typename Derived>
5065 QualType
5066 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformQualifiedType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5067  QualifiedTypeLoc T) {
5068  QualType Result;
5069  TypeLoc UnqualTL = T.getUnqualifiedLoc();
5070  auto SuppressObjCLifetime =
5071  T.getType().getLocalQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime();
5072  if (auto TTP = UnqualTL.getAs<TemplateTypeParmTypeLoc>()) {
5073  Result = getDerived().TransformTemplateTypeParmType(TLB, TTP,
5074  SuppressObjCLifetime);
5075  } else if (auto STTP = UnqualTL.getAs<SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypeLoc>()) {
5076  Result = getDerived().TransformSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
5077  TLB, STTP, SuppressObjCLifetime);
5078  } else {
5079  Result = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, UnqualTL);
5080  }
5081 
5082  if (Result.isNull())
5083  return QualType();
5084 
5085  Result = getDerived().RebuildQualifiedType(Result, T);
5086 
5087  if (Result.isNull())
5088  return QualType();
5089 
5090  // RebuildQualifiedType might have updated the type, but not in a way
5091  // that invalidates the TypeLoc. (There's no location information for
5092  // qualifiers.)
5093  TLB.TypeWasModifiedSafely(Result);
5094 
5095  return Result;
5096 }
5097 
5098 template <typename Derived>
5099 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildQualifiedType(QualType T,
5100  QualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5101 
5102  SourceLocation Loc = TL.getBeginLoc();
5103  Qualifiers Quals = TL.getType().getLocalQualifiers();
5104 
5105  if ((T.getAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default &&
5106  Quals.getAddressSpace() != LangAS::Default) &&
5107  T.getAddressSpace() != Quals.getAddressSpace()) {
5108  SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_address_space_mismatch_templ_inst)
5109  << TL.getType() << T;
5110  return QualType();
5111  }
5112 
5113  // C++ [dcl.fct]p7:
5114  // [When] adding cv-qualifications on top of the function type [...] the
5115  // cv-qualifiers are ignored.
5116  if (T->isFunctionType()) {
5117  T = SemaRef.getASTContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(T,
5118  Quals.getAddressSpace());
5119  return T;
5120  }
5121 
5122  // C++ [dcl.ref]p1:
5123  // when the cv-qualifiers are introduced through the use of a typedef-name
5124  // or decltype-specifier [...] the cv-qualifiers are ignored.
5125  // Note that [dcl.ref]p1 lists all cases in which cv-qualifiers can be
5126  // applied to a reference type.
5127  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
5128  // The only qualifier that applies to a reference type is restrict.
5129  if (!Quals.hasRestrict())
5130  return T;
5131  Quals = Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(Qualifiers::Restrict);
5132  }
5133 
5134  // Suppress Objective-C lifetime qualifiers if they don't make sense for the
5135  // resulting type.
5136  if (Quals.hasObjCLifetime()) {
5137  if (!T->isObjCLifetimeType() && !T->isDependentType())
5138  Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
5139  else if (T.getObjCLifetime()) {
5140  // Objective-C ARC:
5141  // A lifetime qualifier applied to a substituted template parameter
5142  // overrides the lifetime qualifier from the template argument.
5143  const AutoType *AutoTy;
5144  if ((AutoTy = dyn_cast<AutoType>(T)) && AutoTy->isDeduced()) {
5145  // 'auto' types behave the same way as template parameters.
5146  QualType Deduced = AutoTy->getDeducedType();
5147  Qualifiers Qs = Deduced.getQualifiers();
5148  Qs.removeObjCLifetime();
5149  Deduced =
5150  SemaRef.Context.getQualifiedType(Deduced.getUnqualifiedType(), Qs);
5151  T = SemaRef.Context.getAutoType(Deduced, AutoTy->getKeyword(),
5152  AutoTy->isDependentType(),
5153  /*isPack=*/false,
5154  AutoTy->getTypeConstraintConcept(),
5155  AutoTy->getTypeConstraintArguments());
5156  } else {
5157  // Otherwise, complain about the addition of a qualifier to an
5158  // already-qualified type.
5159  // FIXME: Why is this check not in Sema::BuildQualifiedType?
5160  SemaRef.Diag(Loc, diag::err_attr_objc_ownership_redundant) << T;
5161  Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
5162  }
5163  }
5164  }
5165 
5166  return SemaRef.BuildQualifiedType(T, Loc, Quals);
5167 }
5168

5170 TypeLoc
5171 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeInObjectScope(TypeLoc TL,
5172  QualType ObjectType,
5173  NamedDecl *UnqualLookup,
5174  CXXScopeSpec &SS) {
5175  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(TL.getType()))
5176  return TL;
5177 
5178  TypeSourceInfo *TSI =
5179  TransformTSIInObjectScope(TL, ObjectType, UnqualLookup, SS);
5180  if (TSI)
5181  return TSI->getTypeLoc();
5182  return TypeLoc();
5183 }

5187 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeInObjectScope(TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo,
5188  QualType ObjectType,
5189  NamedDecl *UnqualLookup,
5190  CXXScopeSpec &SS) {
5191  if (getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(TSInfo->getType()))

5197 
5198 template <typename Derived>
5199 TypeSourceInfo *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTSIInObjectScope(
5200  TypeLoc TL, QualType ObjectType, NamedDecl *UnqualLookup,
5201  CXXScopeSpec &SS) {
5202  QualType T = TL.getType();
5203  assert(!getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(T));
5204 
5205  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
5206  QualType Result;
5207 
5208  if (isa<TemplateSpecializationType>(T)) {
5209  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc SpecTL =
5210  TL.castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
5211 
5212  TemplateName Template = getDerived().TransformTemplateName(
5213  SS, SpecTL.getTypePtr()->getTemplateName(), SpecTL.getTemplateNameLoc(),
5214  ObjectType, UnqualLookup, /*AllowInjectedClassName*/true);
5215  if (Template.isNull())
5216  return nullptr;
5217 
5218  Result = getDerived().TransformTemplateSpecializationType(TLB, SpecTL,
5219  Template);
5220  } else if (isa<DependentTemplateSpecializationType>(T)) {
5221  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc SpecTL =
5222  TL.castAs<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
5223 
5224  TemplateName Template
5225  = getDerived().RebuildTemplateName(SS,
5226  SpecTL.getTemplateKeywordLoc(),
5227  *SpecTL.getTypePtr()->getIdentifier(),
5228  SpecTL.getTemplateNameLoc(),
5229  ObjectType, UnqualLookup,
5230  /*AllowInjectedClassName*/true);
5231  if (Template.isNull())
5232  return nullptr;
5233 
5234  Result = getDerived().TransformDependentTemplateSpecializationType(TLB,
5235  SpecTL,
5236  Template,
5237  SS);
5238  } else {
5239  // Nothing special needs to be done for these.
5240  Result = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL);
5241  }
5242 
5243  if (Result.isNull())
5244  return nullptr;
5245 
5246  return TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, Result);
5247 }

5313 template<typename Derived>
5314 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPointerType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5315  PointerTypeLoc TL) {
5316  QualType PointeeType
5317  = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPointeeLoc());
5318  if (PointeeType.isNull())
5319  return QualType();
5320 
5321  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5322  if (PointeeType->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()) {
5323  // A dependent pointer type 'T *' has is being transformed such
5324  // that an Objective-C class type is being replaced for 'T'. The
5325  // resulting pointer type is an ObjCObjectPointerType, not a
5326  // PointerType.
5327  Result = SemaRef.Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(PointeeType);
5328 
5329  ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc NewT = TLB.push<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>(Result);
5330  NewT.setStarLoc(TL.getStarLoc());
5331  return Result;
5332  }
5333 
5334  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5335  PointeeType != TL.getPointeeLoc().getType()) {
5336  Result = getDerived().RebuildPointerType(PointeeType, TL.getSigilLoc());
5337  if (Result.isNull())
5338  return QualType();
5339  }
5340 
5341  // Objective-C ARC can add lifetime qualifiers to the type that we're
5342  // pointing to.
5343  TLB.TypeWasModifiedSafely(Result->getPointeeType());
5344 
5345  PointerTypeLoc NewT = TLB.push<PointerTypeLoc>(Result);
5346  NewT.setSigilLoc(TL.getSigilLoc());
5347  return Result;
5348 }

5373 /// Transforms a reference type. Note that somewhat paradoxically we
5374 /// don't care whether the type itself is an l-value type or an r-value
5375 /// type; we only care if the type was *written* as an l-value type
5376 /// or an r-value type.
5377 template<typename Derived>
5378 QualType
5379 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformReferenceType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5380  ReferenceTypeLoc TL) {
5381  const ReferenceType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5382 
5383  // Note that this works with the pointee-as-written.
5384  QualType PointeeType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPointeeLoc());
5385  if (PointeeType.isNull())
5386  return QualType();
5387 
5388  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5389  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5390  PointeeType != T->getPointeeTypeAsWritten()) {
5391  Result = getDerived().RebuildReferenceType(PointeeType,
5392  T->isSpelledAsLValue(),
5393  TL.getSigilLoc());
5394  if (Result.isNull())
5395  return QualType();
5396  }
5397 
5398  // Objective-C ARC can add lifetime qualifiers to the type that we're
5399  // referring to.
5400  TLB.TypeWasModifiedSafely(
5401  Result->castAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeTypeAsWritten());
5402 
5403  // r-value references can be rebuilt as l-value references.
5404  ReferenceTypeLoc NewTL;
5405  if (isa<LValueReferenceType>(Result))
5406  NewTL = TLB.push<LValueReferenceTypeLoc>(Result);
5407  else
5408  NewTL = TLB.push<RValueReferenceTypeLoc>(Result);
5409  NewTL.setSigilLoc(TL.getSigilLoc());
5410 
5411  return Result;
5412 }

5419 }

5428 template<typename Derived>
5429 QualType
5430 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMemberPointerType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5431  MemberPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5432  QualType PointeeType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPointeeLoc());
5433  if (PointeeType.isNull())
5434  return QualType();
5435 
5436  TypeSourceInfo* OldClsTInfo = TL.getClassTInfo();
5437  TypeSourceInfo *NewClsTInfo = nullptr;
5438  if (OldClsTInfo) {
5439  NewClsTInfo = getDerived().TransformType(OldClsTInfo);
5440  if (!NewClsTInfo)
5441  return QualType();
5442  }
5443 
5444  const MemberPointerType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5445  QualType OldClsType = QualType(T->getClass(), 0);
5446  QualType NewClsType;
5447  if (NewClsTInfo)
5448  NewClsType = NewClsTInfo->getType();
5449  else {
5450  NewClsType = getDerived().TransformType(OldClsType);
5451  if (NewClsType.isNull())
5452  return QualType();
5453  }
5454 
5455  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5456  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5457  PointeeType != T->getPointeeType() ||
5458  NewClsType != OldClsType) {
5459  Result = getDerived().RebuildMemberPointerType(PointeeType, NewClsType,
5460  TL.getStarLoc());
5461  if (Result.isNull())
5462  return QualType();
5463  }
5464 
5465  // If we had to adjust the pointee type when building a member pointer, make
5466  // sure to push TypeLoc info for it.
5467  const MemberPointerType *MPT = Result->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
5468  if (MPT && PointeeType != MPT->getPointeeType()) {
5469  assert(isa<AdjustedType>(MPT->getPointeeType()));
5470  TLB.push<AdjustedTypeLoc>(MPT->getPointeeType());
5471  }
5472 
5473  MemberPointerTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<MemberPointerTypeLoc>(Result);
5474  NewTL.setSigilLoc(TL.getSigilLoc());
5475  NewTL.setClassTInfo(NewClsTInfo);
5476 
5477  return Result;
5478 }
5479 
5480 template<typename Derived>
5481 QualType
5482 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformConstantArrayType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5483  ConstantArrayTypeLoc TL) {
5484  const ConstantArrayType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5485  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getElementLoc());
5486  if (ElementType.isNull())
5487  return QualType();
5488 
5489  // Prefer the expression from the TypeLoc; the other may have been uniqued.
5490  Expr *OldSize = TL.getSizeExpr();
5491  if (!OldSize)
5492  OldSize = const_cast<Expr*>(T->getSizeExpr());
5493  Expr *NewSize = nullptr;
5494  if (OldSize) {
5495  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5496  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
5497  NewSize = getDerived().TransformExpr(OldSize).template getAs<Expr>();
5498  NewSize = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(NewSize).get();
5499  }
5500 
5501  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5502  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5503  ElementType != T->getElementType() ||
5504  (T->getSizeExpr() && NewSize != OldSize)) {
5505  Result = getDerived().RebuildConstantArrayType(ElementType,
5506  T->getSizeModifier(),
5507  T->getSize(), NewSize,
5508  T->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5509  TL.getBracketsRange());
5510  if (Result.isNull())
5511  return QualType();
5512  }
5513 
5514  // We might have either a ConstantArrayType or a VariableArrayType now:
5515  // a ConstantArrayType is allowed to have an element type which is a
5516  // VariableArrayType if the type is dependent. Fortunately, all array
5517  // types have the same location layout.
5518  ArrayTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ArrayTypeLoc>(Result);
5519  NewTL.setLBracketLoc(TL.getLBracketLoc());
5520  NewTL.setRBracketLoc(TL.getRBracketLoc());
5521  NewTL.setSizeExpr(NewSize);
5522 
5523  return Result;
5524 }

5526 template<typename Derived>
5527 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformIncompleteArrayType(
5528  TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5529  IncompleteArrayTypeLoc TL) {
5530  const IncompleteArrayType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5531  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getElementLoc());
5532  if (ElementType.isNull())
5533  return QualType();
5534 
5535  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5536  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5537  ElementType != T->getElementType()) {
5538  Result = getDerived().RebuildIncompleteArrayType(ElementType,
5539  T->getSizeModifier(),
5540  T->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5541  TL.getBracketsRange());
5542  if (Result.isNull())
5543  return QualType();
5544  }
5545 
5546  IncompleteArrayTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<IncompleteArrayTypeLoc>(Result);
5547  NewTL.setLBracketLoc(TL.getLBracketLoc());
5548  NewTL.setRBracketLoc(TL.getRBracketLoc());
5549  NewTL.setSizeExpr(nullptr);
5550 
5551  return Result;
5552 }

5554 template<typename Derived>
5555 QualType
5556 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformVariableArrayType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5557  VariableArrayTypeLoc TL) {
5558  const VariableArrayType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5559  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getElementLoc());
5560  if (ElementType.isNull())
5561  return QualType();
5562 
5563  ExprResult SizeResult;
5564  {
5565  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
5566  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
5567  SizeResult = getDerived().TransformExpr(T->getSizeExpr());
5568  }
5569  if (SizeResult.isInvalid())
5570  return QualType();
5571  SizeResult =
5572  SemaRef.ActOnFinishFullExpr(SizeResult.get(), /*DiscardedValue*/ false);
5573  if (SizeResult.isInvalid())
5574  return QualType();
5575 
5576  Expr *Size = SizeResult.get();
5577 
5578  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5579  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5580  ElementType != T->getElementType() ||
5581  Size != T->getSizeExpr()) {
5582  Result = getDerived().RebuildVariableArrayType(ElementType,
5583  T->getSizeModifier(),
5584  Size,
5585  T->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5586  TL.getBracketsRange());
5587  if (Result.isNull())
5588  return QualType();
5589  }
5590 
5591  // We might have constant size array now, but fortunately it has the same
5592  // location layout.
5593  ArrayTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ArrayTypeLoc>(Result);
5594  NewTL.setLBracketLoc(TL.getLBracketLoc());
5595  NewTL.setRBracketLoc(TL.getRBracketLoc());
5596  NewTL.setSizeExpr(Size);
5597 
5598  return Result;
5599 }

5601 template<typename Derived>
5602 QualType
5603 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentSizedArrayType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
5604  DependentSizedArrayTypeLoc TL) {
5605  const DependentSizedArrayType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5606  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getElementLoc());
5607  if (ElementType.isNull())
5608  return QualType();
5609 
5610  // Array bounds are constant expressions.
5611  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5612  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
5613 
5614  // If we have a VLA then it won't be a constant.
5615  SemaRef.ExprEvalContexts.back().InConditionallyConstantEvaluateContext = true;
5616 
5617  // Prefer the expression from the TypeLoc; the other may have been uniqued.
5618  Expr *origSize = TL.getSizeExpr();
5619  if (!origSize) origSize = T->getSizeExpr();
5620 
5621  ExprResult sizeResult
5622  = getDerived().TransformExpr(origSize);
5623  sizeResult = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(sizeResult);
5624  if (sizeResult.isInvalid())
5625  return QualType();
5626 
5627  Expr *size = sizeResult.get();
5628 
5629  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5630  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
5631  ElementType != T->getElementType() ||
5632  size != origSize) {
5633  Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentSizedArrayType(ElementType,
5634  T->getSizeModifier(),
5635  size,
5636  T->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5637  TL.getBracketsRange());
5638  if (Result.isNull())
5639  return QualType();
5640  }
5641 
5642  // We might have any sort of array type now, but fortunately they
5643  // all have the same location layout.
5644  ArrayTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ArrayTypeLoc>(Result);
5645  NewTL.setLBracketLoc(TL.getLBracketLoc());
5646  NewTL.setRBracketLoc(TL.getRBracketLoc());
5647  NewTL.setSizeExpr(size);
5648 
5649  return Result;
5650 }

5652 template <typename Derived>
5653 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentVectorType(
5654  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, DependentVectorTypeLoc TL) {
5655  const DependentVectorType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5656  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getElementLoc());
5657  if (ElementType.isNull())
5658  return QualType();
5659 
5660  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5661  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
5662 
5663  ExprResult Size = getDerived().TransformExpr(T->getSizeExpr());
5664  Size = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(Size);
5665  if (Size.isInvalid())
5666  return QualType();
5667 
5668  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5669  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || ElementType != T->getElementType() ||
5670  Size.get() != T->getSizeExpr()) {
5671  Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentVectorType(
5672  ElementType, Size.get(), T->getAttributeLoc(), T->getVectorKind());
5673  if (Result.isNull())

5682  } else {
5683  VectorTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<VectorTypeLoc>(Result);
5684  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
5685  }
5686 
5687  return Result;
5688 }

5760 template <typename Derived>
5761 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentSizedMatrixType(
5762  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, DependentSizedMatrixTypeLoc TL) {
5763  const DependentSizedMatrixType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5764 
5765  QualType ElementType = getDerived().TransformType(T->getElementType());
5766  if (ElementType.isNull()) {
5767  return QualType();
5768  }
5769 
5770  // Matrix dimensions are constant expressions.
5771  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5772  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
5773 
5774  Expr *origRows = TL.getAttrRowOperand();
5775  if (!origRows)
5776  origRows = T->getRowExpr();
5777  Expr *origColumns = TL.getAttrColumnOperand();
5778  if (!origColumns)
5779  origColumns = T->getColumnExpr();
5780 
5781  ExprResult rowResult = getDerived().TransformExpr(origRows);
5782  rowResult = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(rowResult);
5783  if (rowResult.isInvalid())
5784  return QualType();
5785 
5786  ExprResult columnResult = getDerived().TransformExpr(origColumns);
5787  columnResult = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(columnResult);
5788  if (columnResult.isInvalid())
5789  return QualType();
5790 
5791  Expr *rows = rowResult.get();
5792  Expr *columns = columnResult.get();
5793 
5794  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5795  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || ElementType != T->getElementType() ||
5796  rows != origRows || columns != origColumns) {
5797  Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentSizedMatrixType(
5798  ElementType, rows, columns, T->getAttributeLoc());
5799 
5800  if (Result.isNull())
5801  return QualType();
5802  }
5803 
5804  // We might have any sort of matrix type now, but fortunately they
5805  // all have the same location layout.
5806  MatrixTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<MatrixTypeLoc>(Result);
5807  NewTL.setAttrNameLoc(TL.getAttrNameLoc());
5808  NewTL.setAttrOperandParensRange(TL.getAttrOperandParensRange());
5809  NewTL.setAttrRowOperand(rows);
5810  NewTL.setAttrColumnOperand(columns);
5811  return Result;
5812 }

5814 template <typename Derived>
5815 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentAddressSpaceType(
5816  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc TL) {
5817  const DependentAddressSpaceType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5818 
5819  QualType pointeeType = getDerived().TransformType(T->getPointeeType());
5820 
5821  if (pointeeType.isNull())
5822  return QualType();
5823 
5824  // Address spaces are constant expressions.
5825  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
5826  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
5827 
5828  ExprResult AddrSpace = getDerived().TransformExpr(T->getAddrSpaceExpr());
5829  AddrSpace = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(AddrSpace);
5830  if (AddrSpace.isInvalid())
5831  return QualType();
5832 
5833  QualType Result = TL.getType();
5834  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || pointeeType != T->getPointeeType() ||
5835  AddrSpace.get() != T->getAddrSpaceExpr()) {
5836  Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentAddressSpaceType(
5837  pointeeType, AddrSpace.get(), T->getAttributeLoc());
5838  if (Result.isNull())
5839  return QualType();
5840  }
5841 
5842  // Result might be dependent or not.
5843  if (isa<DependentAddressSpaceType>(Result)) {
5844  DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc NewTL =
5845  TLB.push<DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc>(Result);
5846 
5847  NewTL.setAttrOperandParensRange(TL.getAttrOperandParensRange());
5848  NewTL.setAttrExprOperand(TL.getAttrExprOperand());
5849  NewTL.setAttrNameLoc(TL.getAttrNameLoc());
5850 
5851  } else {
5852  TypeSourceInfo *DI = getSema().Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(
5853  Result, getDerived().getBaseLocation());
5854  TransformType(TLB, DI->getTypeLoc());
5855  }
5856 
5857  return Result;
5858 }

5906 
5907 template <typename Derived>
5908 ParmVarDecl *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformFunctionTypeParam(
5909  ParmVarDecl *OldParm, int indexAdjustment,
5910  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions, bool ExpectParameterPack) {
5911  TypeSourceInfo *OldDI = OldParm->getTypeSourceInfo();
5912  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI = nullptr;
5913 
5914  if (NumExpansions && isa<PackExpansionType>(OldDI->getType())) {
5915  // If we're substituting into a pack expansion type and we know the
5916  // length we want to expand to, just substitute for the pattern.
5917  TypeLoc OldTL = OldDI->getTypeLoc();
5918  PackExpansionTypeLoc OldExpansionTL = OldTL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>();
5919 
5920  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
5921  TypeLoc NewTL = OldDI->getTypeLoc();
5922  TLB.reserve(NewTL.getFullDataSize());
5923 
5924  QualType Result = getDerived().TransformType(TLB,
5925  OldExpansionTL.getPatternLoc());
5926  if (Result.isNull())
5927  return nullptr;
5928 
5929  Result = RebuildPackExpansionType(Result,
5930  OldExpansionTL.getPatternLoc().getSourceRange(),
5931  OldExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
5932  NumExpansions);
5933  if (Result.isNull())
5934  return nullptr;
5935 
5936  PackExpansionTypeLoc NewExpansionTL
5937  = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(Result);
5938  NewExpansionTL.setEllipsisLoc(OldExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc());
5939  NewDI = TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, Result);
5940  } else
5941  NewDI = getDerived().TransformType(OldDI);
5942  if (!NewDI)
5943  return nullptr;
5944 
5945  if (NewDI == OldDI && indexAdjustment == 0)
5946  return OldParm;
5947 
5948  ParmVarDecl *newParm = ParmVarDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context,
5949  OldParm->getDeclContext(),
5950  OldParm->getInnerLocStart(),
5951  OldParm->getLocation(),
5952  OldParm->getIdentifier(),
5953  NewDI->getType(),
5954  NewDI,
5955  OldParm->getStorageClass(),
5956  /* DefArg */ nullptr);
5957  newParm->setScopeInfo(OldParm->getFunctionScopeDepth(),
5958  OldParm->getFunctionScopeIndex() + indexAdjustment);
5959  transformedLocalDecl(OldParm, {newParm});
5960  return newParm;
5961 }
5962 
5963 template <typename Derived>
5964 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformFunctionTypeParams(
5965  SourceLocation Loc, ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params,
5966  const QualType *ParamTypes,
5967  const FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo *ParamInfos,
5968  SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &OutParamTypes,
5969  SmallVectorImpl<ParmVarDecl *> *PVars,
5970  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder &PInfos,
5971  unsigned *LastParamTransformed) {
5972  int indexAdjustment = 0;
5973 
5974  unsigned NumParams = Params.size();
5975  for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumParams; ++i) {
5976  if (LastParamTransformed)
5977  *LastParamTransformed = i;
5978  if (ParmVarDecl *OldParm = Params[i]) {
5979  assert(OldParm->getFunctionScopeIndex() == i);
5980 
5981  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
5982  ParmVarDecl *NewParm = nullptr;
5983  if (OldParm->isParameterPack()) {
5984  // We have a function parameter pack that may need to be expanded.
5985  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
5986 
5987  // Find the parameter packs that could be expanded.
5988  TypeLoc TL = OldParm->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc();
5989  PackExpansionTypeLoc ExpansionTL = TL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>();
5990  TypeLoc Pattern = ExpansionTL.getPatternLoc();
5991  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
5992 
5993  // Determine whether we should expand the parameter packs.
5994  bool ShouldExpand = false;
5995  bool RetainExpansion = false;
5996  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions;
5997  if (Unexpanded.size() > 0) {
5998  OrigNumExpansions = ExpansionTL.getTypePtr()->getNumExpansions();
5999  NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
6000  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
6001  Pattern.getSourceRange(),
6002  Unexpanded,
6003  ShouldExpand,
6004  RetainExpansion,
6005  NumExpansions)) {
6006  return true;
6007  }
6008  } else {
6009 #ifndef NDEBUG
6010  const AutoType *AT =
6011  Pattern.getType().getTypePtr()->getContainedAutoType();
6012  assert((AT && (!AT->isDeduced() || AT->getDeducedType().isNull())) &&
6013  "Could not find parameter packs or undeduced auto type!");
6014 #endif
6015  }
6016 
6017  if (ShouldExpand) {
6018  // Expand the function parameter pack into multiple, separate
6019  // parameters.
6020  getDerived().ExpandingFunctionParameterPack(OldParm);
6021  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
6022  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
6023  ParmVarDecl *NewParm
6024  = getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParam(OldParm,
6025  indexAdjustment++,
6026  OrigNumExpansions,
6027  /*ExpectParameterPack=*/false);
6028  if (!NewParm)
6029  return true;
6030 
6031  if (ParamInfos)
6032  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6033  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewParm->getType());
6034  if (PVars)
6035  PVars->push_back(NewParm);
6036  }
6037 
6038  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
6039  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
6040  if (RetainExpansion) {
6041  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
6042  ParmVarDecl *NewParm
6043  = getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParam(OldParm,
6044  indexAdjustment++,
6045  OrigNumExpansions,
6046  /*ExpectParameterPack=*/false);
6047  if (!NewParm)
6048  return true;
6049 
6050  if (ParamInfos)
6051  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6052  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewParm->getType());
6053  if (PVars)
6054  PVars->push_back(NewParm);
6055  }
6056 
6057  // The next parameter should have the same adjustment as the
6058  // last thing we pushed, but we post-incremented indexAdjustment
6059  // on every push. Also, if we push nothing, the adjustment should
6060  // go down by one.
6061  indexAdjustment--;
6062 
6063  // We're done with the pack expansion.
6064  continue;
6065  }
6066 
6067  // We'll substitute the parameter now without expanding the pack
6068  // expansion.
6069  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
6070  NewParm = getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParam(OldParm,
6071  indexAdjustment,
6072  NumExpansions,
6073  /*ExpectParameterPack=*/true);
6074  assert(NewParm->isParameterPack() &&
6075  "Parameter pack no longer a parameter pack after "
6076  "transformation.");
6077  } else {
6078  NewParm = getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParam(
6079  OldParm, indexAdjustment, std::nullopt,
6080  /*ExpectParameterPack=*/false);
6081  }
6082 
6083  if (!NewParm)
6084  return true;
6085 
6086  if (ParamInfos)
6087  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6088  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewParm->getType());
6089  if (PVars)
6090  PVars->push_back(NewParm);
6091  continue;
6092  }
6093 
6094  // Deal with the possibility that we don't have a parameter
6095  // declaration for this parameter.
6096  assert(ParamTypes);
6097  QualType OldType = ParamTypes[i];
6098  bool IsPackExpansion = false;
6099  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
6100  QualType NewType;
6101  if (const PackExpansionType *Expansion
6102  = dyn_cast<PackExpansionType>(OldType)) {
6103  // We have a function parameter pack that may need to be expanded.
6104  QualType Pattern = Expansion->getPattern();
6105  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
6106  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
6107 
6108  // Determine whether we should expand the parameter packs.
6109  bool ShouldExpand = false;
6110  bool RetainExpansion = false;
6111  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(Loc, SourceRange(),
6112  Unexpanded,
6113  ShouldExpand,
6114  RetainExpansion,
6115  NumExpansions)) {
6116  return true;
6117  }
6118 
6119  if (ShouldExpand) {
6120  // Expand the function parameter pack into multiple, separate
6121  // parameters.
6122  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
6123  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
6124  QualType NewType = getDerived().TransformType(Pattern);
6125  if (NewType.isNull())
6126  return true;
6127 
6128  if (NewType->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
6129  NewType = getSema().getASTContext().getPackExpansionType(
6130  NewType, std::nullopt);
6131 
6132  if (NewType.isNull())
6133  return true;
6134  }
6135 
6136  if (ParamInfos)
6137  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6138  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewType);
6139  if (PVars)
6140  PVars->push_back(nullptr);
6141  }
6142 
6143  // We're done with the pack expansion.
6144  continue;
6145  }
6146 
6147  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
6148  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
6149  if (RetainExpansion) {
6150  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
6151  QualType NewType = getDerived().TransformType(Pattern);
6152  if (NewType.isNull())
6153  return true;
6154 
6155  if (ParamInfos)
6156  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6157  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewType);
6158  if (PVars)
6159  PVars->push_back(nullptr);
6160  }
6161 
6162  // We'll substitute the parameter now without expanding the pack
6163  // expansion.
6164  OldType = Expansion->getPattern();
6165  IsPackExpansion = true;
6166  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
6167  NewType = getDerived().TransformType(OldType);
6168  } else {
6169  NewType = getDerived().TransformType(OldType);
6170  }
6171 
6172  if (NewType.isNull())
6173  return true;
6174 
6175  if (IsPackExpansion)
6176  NewType = getSema().Context.getPackExpansionType(NewType,
6177  NumExpansions);
6178 
6179  if (ParamInfos)
6180  PInfos.set(OutParamTypes.size(), ParamInfos[i]);
6181  OutParamTypes.push_back(NewType);
6182  if (PVars)
6183  PVars->push_back(nullptr);
6184  }
6185 
6186 #ifndef NDEBUG
6187  if (PVars) {
6188  for (unsigned i = 0, e = PVars->size(); i != e; ++i)
6189  if (ParmVarDecl *parm = (*PVars)[i])
6190  assert(parm->getFunctionScopeIndex() == i);
6191  }
6192 #endif
6193 
6194  return false;
6195 }
6196 
6197 template<typename Derived>
6198 QualType
6199 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformFunctionProtoType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6200  FunctionProtoTypeLoc TL) {
6201  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ExceptionStorage;
6202  return getDerived().TransformFunctionProtoType(
6203  TLB, TL, nullptr, Qualifiers(),
6204  [&](FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI, bool &Changed) {
6205  return getDerived().TransformExceptionSpec(TL.getBeginLoc(), ESI,
6206  ExceptionStorage, Changed);
6207  });
6208 }
6209 
6210 template<typename Derived> template<typename Fn>
6211 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformFunctionProtoType(
6212  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, FunctionProtoTypeLoc TL, CXXRecordDecl *ThisContext,
6213  Qualifiers ThisTypeQuals, Fn TransformExceptionSpec) {
6214 
6215  // Transform the parameters and return type.
6216  //
6217  // We are required to instantiate the params and return type in source order.
6218  // When the function has a trailing return type, we instantiate the
6219  // parameters before the return type, since the return type can then refer
6220  // to the parameters themselves (via decltype, sizeof, etc.).
6221  //
6222  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ParamTypes;
6223  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl*, 4> ParamDecls;
6224  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder ExtParamInfos;
6225  const FunctionProtoType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6226 
6227  QualType ResultType;
6228 
6229  if (T->hasTrailingReturn()) {
6230  if (getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParams(
6231  TL.getBeginLoc(), TL.getParams(),
6232  TL.getTypePtr()->param_type_begin(),
6233  T->getExtParameterInfosOrNull(),
6234  ParamTypes, &ParamDecls, ExtParamInfos))
6235  return QualType();
6236 
6237  {
6238  // C++11 [expr.prim.general]p3:
6239  // If a declaration declares a member function or member function
6240  // template of a class X, the expression this is a prvalue of type
6241  // "pointer to cv-qualifier-seq X" between the optional cv-qualifer-seq
6242  // and the end of the function-definition, member-declarator, or
6243  // declarator.
6244  auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SemaRef.getCurLexicalContext());
6245  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(
6246  SemaRef, !ThisContext && RD ? RD : ThisContext, ThisTypeQuals);
6247 
6248  ResultType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getReturnLoc());
6249  if (ResultType.isNull())
6250  return QualType();
6251  }
6252  }
6253  else {
6254  ResultType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getReturnLoc());
6255  if (ResultType.isNull())
6256  return QualType();
6257 
6258  if (getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParams(
6259  TL.getBeginLoc(), TL.getParams(),
6260  TL.getTypePtr()->param_type_begin(),
6261  T->getExtParameterInfosOrNull(),
6262  ParamTypes, &ParamDecls, ExtParamInfos))
6263  return QualType();
6264  }
6265 
6266  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = T->getExtProtoInfo();
6267 
6268  bool EPIChanged = false;
6269  if (TransformExceptionSpec(EPI.ExceptionSpec, EPIChanged))
6270  return QualType();
6271 
6272  // Handle extended parameter information.
6273  if (auto NewExtParamInfos =
6274  ExtParamInfos.getPointerOrNull(ParamTypes.size())) {
6275  if (!EPI.ExtParameterInfos ||
6276  llvm::ArrayRef(EPI.ExtParameterInfos, TL.getNumParams()) !=
6277  llvm::ArrayRef(NewExtParamInfos, ParamTypes.size())) {
6278  EPIChanged = true;
6279  }
6280  EPI.ExtParameterInfos = NewExtParamInfos;
6281  } else if (EPI.ExtParameterInfos) {
6282  EPIChanged = true;
6283  EPI.ExtParameterInfos = nullptr;
6284  }
6285 
6286  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6287  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || ResultType != T->getReturnType() ||
6288  T->getParamTypes() != llvm::ArrayRef(ParamTypes) || EPIChanged) {
6289  Result = getDerived().RebuildFunctionProtoType(ResultType, ParamTypes, EPI);
6290  if (Result.isNull())
6291  return QualType();
6292  }
6293 
6294  FunctionProtoTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>(Result);
6295  NewTL.setLocalRangeBegin(TL.getLocalRangeBegin());
6296  NewTL.setLParenLoc(TL.getLParenLoc());
6297  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
6298  NewTL.setExceptionSpecRange(TL.getExceptionSpecRange());
6299  NewTL.setLocalRangeEnd(TL.getLocalRangeEnd());
6300  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewTL.getNumParams(); i != e; ++i)
6301  NewTL.setParam(i, ParamDecls[i]);
6302 
6303  return Result;
6304 }
6305 
6306 template<typename Derived>
6307 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExceptionSpec(
6308  SourceLocation Loc, FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI,
6309  SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &Exceptions, bool &Changed) {
6310  assert(ESI.Type != EST_Uninstantiated && ESI.Type != EST_Unevaluated);
6311 
6312  // Instantiate a dynamic noexcept expression, if any.
6313  if (isComputedNoexcept(ESI.Type)) {
6314  // Update this scrope because ContextDecl in Sema will be used in
6315  // TransformExpr.
6316  auto *Method = dyn_cast_if_present<CXXMethodDecl>(ESI.SourceTemplate);
6317  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(
6318  SemaRef, Method ? Method->getParent() : nullptr,
6319  Method ? Method->getMethodQualifiers() : Qualifiers{},
6320  Method != nullptr);
6321  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6322  getSema(), Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
6323  ExprResult NoexceptExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(ESI.NoexceptExpr);
6324  if (NoexceptExpr.isInvalid())
6325  return true;
6326 
6327  ExceptionSpecificationType EST = ESI.Type;
6328  NoexceptExpr =
6329  getSema().ActOnNoexceptSpec(NoexceptExpr.get(), EST);
6330  if (NoexceptExpr.isInvalid())
6331  return true;
6332 
6333  if (ESI.NoexceptExpr != NoexceptExpr.get() || EST != ESI.Type)
6334  Changed = true;
6335  ESI.NoexceptExpr = NoexceptExpr.get();
6336  ESI.Type = EST;
6337  }
6338 
6339  if (ESI.Type != EST_Dynamic)
6340  return false;
6341 
6342  // Instantiate a dynamic exception specification's type.
6343  for (QualType T : ESI.Exceptions) {
6344  if (const PackExpansionType *PackExpansion =
6345  T->getAs<PackExpansionType>()) {
6346  Changed = true;
6347 
6348  // We have a pack expansion. Instantiate it.
6349  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
6350  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(PackExpansion->getPattern(),
6351  Unexpanded);
6352  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
6353 
6354  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and
6355  // should
6356  // be expanded.
6357  bool Expand = false;
6358  bool RetainExpansion = false;
6359  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = PackExpansion->getNumExpansions();
6360  // FIXME: Track the location of the ellipsis (and track source location
6361  // information for the types in the exception specification in general).
6362  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(
6363  Loc, SourceRange(), Unexpanded, Expand,
6364  RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
6365  return true;
6366 
6367  if (!Expand) {
6368  // We can't expand this pack expansion into separate arguments yet;
6369  // just substitute into the pattern and create a new pack expansion
6370  // type.
6371  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
6372  QualType U = getDerived().TransformType(PackExpansion->getPattern());
6373  if (U.isNull())
6374  return true;
6375 
6376  U = SemaRef.Context.getPackExpansionType(U, NumExpansions);
6377  Exceptions.push_back(U);
6378  continue;
6379  }
6380 
6381  // Substitute into the pack expansion pattern for each slice of the
6382  // pack.
6383  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx != *NumExpansions; ++ArgIdx) {
6384  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), ArgIdx);
6385 
6386  QualType U = getDerived().TransformType(PackExpansion->getPattern());
6387  if (U.isNull() || SemaRef.CheckSpecifiedExceptionType(U, Loc))
6388  return true;
6389 
6390  Exceptions.push_back(U);
6391  }
6392  } else {
6393  QualType U = getDerived().TransformType(T);
6394  if (U.isNull() || SemaRef.CheckSpecifiedExceptionType(U, Loc))
6395  return true;
6396  if (T != U)
6397  Changed = true;
6398 
6399  Exceptions.push_back(U);
6400  }
6401  }
6402 
6403  ESI.Exceptions = Exceptions;
6404  if (ESI.Exceptions.empty())
6405  ESI.Type = EST_DynamicNone;
6406  return false;
6407 }
6408 
6409 template<typename Derived>
6410 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformFunctionNoProtoType(
6411  TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6412  FunctionNoProtoTypeLoc TL) {
6413  const FunctionNoProtoType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6414  QualType ResultType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getReturnLoc());
6415  if (ResultType.isNull())
6416  return QualType();
6417 
6418  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6419  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || ResultType != T->getReturnType())
6420  Result = getDerived().RebuildFunctionNoProtoType(ResultType);
6421 
6422  FunctionNoProtoTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<FunctionNoProtoTypeLoc>(Result);
6423  NewTL.setLocalRangeBegin(TL.getLocalRangeBegin());
6424  NewTL.setLParenLoc(TL.getLParenLoc());
6425  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
6426  NewTL.setLocalRangeEnd(TL.getLocalRangeEnd());
6427 
6428  return Result;
6429 }

6431 template <typename Derived>
6432 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnresolvedUsingType(
6433  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, UnresolvedUsingTypeLoc TL) {
6434  const UnresolvedUsingType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6435  Decl *D = getDerived().TransformDecl(TL.getNameLoc(), T->getDecl());
6436  if (!D)
6437  return QualType();
6438 
6439  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6440  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || D != T->getDecl()) {
6441  Result = getDerived().RebuildUnresolvedUsingType(TL.getNameLoc(), D);
6442  if (Result.isNull())
6443  return QualType();
6444  }
6445 
6446  // We might get an arbitrary type spec type back. We should at
6447  // least always get a type spec type, though.
6448  TypeSpecTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.pushTypeSpec(Result);
6449  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
6450 
6451  return Result;
6452 }

6454 template <typename Derived>
6455 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUsingType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6456  UsingTypeLoc TL) {
6457  const UsingType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6458 
6459  auto *Found = cast_or_null<UsingShadowDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
6460  TL.getLocalSourceRange().getBegin(), T->getFoundDecl()));
6461  if (!Found)
6462  return QualType();
6463 
6464  QualType Underlying = getDerived().TransformType(T->desugar());
6465  if (Underlying.isNull())
6466  return QualType();
6467 
6468  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6469  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || Found != T->getFoundDecl() ||
6470  Underlying != T->getUnderlyingType()) {
6471  Result = getDerived().RebuildUsingType(Found, Underlying);
6472  if (Result.isNull())
6473  return QualType();
6474  }
6475 
6476  TLB.pushTypeSpec(Result).setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
6477  return Result;
6478 }

6485  = cast_or_null<TypedefNameDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(TL.getNameLoc(),

6487  if (!Typedef)
6488  return QualType();

6490  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6491  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
6492  Typedef != T->getDecl()) {
6493  Result = getDerived().RebuildTypedefType(Typedef);
6494  if (Result.isNull())
6495  return QualType();
6496  }
6497 
6498  TypedefTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<TypedefTypeLoc>(Result);
6499  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
6500 
6501  return Result;

6504 template<typename Derived>
6505 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeOfExprType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6506  TypeOfExprTypeLoc TL) {
6507  // typeof expressions are not potentially evaluated contexts
6508  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6509  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
6510  Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
6511 
6512  ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(TL.getUnderlyingExpr());
6513  if (E.isInvalid())
6514  return QualType();
6515 
6516  E = SemaRef.HandleExprEvaluationContextForTypeof(E.get());
6517  if (E.isInvalid())
6518  return QualType();
6519 
6520  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6521  TypeOfKind Kind = Result->getAs<TypeOfExprType>()->getKind();
6522  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || E.get() != TL.getUnderlyingExpr()) {
6523  Result =
6524  getDerived().RebuildTypeOfExprType(E.get(), TL.getTypeofLoc(), Kind);
6525  if (Result.isNull())
6526  return QualType();
6527  }
6528 
6529  TypeOfExprTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<TypeOfExprTypeLoc>(Result);
6530  NewTL.setTypeofLoc(TL.getTypeofLoc());
6531  NewTL.setLParenLoc(TL.getLParenLoc());
6532  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
6533 
6534  return Result;
6535 }

6537 template<typename Derived>
6538 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeOfType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6539  TypeOfTypeLoc TL) {
6540  TypeSourceInfo* Old_Under_TI = TL.getUnmodifiedTInfo();
6541  TypeSourceInfo* New_Under_TI = getDerived().TransformType(Old_Under_TI);
6542  if (!New_Under_TI)
6543  return QualType();
6544 
6545  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6546  TypeOfKind Kind = Result->getAs<TypeOfType>()->getKind();
6547  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || New_Under_TI != Old_Under_TI) {
6548  Result = getDerived().RebuildTypeOfType(New_Under_TI->getType(), Kind);
6549  if (Result.isNull())
6550  return QualType();
6551  }
6552 
6553  TypeOfTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<TypeOfTypeLoc>(Result);
6554  NewTL.setTypeofLoc(TL.getTypeofLoc());
6555  NewTL.setLParenLoc(TL.getLParenLoc());
6556  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
6557  NewTL.setUnmodifiedTInfo(New_Under_TI);
6558 
6559  return Result;
6560 }

6562 template<typename Derived>
6563 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDecltypeType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6564  DecltypeTypeLoc TL) {
6565  const DecltypeType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6566 
6567  // decltype expressions are not potentially evaluated contexts
6568  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6569  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated, nullptr,
6570  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Decltype);
6571 
6572  ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(T->getUnderlyingExpr());
6573  if (E.isInvalid())
6574  return QualType();
6575 
6576  E = getSema().ActOnDecltypeExpression(E.get());
6577  if (E.isInvalid())
6578  return QualType();
6579 
6580  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6581  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
6582  E.get() != T->getUnderlyingExpr()) {
6583  Result = getDerived().RebuildDecltypeType(E.get(), TL.getDecltypeLoc());
6584  if (Result.isNull())
6585  return QualType();
6586  }
6587  else E.get();
6588 
6589  DecltypeTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<DecltypeTypeLoc>(Result);
6590  NewTL.setDecltypeLoc(TL.getDecltypeLoc());
6591  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
6592  return Result;
6593 }

6595 template <typename Derived>
6596 QualType
6597 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPackIndexingType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6598  PackIndexingTypeLoc TL) {
6599  // Transform the index
6600  ExprResult IndexExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(TL.getIndexExpr());
6601  if (IndexExpr.isInvalid())
6602  return QualType();
6603  QualType Pattern = TL.getPattern();
6604 
6605  const PackIndexingType *PIT = TL.getTypePtr();
6606  SmallVector<QualType, 5> SubtitutedTypes;
6607  llvm::ArrayRef<QualType> Types = PIT->getExpansions();
6608 
6609  bool NotYetExpanded = Types.empty();
6610  bool FullySubstituted = true;
6611 
6612  if (Types.empty())
6613  Types = llvm::ArrayRef<QualType>(&Pattern, 1);
6614 
6615  for (const QualType &T : Types) {
6616  if (!T->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
6617  QualType Transformed = getDerived().TransformType(T);
6618  if (Transformed.isNull())
6619  return QualType();
6620  SubtitutedTypes.push_back(Transformed);
6621  continue;
6622  }
6623 
6624  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
6625  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(T, Unexpanded);
6626  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
6627  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
6628  // be expanded.
6629  bool ShouldExpand = true;
6630  bool RetainExpansion = false;
6631  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions;
6632  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
6633  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(TL.getEllipsisLoc(), SourceRange(),
6634  Unexpanded, ShouldExpand,
6635  RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
6636  return QualType();
6637  if (!ShouldExpand) {
6638  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
6639  // FIXME: should we keep TypeLoc for individual expansions in
6640  // PackIndexingTypeLoc?
6641  TypeSourceInfo *TI =
6642  SemaRef.getASTContext().getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, TL.getBeginLoc());
6643  QualType Pack = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TI->getTypeLoc());
6644  if (Pack.isNull())
6645  return QualType();
6646  if (NotYetExpanded) {
6647  FullySubstituted = false;
6648  QualType Out = getDerived().RebuildPackIndexingType(
6649  Pack, IndexExpr.get(), SourceLocation(), TL.getEllipsisLoc(),
6650  FullySubstituted);
6651  if (Out.isNull())
6652  return QualType();
6653 
6654  PackIndexingTypeLoc Loc = TLB.push<PackIndexingTypeLoc>(Out);
6655  Loc.setEllipsisLoc(TL.getEllipsisLoc());
6656  return Out;
6657  }
6658  SubtitutedTypes.push_back(Pack);
6659  continue;
6660  }
6661  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
6662  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
6663  QualType Out = getDerived().TransformType(T);
6664  if (Out.isNull())
6665  return QualType();
6666  SubtitutedTypes.push_back(Out);
6667  }
6668  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
6669  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
6670  if (RetainExpansion) {
6671  FullySubstituted = false;
6672  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
6673  QualType Out = getDerived().TransformType(T);
6674  if (Out.isNull())
6675  return QualType();
6676  SubtitutedTypes.push_back(Out);
6677  }
6678  }
6679 
6680  QualType Result = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPatternLoc());
6681 
6682  QualType Out = getDerived().RebuildPackIndexingType(
6683  Result, IndexExpr.get(), SourceLocation(), TL.getEllipsisLoc(),
6684  FullySubstituted, SubtitutedTypes);
6685  if (Out.isNull())
6686  return Out;
6687 
6688  PackIndexingTypeLoc Loc = TLB.push<PackIndexingTypeLoc>(Out);
6689  Loc.setEllipsisLoc(TL.getEllipsisLoc());
6690  return Out;
6691 }
6692

6694 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnaryTransformType(
6695  TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
6696  UnaryTransformTypeLoc TL) {
6697  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6698  if (Result->isDependentType()) {
6699  const UnaryTransformType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
6700  QualType NewBase =
6701  getDerived().TransformType(TL.getUnderlyingTInfo())->getType();
6702  Result = getDerived().RebuildUnaryTransformType(NewBase,
6703  T->getUTTKind(),
6704  TL.getKWLoc());
6705  if (Result.isNull())
6706  return QualType();
6707  }

6710  NewTL.setKWLoc(TL.getKWLoc());
6711  NewTL.setParensRange(TL.getParensRange());
6712  NewTL.setUnderlyingTInfo(TL.getUnderlyingTInfo());

6946 template <typename Derived>
6947 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentBitIntType(
6948  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, DependentBitIntTypeLoc TL) {
6949  const DependentBitIntType *EIT = TL.getTypePtr();
6950 
6951  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
6952  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
6953  ExprResult BitsExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(EIT->getNumBitsExpr());
6954  BitsExpr = SemaRef.ActOnConstantExpression(BitsExpr);
6955 
6956  if (BitsExpr.isInvalid())
6957  return QualType();
6958 
6959  QualType Result = TL.getType();
6960 
6961  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || BitsExpr.get() != EIT->getNumBitsExpr()) {
6962  Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentBitIntType(
6963  EIT->isUnsigned(), BitsExpr.get(), TL.getNameLoc());
6964 
6965  if (Result.isNull())
6966  return QualType();
6967  }
6968 
6969  if (isa<DependentBitIntType>(Result)) {
6970  DependentBitIntTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<DependentBitIntTypeLoc>(Result);
6971  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
6972  } else {
6973  BitIntTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<BitIntTypeLoc>(Result);
6974  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
6975  }
6976  return Result;
6977 }
6978 
6979  /// Simple iterator that traverses the template arguments in a
6980  /// container that provides a \c getArgLoc() member function.
6981  ///
6982  /// This iterator is intended to be used with the iterator form of
6983  /// \c TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTemplateArguments().
6984  template<typename ArgLocContainer>
6985  class TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator {
6986  ArgLocContainer *Container;
6987  unsigned Index;
6988 
6989  public:
6990  typedef TemplateArgumentLoc value_type;
6991  typedef TemplateArgumentLoc reference;
6992  typedef int difference_type;
6993  typedef std::input_iterator_tag iterator_category;
6994 
6995  class pointer {
6996  TemplateArgumentLoc Arg;
6997 
6998  public:
6999  explicit pointer(TemplateArgumentLoc Arg) : Arg(Arg) { }
7000 
7001  const TemplateArgumentLoc *operator->() const {
7002  return &Arg;
7003  }
7004  };
7005 
7006 
7007  TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator() {}
7008 
7009  TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator(ArgLocContainer &Container,
7010  unsigned Index)
7011  : Container(&Container), Index(Index) { }
7012 
7013  TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator &operator++() {
7014  ++Index;
7015  return *this;
7016  }
7017 
7018  TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator operator++(int) {
7019  TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator Old(*this);
7020  ++(*this);
7021  return Old;
7022  }
7023 
7024  TemplateArgumentLoc operator*() const {
7025  return Container->getArgLoc(Index);
7026  }
7027 
7028  pointer operator->() const {
7029  return pointer(Container->getArgLoc(Index));
7030  }
7031 
7032  friend bool operator==(const TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator &X,
7033  const TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator &Y) {
7034  return X.Container == Y.Container && X.Index == Y.Index;
7035  }
7036 
7037  friend bool operator!=(const TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator &X,
7038  const TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator &Y) {
7039  return !(X == Y);
7040  }
7041  };
7042 
7043 template<typename Derived>
7044 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAutoType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7045  AutoTypeLoc TL) {
7046  const AutoType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
7047  QualType OldDeduced = T->getDeducedType();
7048  QualType NewDeduced;
7049  if (!OldDeduced.isNull()) {
7050  NewDeduced = getDerived().TransformType(OldDeduced);
7051  if (NewDeduced.isNull())
7052  return QualType();
7053  }
7054 
7055  ConceptDecl *NewCD = nullptr;
7056  TemplateArgumentListInfo NewTemplateArgs;
7057  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NewNestedNameSpec;
7058  if (T->isConstrained()) {
7059  assert(TL.getConceptReference());
7060  NewCD = cast_or_null<ConceptDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
7061  TL.getConceptNameLoc(), T->getTypeConstraintConcept()));
7062 
7063  NewTemplateArgs.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7064  NewTemplateArgs.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7065  typedef TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator<AutoTypeLoc> ArgIterator;
7066  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(
7067  ArgIterator(TL, 0), ArgIterator(TL, TL.getNumArgs()),
7068  NewTemplateArgs))
7069  return QualType();
7070 
7071  if (TL.getNestedNameSpecifierLoc()) {
7072  NewNestedNameSpec
7073  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(
7074  TL.getNestedNameSpecifierLoc());
7075  if (!NewNestedNameSpec)
7076  return QualType();
7077  }
7078  }
7079 
7080  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7081  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || NewDeduced != OldDeduced ||
7082  T->isDependentType() || T->isConstrained()) {
7083  // FIXME: Maybe don't rebuild if all template arguments are the same.
7084  llvm::SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> NewArgList;
7085  NewArgList.reserve(NewTemplateArgs.size());
7086  for (const auto &ArgLoc : NewTemplateArgs.arguments())
7087  NewArgList.push_back(ArgLoc.getArgument());
7088  Result = getDerived().RebuildAutoType(NewDeduced, T->getKeyword(), NewCD,
7089  NewArgList);
7090  if (Result.isNull())
7091  return QualType();
7092  }
7093 
7094  AutoTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<AutoTypeLoc>(Result);
7095  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
7096  NewTL.setRParenLoc(TL.getRParenLoc());
7097  NewTL.setConceptReference(nullptr);
7098 
7099  if (T->isConstrained()) {
7100  DeclarationNameInfo DNI = DeclarationNameInfo(
7101  TL.getTypePtr()->getTypeConstraintConcept()->getDeclName(),
7102  TL.getConceptNameLoc(),
7103  TL.getTypePtr()->getTypeConstraintConcept()->getDeclName());
7104  auto *CR = ConceptReference::Create(
7105  SemaRef.Context, NewNestedNameSpec, TL.getTemplateKWLoc(), DNI,
7106  TL.getFoundDecl(), TL.getTypePtr()->getTypeConstraintConcept(),
7107  ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo::Create(SemaRef.Context, NewTemplateArgs));
7108  NewTL.setConceptReference(CR);
7109  }
7110 
7111  return Result;
7112 }
7113 
7114 template <typename Derived>
7115 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTemplateSpecializationType(
7116  TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7117  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL,
7118  TemplateName Template) {
7119  TemplateArgumentListInfo NewTemplateArgs;
7120  NewTemplateArgs.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7121  NewTemplateArgs.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7122  typedef TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>
7123  ArgIterator;
7124  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(ArgIterator(TL, 0),
7125  ArgIterator(TL, TL.getNumArgs()),
7126  NewTemplateArgs))
7127  return QualType();
7128 
7129  // FIXME: maybe don't rebuild if all the template arguments are the same.
7130 
7131  QualType Result =
7132  getDerived().RebuildTemplateSpecializationType(Template,
7133  TL.getTemplateNameLoc(),
7134  NewTemplateArgs);
7135 
7136  if (!Result.isNull()) {
7137  // Specializations of template template parameters are represented as
7138  // TemplateSpecializationTypes, and substitution of type alias templates
7139  // within a dependent context can transform them into
7140  // DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.
7141  if (isa<DependentTemplateSpecializationType>(Result)) {
7142  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NewTL
7143  = TLB.push<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7144  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
7145  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc());
7146  NewTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7147  NewTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7148  NewTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7149  NewTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7150  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewTemplateArgs.size(); i != e; ++i)
7151  NewTL.setArgLocInfo(i, NewTemplateArgs[i].getLocInfo());
7152  return Result;
7153  }
7154 
7155  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NewTL
7156  = TLB.push<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7157  NewTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7158  NewTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7159  NewTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7160  NewTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7161  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewTemplateArgs.size(); i != e; ++i)
7162  NewTL.setArgLocInfo(i, NewTemplateArgs[i].getLocInfo());
7163  }
7164 
7165  return Result;
7166 }
7167 
7168 template <typename Derived>
7169 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
7170  TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7171  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL,
7172  TemplateName Template,
7173  CXXScopeSpec &SS) {
7174  TemplateArgumentListInfo NewTemplateArgs;
7175  NewTemplateArgs.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7176  NewTemplateArgs.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7177  typedef TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator<
7178  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc> ArgIterator;
7179  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(ArgIterator(TL, 0),
7180  ArgIterator(TL, TL.getNumArgs()),
7181  NewTemplateArgs))
7182  return QualType();
7183 
7184  // FIXME: maybe don't rebuild if all the template arguments are the same.
7185 
7186  if (DependentTemplateName *DTN = Template.getAsDependentTemplateName()) {
7187  QualType Result = getSema().Context.getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
7188  TL.getTypePtr()->getKeyword(), DTN->getQualifier(),
7189  DTN->getIdentifier(), NewTemplateArgs.arguments());
7190 
7191  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NewTL
7192  = TLB.push<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7193  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7194  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(SS.getWithLocInContext(SemaRef.Context));
7195  NewTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7196  NewTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7197  NewTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7198  NewTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7199  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewTemplateArgs.size(); i != e; ++i)
7200  NewTL.setArgLocInfo(i, NewTemplateArgs[i].getLocInfo());
7201  return Result;
7202  }
7203 
7204  QualType Result
7205  = getDerived().RebuildTemplateSpecializationType(Template,
7206  TL.getTemplateNameLoc(),
7207  NewTemplateArgs);
7208 
7209  if (!Result.isNull()) {
7210  /// FIXME: Wrap this in an elaborated-type-specifier?
7211  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NewTL
7212  = TLB.push<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7213  NewTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7214  NewTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7215  NewTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7216  NewTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7217  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NewTemplateArgs.size(); i != e; ++i)
7218  NewTL.setArgLocInfo(i, NewTemplateArgs[i].getLocInfo());
7219  }
7220 
7221  return Result;
7222 }
7223 
7224 template<typename Derived>
7225 QualType
7226 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformElaboratedType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7227  ElaboratedTypeLoc TL) {
7228  const ElaboratedType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
7229 
7230  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
7231  // NOTE: the qualifier in an ElaboratedType is optional.
7232  if (TL.getQualifierLoc()) {
7233  QualifierLoc
7234  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(TL.getQualifierLoc());
7235  if (!QualifierLoc)
7236  return QualType();
7237  }
7238 
7239  QualType NamedT = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getNamedTypeLoc());
7240  if (NamedT.isNull())
7241  return QualType();
7242 
7243  // C++0x [dcl.type.elab]p2:
7244  // If the identifier resolves to a typedef-name or the simple-template-id
7245  // resolves to an alias template specialization, the
7246  // elaborated-type-specifier is ill-formed.
7247  if (T->getKeyword() != ElaboratedTypeKeyword::None &&
7248  T->getKeyword() != ElaboratedTypeKeyword::Typename) {
7249  if (const TemplateSpecializationType *TST =
7250  NamedT->getAs<TemplateSpecializationType>()) {
7251  TemplateName Template = TST->getTemplateName();
7252  if (TypeAliasTemplateDecl *TAT = dyn_cast_or_null<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(
7253  Template.getAsTemplateDecl())) {
7254  SemaRef.Diag(TL.getNamedTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
7255  diag::err_tag_reference_non_tag)
7256  << TAT << Sema::NTK_TypeAliasTemplate
7257  << llvm::to_underlying(
7258  ElaboratedType::getTagTypeKindForKeyword(T->getKeyword()));
7259  SemaRef.Diag(TAT->getLocation(), diag::note_declared_at);
7260  }
7261  }
7262  }
7263 
7264  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7265  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
7266  QualifierLoc != TL.getQualifierLoc() ||
7267  NamedT != T->getNamedType()) {
7268  Result = getDerived().RebuildElaboratedType(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc(),
7269  T->getKeyword(),
7270  QualifierLoc, NamedT);
7271  if (Result.isNull())
7272  return QualType();
7273  }
7274 
7275  ElaboratedTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ElaboratedTypeLoc>(Result);
7276  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7277  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
7278  return Result;
7279 }
7280 
7281 template <typename Derived>
7282 template <typename Fn>
7283 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAttributedType(
7284  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, AttributedTypeLoc TL, Fn TransformModifiedTypeFn) {
7285  const AttributedType *oldType = TL.getTypePtr();
7286  QualType modifiedType = TransformModifiedTypeFn(TLB, TL.getModifiedLoc());
7287  if (modifiedType.isNull())
7288  return QualType();
7289 
7290  // oldAttr can be null if we started with a QualType rather than a TypeLoc.
7291  const Attr *oldAttr = TL.getAttr();
7292  const Attr *newAttr = oldAttr ? getDerived().TransformAttr(oldAttr) : nullptr;
7293  if (oldAttr && !newAttr)
7294  return QualType();
7295 
7296  QualType result = TL.getType();
7297 
7298  // FIXME: dependent operand expressions?
7299  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
7300  modifiedType != oldType->getModifiedType()) {
7301  TypeLocBuilder AuxiliaryTLB;
7302  AuxiliaryTLB.reserve(TL.getFullDataSize());
7303  QualType equivalentType =
7304  getDerived().TransformType(AuxiliaryTLB, TL.getEquivalentTypeLoc());
7305  if (equivalentType.isNull())
7306  return QualType();
7307 
7308  // Check whether we can add nullability; it is only represented as
7309  // type sugar, and therefore cannot be diagnosed in any other way.
7310  if (auto nullability = oldType->getImmediateNullability()) {
7311  if (!modifiedType->canHaveNullability()) {
7312  SemaRef.Diag((TL.getAttr() ? TL.getAttr()->getLocation()
7313  : TL.getModifiedLoc().getBeginLoc()),
7314  diag::err_nullability_nonpointer)
7315  << DiagNullabilityKind(*nullability, false) << modifiedType;
7316  return QualType();
7317  }
7318  }
7319 
7320  result = SemaRef.Context.getAttributedType(TL.getAttrKind(),
7321  modifiedType,
7322  equivalentType);
7323  }
7324 
7325  AttributedTypeLoc newTL = TLB.push<AttributedTypeLoc>(result);
7326  newTL.setAttr(newAttr);
7327  return result;
7328 }
7329 
7330 template <typename Derived>
7331 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAttributedType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7332  AttributedTypeLoc TL) {
7333  return getDerived().TransformAttributedType(
7334  TLB, TL, [&](TypeLocBuilder &TLB, TypeLoc ModifiedLoc) -> QualType {
7335  return getDerived().TransformType(TLB, ModifiedLoc);
7336  });
7337 }
7338 
7339 template <typename Derived>
7340 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCountAttributedType(
7341  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, CountAttributedTypeLoc TL) {
7342  const CountAttributedType *OldTy = TL.getTypePtr();
7343  QualType InnerTy = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getInnerLoc());
7344  if (InnerTy.isNull())
7345  return QualType();
7346 
7347  Expr *OldCount = TL.getCountExpr();
7348  Expr *NewCount = nullptr;
7349  if (OldCount) {
7350  ExprResult CountResult = getDerived().TransformExpr(OldCount);
7351  if (CountResult.isInvalid())
7352  return QualType();
7353  NewCount = CountResult.get();
7354  }
7355 
7356  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7357  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || InnerTy != OldTy->desugar() ||
7358  OldCount != NewCount) {
7359  // Currently, CountAttributedType can only wrap incomplete array types.
7360  Result = SemaRef.BuildCountAttributedArrayType(InnerTy, NewCount);
7361  }
7362 
7363  TLB.push<CountAttributedTypeLoc>(Result);
7364  return Result;
7365 }

7371  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected TreeTransform for BTFTagAttributedType");
7372 }

7423 template<typename Derived>
7424 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentNameType(
7425  TypeLocBuilder &TLB, DependentNameTypeLoc TL, bool DeducedTSTContext) {
7426  const DependentNameType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
7427 
7428  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc
7429  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(TL.getQualifierLoc());
7430  if (!QualifierLoc)
7431  return QualType();
7432 
7433  QualType Result
7434  = getDerived().RebuildDependentNameType(T->getKeyword(),
7435  TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc(),
7436  QualifierLoc,
7437  T->getIdentifier(),
7438  TL.getNameLoc(),
7439  DeducedTSTContext);
7440  if (Result.isNull())
7441  return QualType();
7442 
7443  if (const ElaboratedType* ElabT = Result->getAs<ElaboratedType>()) {
7444  QualType NamedT = ElabT->getNamedType();
7445  TLB.pushTypeSpec(NamedT).setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
7446 
7447  ElaboratedTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ElaboratedTypeLoc>(Result);
7448  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7449  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
7450  } else {
7451  DependentNameTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<DependentNameTypeLoc>(Result);
7452  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7453  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
7454  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
7455  }
7456  return Result;
7457 }

7459 template<typename Derived>
7460 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::
7461  TransformDependentTemplateSpecializationType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7462  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
7463  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
7464  if (TL.getQualifierLoc()) {
7465  QualifierLoc
7466  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(TL.getQualifierLoc());
7467  if (!QualifierLoc)
7468  return QualType();
7469  }
7470 
7471  return getDerived()
7472  .TransformDependentTemplateSpecializationType(TLB, TL, QualifierLoc);
7473 }
7474 
7475 template<typename Derived>
7476 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::
7477 TransformDependentTemplateSpecializationType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7478  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL,
7479  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc) {
7480  const DependentTemplateSpecializationType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
7481 
7482  TemplateArgumentListInfo NewTemplateArgs;
7483  NewTemplateArgs.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7484  NewTemplateArgs.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7485 
7486  typedef TemplateArgumentLocContainerIterator<
7487  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc> ArgIterator;
7488  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(ArgIterator(TL, 0),
7489  ArgIterator(TL, TL.getNumArgs()),
7490  NewTemplateArgs))
7491  return QualType();
7492 
7493  QualType Result = getDerived().RebuildDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
7494  T->getKeyword(), QualifierLoc, TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc(),
7495  T->getIdentifier(), TL.getTemplateNameLoc(), NewTemplateArgs,
7496  /*AllowInjectedClassName*/ false);
7497  if (Result.isNull())
7498  return QualType();
7499 
7500  if (const ElaboratedType *ElabT = dyn_cast<ElaboratedType>(Result)) {
7501  QualType NamedT = ElabT->getNamedType();
7502 
7503  // Copy information relevant to the template specialization.
7504  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NamedTL
7505  = TLB.push<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(NamedT);
7506  NamedTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7507  NamedTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7508  NamedTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7509  NamedTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7510  for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewTemplateArgs.size(); I != E; ++I)
7511  NamedTL.setArgLocInfo(I, NewTemplateArgs[I].getLocInfo());
7512 
7513  // Copy information relevant to the elaborated type.
7514  ElaboratedTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ElaboratedTypeLoc>(Result);
7515  NewTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7516  NewTL.setQualifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
7517  } else if (isa<DependentTemplateSpecializationType>(Result)) {
7518  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc SpecTL
7519  = TLB.push<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7520  SpecTL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(TL.getElaboratedKeywordLoc());
7521  SpecTL.setQualifierLoc(QualifierLoc);
7522  SpecTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7523  SpecTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7524  SpecTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7525  SpecTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7526  for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewTemplateArgs.size(); I != E; ++I)
7527  SpecTL.setArgLocInfo(I, NewTemplateArgs[I].getLocInfo());
7528  } else {
7529  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc SpecTL
7530  = TLB.push<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>(Result);
7531  SpecTL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(TL.getTemplateKeywordLoc());
7532  SpecTL.setTemplateNameLoc(TL.getTemplateNameLoc());
7533  SpecTL.setLAngleLoc(TL.getLAngleLoc());
7534  SpecTL.setRAngleLoc(TL.getRAngleLoc());
7535  for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewTemplateArgs.size(); I != E; ++I)
7536  SpecTL.setArgLocInfo(I, NewTemplateArgs[I].getLocInfo());
7537  }
7538  return Result;
7539 }

7541 template<typename Derived>
7542 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPackExpansionType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7543  PackExpansionTypeLoc TL) {
7544  QualType Pattern
7545  = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPatternLoc());
7546  if (Pattern.isNull())
7547  return QualType();
7548 
7549  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7550  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
7551  Pattern != TL.getPatternLoc().getType()) {
7552  Result = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansionType(Pattern,
7553  TL.getPatternLoc().getSourceRange(),
7554  TL.getEllipsisLoc(),
7555  TL.getTypePtr()->getNumExpansions());
7556  if (Result.isNull())
7557  return QualType();
7558  }
7559 
7560  PackExpansionTypeLoc NewT = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(Result);
7561  NewT.setEllipsisLoc(TL.getEllipsisLoc());
7562  return Result;
7563 }
