7574 template<typename Derived>
7575 QualType
7576 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCTypeParamType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7577  ObjCTypeParamTypeLoc TL) {
7578  const ObjCTypeParamType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
7579  ObjCTypeParamDecl *OTP = cast_or_null<ObjCTypeParamDecl>(
7580  getDerived().TransformDecl(T->getDecl()->getLocation(), T->getDecl()));
7581  if (!OTP)
7582  return QualType();
7583 
7584  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7585  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
7586  OTP != T->getDecl()) {
7587  Result = getDerived().RebuildObjCTypeParamType(
7588  OTP, TL.getProtocolLAngleLoc(),
7589  llvm::ArrayRef(TL.getTypePtr()->qual_begin(), TL.getNumProtocols()),
7590  TL.getProtocolLocs(), TL.getProtocolRAngleLoc());
7591  if (Result.isNull())
7592  return QualType();
7593  }
7594 
7595  ObjCTypeParamTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<ObjCTypeParamTypeLoc>(Result);
7596  if (TL.getNumProtocols()) {
7597  NewTL.setProtocolLAngleLoc(TL.getProtocolLAngleLoc());
7598  for (unsigned i = 0, n = TL.getNumProtocols(); i != n; ++i)
7599  NewTL.setProtocolLoc(i, TL.getProtocolLoc(i));
7600  NewTL.setProtocolRAngleLoc(TL.getProtocolRAngleLoc());
7601  }
7602  return Result;
7603 }
7604 
7605 template<typename Derived>
7606 QualType
7607 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCObjectType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7608  ObjCObjectTypeLoc TL) {
7609  // Transform base type.
7610  QualType BaseType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getBaseLoc());
7611  if (BaseType.isNull())
7612  return QualType();
7613 
7614  bool AnyChanged = BaseType != TL.getBaseLoc().getType();
7615 
7616  // Transform type arguments.
7617  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> NewTypeArgInfos;
7618  for (unsigned i = 0, n = TL.getNumTypeArgs(); i != n; ++i) {
7619  TypeSourceInfo *TypeArgInfo = TL.getTypeArgTInfo(i);
7620  TypeLoc TypeArgLoc = TypeArgInfo->getTypeLoc();
7621  QualType TypeArg = TypeArgInfo->getType();
7622  if (auto PackExpansionLoc = TypeArgLoc.getAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>()) {
7623  AnyChanged = true;
7624 
7625  // We have a pack expansion. Instantiate it.
7626  const auto *PackExpansion = PackExpansionLoc.getType()
7627  ->castAs<PackExpansionType>();
7628  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
7629  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(PackExpansion->getPattern(),
7630  Unexpanded);
7631  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
7632 
7633  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can
7634  // and should be expanded.
7635  TypeLoc PatternLoc = PackExpansionLoc.getPatternLoc();
7636  bool Expand = false;
7637  bool RetainExpansion = false;
7638  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = PackExpansion->getNumExpansions();
7639  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(
7640  PackExpansionLoc.getEllipsisLoc(), PatternLoc.getSourceRange(),
7641  Unexpanded, Expand, RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
7642  return QualType();
7643 
7644  if (!Expand) {
7645  // We can't expand this pack expansion into separate arguments yet;
7646  // just substitute into the pattern and create a new pack expansion
7647  // type.
7648  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
7649 
7650  TypeLocBuilder TypeArgBuilder;
7651  TypeArgBuilder.reserve(PatternLoc.getFullDataSize());
7652  QualType NewPatternType = getDerived().TransformType(TypeArgBuilder,
7653  PatternLoc);
7654  if (NewPatternType.isNull())
7655  return QualType();
7656 
7657  QualType NewExpansionType = SemaRef.Context.getPackExpansionType(
7658  NewPatternType, NumExpansions);
7659  auto NewExpansionLoc = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(NewExpansionType);
7660  NewExpansionLoc.setEllipsisLoc(PackExpansionLoc.getEllipsisLoc());
7661  NewTypeArgInfos.push_back(
7662  TypeArgBuilder.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, NewExpansionType));
7663  continue;
7664  }
7665 
7666  // Substitute into the pack expansion pattern for each slice of the
7667  // pack.
7668  for (unsigned ArgIdx = 0; ArgIdx != *NumExpansions; ++ArgIdx) {
7669  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), ArgIdx);
7670 
7671  TypeLocBuilder TypeArgBuilder;
7672  TypeArgBuilder.reserve(PatternLoc.getFullDataSize());
7673 
7674  QualType NewTypeArg = getDerived().TransformType(TypeArgBuilder,
7675  PatternLoc);
7676  if (NewTypeArg.isNull())
7677  return QualType();
7678 
7679  NewTypeArgInfos.push_back(
7680  TypeArgBuilder.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, NewTypeArg));
7681  }
7682 
7683  continue;
7684  }
7685 
7686  TypeLocBuilder TypeArgBuilder;
7687  TypeArgBuilder.reserve(TypeArgLoc.getFullDataSize());
7688  QualType NewTypeArg =
7689  getDerived().TransformType(TypeArgBuilder, TypeArgLoc);
7690  if (NewTypeArg.isNull())
7691  return QualType();
7692 
7693  // If nothing changed, just keep the old TypeSourceInfo.
7694  if (NewTypeArg == TypeArg) {
7695  NewTypeArgInfos.push_back(TypeArgInfo);
7696  continue;
7697  }
7698 
7699  NewTypeArgInfos.push_back(
7700  TypeArgBuilder.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, NewTypeArg));
7701  AnyChanged = true;
7702  }
7703 
7704  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7705  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() || AnyChanged) {
7706  // Rebuild the type.
7707  Result = getDerived().RebuildObjCObjectType(
7708  BaseType, TL.getBeginLoc(), TL.getTypeArgsLAngleLoc(), NewTypeArgInfos,
7709  TL.getTypeArgsRAngleLoc(), TL.getProtocolLAngleLoc(),
7710  llvm::ArrayRef(TL.getTypePtr()->qual_begin(), TL.getNumProtocols()),
7711  TL.getProtocolLocs(), TL.getProtocolRAngleLoc());
7712 
7713  if (Result.isNull())
7714  return QualType();
7715  }
7716 
7717  ObjCObjectTypeLoc NewT = TLB.push<ObjCObjectTypeLoc>(Result);
7718  NewT.setHasBaseTypeAsWritten(true);
7719  NewT.setTypeArgsLAngleLoc(TL.getTypeArgsLAngleLoc());
7720  for (unsigned i = 0, n = TL.getNumTypeArgs(); i != n; ++i)
7721  NewT.setTypeArgTInfo(i, NewTypeArgInfos[i]);
7722  NewT.setTypeArgsRAngleLoc(TL.getTypeArgsRAngleLoc());
7723  NewT.setProtocolLAngleLoc(TL.getProtocolLAngleLoc());
7724  for (unsigned i = 0, n = TL.getNumProtocols(); i != n; ++i)
7725  NewT.setProtocolLoc(i, TL.getProtocolLoc(i));
7726  NewT.setProtocolRAngleLoc(TL.getProtocolRAngleLoc());
7727  return Result;
7728 }
7729 
7730 template<typename Derived>
7731 QualType
7732 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCObjectPointerType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB,
7733  ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
7734  QualType PointeeType = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, TL.getPointeeLoc());
7735  if (PointeeType.isNull())
7736  return QualType();
7737 
7738  QualType Result = TL.getType();
7739  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
7740  PointeeType != TL.getPointeeLoc().getType()) {
7741  Result = getDerived().RebuildObjCObjectPointerType(PointeeType,
7742  TL.getStarLoc());
7743  if (Result.isNull())
7744  return QualType();
7745  }
7746 
7747  ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc NewT = TLB.push<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>(Result);
7748  NewT.setStarLoc(TL.getStarLoc());
7749  return Result;
7750 }

7759 }

7761 template<typename Derived>
7762 StmtResult
7763 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundStmt(CompoundStmt *S) {
7764  return getDerived().TransformCompoundStmt(S, false);
7765 }
7766 
7767 template<typename Derived>
7768 StmtResult
7769 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundStmt(CompoundStmt *S,
7770  bool IsStmtExpr) {
7771  Sema::CompoundScopeRAII CompoundScope(getSema());
7772  Sema::FPFeaturesStateRAII FPSave(getSema());
7773  if (S->hasStoredFPFeatures())
7774  getSema().resetFPOptions(
7775  S->getStoredFPFeatures().applyOverrides(getSema().getLangOpts()));
7776 
7777  const Stmt *ExprResult = S->getStmtExprResult();
7778  bool SubStmtInvalid = false;
7779  bool SubStmtChanged = false;
7780  SmallVector<Stmt*, 8> Statements;
7781  for (auto *B : S->body()) {
7782  StmtResult Result = getDerived().TransformStmt(
7783  B, IsStmtExpr && B == ExprResult ? SDK_StmtExprResult : SDK_Discarded);
7784 
7785  if (Result.isInvalid()) {
7786  // Immediately fail if this was a DeclStmt, since it's very
7787  // likely that this will cause problems for future statements.
7788  if (isa<DeclStmt>(B))
7789  return StmtError();
7790 
7791  // Otherwise, just keep processing substatements and fail later.
7792  SubStmtInvalid = true;
7793  continue;
7794  }
7795 
7796  SubStmtChanged = SubStmtChanged || Result.get() != B;
7797  Statements.push_back(Result.getAs<Stmt>());
7798  }
7799 
7800  if (SubStmtInvalid)
7801  return StmtError();
7802 
7803  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
7804  !SubStmtChanged)
7805  return S;
7806 
7807  return getDerived().RebuildCompoundStmt(S->getLBracLoc(),
7808  Statements,
7809  S->getRBracLoc(),
7810  IsStmtExpr);
7811 }
7812 
7813 template<typename Derived>
7814 StmtResult
7815 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCaseStmt(CaseStmt *S) {
7816  ExprResult LHS, RHS;
7817  {
7818  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
7819  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
7820 
7821  // Transform the left-hand case value.
7822  LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getLHS());
7823  LHS = SemaRef.ActOnCaseExpr(S->getCaseLoc(), LHS);
7824  if (LHS.isInvalid())
7825  return StmtError();
7826 
7827  // Transform the right-hand case value (for the GNU case-range extension).
7828  RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getRHS());
7829  RHS = SemaRef.ActOnCaseExpr(S->getCaseLoc(), RHS);
7830  if (RHS.isInvalid())
7831  return StmtError();
7832  }
7833 
7834  // Build the case statement.
7835  // Case statements are always rebuilt so that they will attached to their
7836  // transformed switch statement.
7837  StmtResult Case = getDerived().RebuildCaseStmt(S->getCaseLoc(),
7838  LHS.get(),
7839  S->getEllipsisLoc(),
7840  RHS.get(),
7841  S->getColonLoc());
7842  if (Case.isInvalid())
7843  return StmtError();
7844 
7845  // Transform the statement following the case
7846  StmtResult SubStmt =
7847  getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getSubStmt());
7848  if (SubStmt.isInvalid())
7849  return StmtError();
7850 
7851  // Attach the body to the case statement
7852  return getDerived().RebuildCaseStmtBody(Case.get(), SubStmt.get());
7853 }
7854 
7855 template <typename Derived>
7856 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDefaultStmt(DefaultStmt *S) {
7857  // Transform the statement following the default case
7858  StmtResult SubStmt =
7859  getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getSubStmt());
7860  if (SubStmt.isInvalid())
7861  return StmtError();
7862 
7863  // Default statements are always rebuilt
7864  return getDerived().RebuildDefaultStmt(S->getDefaultLoc(), S->getColonLoc(),
7865  SubStmt.get());
7866 }
7867 
7868 template<typename Derived>
7869 StmtResult
7870 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformLabelStmt(LabelStmt *S, StmtDiscardKind SDK) {
7871  StmtResult SubStmt = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getSubStmt(), SDK);
7872  if (SubStmt.isInvalid())
7873  return StmtError();
7874 
7875  Decl *LD = getDerived().TransformDecl(S->getDecl()->getLocation(),
7876  S->getDecl());
7877  if (!LD)
7878  return StmtError();
7879 
7880  // If we're transforming "in-place" (we're not creating new local
7881  // declarations), assume we're replacing the old label statement
7882  // and clear out the reference to it.
7883  if (LD == S->getDecl())
7884  S->getDecl()->setStmt(nullptr);
7885 
7886  // FIXME: Pass the real colon location in.
7887  return getDerived().RebuildLabelStmt(S->getIdentLoc(),
7888  cast<LabelDecl>(LD), SourceLocation(),
7889  SubStmt.get());
7890 }

7892 template <typename Derived>
7893 const Attr *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAttr(const Attr *R) {
7894  if (!R)
7895  return R;
7896 
7897  switch (R->getKind()) {
7898 // Transform attributes by calling TransformXXXAttr.
7899 #define ATTR(X) \
7900  case attr::X: \
7901  return getDerived().Transform##X##Attr(cast<X##Attr>(R));
7902 #include "clang/Basic/AttrList.inc"
7903  }
7904  return R;
7905 }
7906 
7907 template <typename Derived>
7908 const Attr *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformStmtAttr(const Stmt *OrigS,
7909  const Stmt *InstS,
7910  const Attr *R) {
7911  if (!R)
7912  return R;
7913 
7914  switch (R->getKind()) {
7915 // Transform attributes by calling TransformStmtXXXAttr.
7916 #define ATTR(X) \
7917  case attr::X: \
7918  return getDerived().TransformStmt##X##Attr(OrigS, InstS, cast<X##Attr>(R));
7919 #include "clang/Basic/AttrList.inc"
7920  }
7921  return TransformAttr(R);
7922 }
7923 
7924 template <typename Derived>
7925 StmtResult
7926 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAttributedStmt(AttributedStmt *S,
7927  StmtDiscardKind SDK) {
7928  StmtResult SubStmt = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getSubStmt(), SDK);
7929  if (SubStmt.isInvalid())
7930  return StmtError();
7931 
7932  bool AttrsChanged = false;
7933  SmallVector<const Attr *, 1> Attrs;
7934 
7935  // Visit attributes and keep track if any are transformed.
7936  for (const auto *I : S->getAttrs()) {
7937  const Attr *R =
7938  getDerived().TransformStmtAttr(S->getSubStmt(), SubStmt.get(), I);
7939  AttrsChanged |= (I != R);
7940  if (R)
7941  Attrs.push_back(R);
7942  }
7943 
7944  if (SubStmt.get() == S->getSubStmt() && !AttrsChanged)
7945  return S;
7946 
7947  // If transforming the attributes failed for all of the attributes in the
7948  // statement, don't make an AttributedStmt without attributes.
7949  if (Attrs.empty())
7950  return SubStmt;
7951 
7952  return getDerived().RebuildAttributedStmt(S->getAttrLoc(), Attrs,
7953  SubStmt.get());
7954 }
7955 
7956 template<typename Derived>
7957 StmtResult
7958 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformIfStmt(IfStmt *S) {
7959  // Transform the initialization statement
7960  StmtResult Init = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getInit());
7961  if (Init.isInvalid())
7962  return StmtError();
7963 
7964  Sema::ConditionResult Cond;
7965  if (!S->isConsteval()) {
7966  // Transform the condition
7967  Cond = getDerived().TransformCondition(
7968  S->getIfLoc(), S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond(),
7969  S->isConstexpr() ? Sema::ConditionKind::ConstexprIf
7970  : Sema::ConditionKind::Boolean);
7971  if (Cond.isInvalid())
7972  return StmtError();
7973  }
7974 
7975  // If this is a constexpr if, determine which arm we should instantiate.
7976  std::optional<bool> ConstexprConditionValue;
7977  if (S->isConstexpr())
7978  ConstexprConditionValue = Cond.getKnownValue();
7979 
7980  // Transform the "then" branch.
7981  StmtResult Then;
7982  if (!ConstexprConditionValue || *ConstexprConditionValue) {
7983  Then = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getThen());
7984  if (Then.isInvalid())
7985  return StmtError();
7986  } else {
7987  // Discarded branch is replaced with empty CompoundStmt so we can keep
7988  // proper source location for start and end of original branch, so
7989  // subsequent transformations like CoverageMapping work properly
7990  Then = new (getSema().Context)
7991  CompoundStmt(S->getThen()->getBeginLoc(), S->getThen()->getEndLoc());
7992  }
7993 
7994  // Transform the "else" branch.
7995  StmtResult Else;
7996  if (!ConstexprConditionValue || !*ConstexprConditionValue) {
7997  Else = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getElse());
7998  if (Else.isInvalid())
7999  return StmtError();
8000  } else if (S->getElse() && ConstexprConditionValue &&
8001  *ConstexprConditionValue) {
8002  // Same thing here as with <then> branch, we are discarding it, we can't
8003  // replace it with NULL nor NullStmt as we need to keep for source location
8004  // range, for CoverageMapping
8005  Else = new (getSema().Context)
8006  CompoundStmt(S->getElse()->getBeginLoc(), S->getElse()->getEndLoc());
8007  }
8008 
8009  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8010  Init.get() == S->getInit() &&
8011  Cond.get() == std::make_pair(S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond()) &&
8012  Then.get() == S->getThen() &&
8013  Else.get() == S->getElse())
8014  return S;
8015 
8016  return getDerived().RebuildIfStmt(
8017  S->getIfLoc(), S->getStatementKind(), S->getLParenLoc(), Cond,
8018  S->getRParenLoc(), Init.get(), Then.get(), S->getElseLoc(), Else.get());
8019 }
8020 
8021 template<typename Derived>
8022 StmtResult
8023 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformSwitchStmt(SwitchStmt *S) {
8024  // Transform the initialization statement
8025  StmtResult Init = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getInit());
8026  if (Init.isInvalid())
8027  return StmtError();
8028 
8029  // Transform the condition.
8030  Sema::ConditionResult Cond = getDerived().TransformCondition(
8031  S->getSwitchLoc(), S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond(),
8032  Sema::ConditionKind::Switch);
8033  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8034  return StmtError();
8035 
8036  // Rebuild the switch statement.
8037  StmtResult Switch =
8038  getDerived().RebuildSwitchStmtStart(S->getSwitchLoc(), S->getLParenLoc(),
8039  Init.get(), Cond, S->getRParenLoc());
8040  if (Switch.isInvalid())
8041  return StmtError();
8042 
8043  // Transform the body of the switch statement.
8044  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8045  if (Body.isInvalid())
8046  return StmtError();
8047 
8048  // Complete the switch statement.
8049  return getDerived().RebuildSwitchStmtBody(S->getSwitchLoc(), Switch.get(),
8050  Body.get());
8051 }

8053 template<typename Derived>
8054 StmtResult
8055 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformWhileStmt(WhileStmt *S) {
8056  // Transform the condition
8057  Sema::ConditionResult Cond = getDerived().TransformCondition(
8058  S->getWhileLoc(), S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond(),
8059  Sema::ConditionKind::Boolean);
8060  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8061  return StmtError();
8062 
8063  // Transform the body
8064  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8065  if (Body.isInvalid())
8066  return StmtError();
8067 
8068  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8069  Cond.get() == std::make_pair(S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond()) &&
8070  Body.get() == S->getBody())
8071  return Owned(S);
8072 
8073  return getDerived().RebuildWhileStmt(S->getWhileLoc(), S->getLParenLoc(),
8074  Cond, S->getRParenLoc(), Body.get());
8075 }

8077 template<typename Derived>
8078 StmtResult
8079 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDoStmt(DoStmt *S) {
8080  // Transform the body
8081  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8082  if (Body.isInvalid())
8083  return StmtError();
8084 
8085  // Transform the condition
8086  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getCond());
8087  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8088  return StmtError();
8089 
8090  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8091  Cond.get() == S->getCond() &&
8092  Body.get() == S->getBody())
8093  return S;
8094 
8095  return getDerived().RebuildDoStmt(S->getDoLoc(), Body.get(), S->getWhileLoc(),
8096  /*FIXME:*/S->getWhileLoc(), Cond.get(),
8097  S->getRParenLoc());
8098 }

8100 template<typename Derived>
8101 StmtResult
8102 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformForStmt(ForStmt *S) {
8103  if (getSema().getLangOpts().OpenMP)
8104  getSema().OpenMP().startOpenMPLoop();
8105 
8106  // Transform the initialization statement
8107  StmtResult Init = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getInit());
8108  if (Init.isInvalid())
8109  return StmtError();
8110 
8111  // In OpenMP loop region loop control variable must be captured and be
8112  // private. Perform analysis of first part (if any).
8113  if (getSema().getLangOpts().OpenMP && Init.isUsable())
8114  getSema().OpenMP().ActOnOpenMPLoopInitialization(S->getForLoc(),
8115  Init.get());
8116 
8117  // Transform the condition
8118  Sema::ConditionResult Cond = getDerived().TransformCondition(
8119  S->getForLoc(), S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond(),
8120  Sema::ConditionKind::Boolean);
8121  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8122  return StmtError();
8123 
8124  // Transform the increment
8125  ExprResult Inc = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getInc());
8126  if (Inc.isInvalid())
8127  return StmtError();
8128 
8129  Sema::FullExprArg FullInc(getSema().MakeFullDiscardedValueExpr(Inc.get()));
8130  if (S->getInc() && !FullInc.get())
8131  return StmtError();
8132 
8133  // Transform the body
8134  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8135  if (Body.isInvalid())
8136  return StmtError();
8137 
8138  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8139  Init.get() == S->getInit() &&
8140  Cond.get() == std::make_pair(S->getConditionVariable(), S->getCond()) &&
8141  Inc.get() == S->getInc() &&
8142  Body.get() == S->getBody())
8143  return S;
8144 
8145  return getDerived().RebuildForStmt(S->getForLoc(), S->getLParenLoc(),
8146  Init.get(), Cond, FullInc,
8147  S->getRParenLoc(), Body.get());
8148 }

8152 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformGotoStmt(GotoStmt *S) {

8154  S->getLabel());
8155  if (!LD)
8156  return StmtError();
8157 
8158  // Goto statements must always be rebuilt, to resolve the label.
8159  return getDerived().RebuildGotoStmt(S->getGotoLoc(), S->getLabelLoc(),
8160  cast<LabelDecl>(LD));
8161 }

8163 template<typename Derived>
8164 StmtResult
8165 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformIndirectGotoStmt(IndirectGotoStmt *S) {

8169  Target = SemaRef.MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Target.get());

8171  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8172  Target.get() == S->getTarget())
8173  return S;
8174 
8175  return getDerived().RebuildIndirectGotoStmt(S->getGotoLoc(), S->getStarLoc(),
8176  Target.get());
8177 }

8191 template<typename Derived>
8192 StmtResult
8193 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformReturnStmt(ReturnStmt *S) {
8194  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformInitializer(S->getRetValue(),
8195  /*NotCopyInit*/false);
8196  if (Result.isInvalid())
8197  return StmtError();

8201  return getDerived().RebuildReturnStmt(S->getReturnLoc(), Result.get());

8204 template<typename Derived>
8205 StmtResult
8206 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDeclStmt(DeclStmt *S) {
8207  bool DeclChanged = false;
8208  SmallVector<Decl *, 4> Decls;
8209  for (auto *D : S->decls()) {
8210  Decl *Transformed = getDerived().TransformDefinition(D->getLocation(), D);
8211  if (!Transformed)
8212  return StmtError();
8213 
8214  if (Transformed != D)
8215  DeclChanged = true;
8216 
8217  Decls.push_back(Transformed);
8218  }
8219 
8220  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !DeclChanged)
8221  return S;
8222 
8223  return getDerived().RebuildDeclStmt(Decls, S->getBeginLoc(), S->getEndLoc());
8224 }

8226 template<typename Derived>
8227 StmtResult
8228 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformGCCAsmStmt(GCCAsmStmt *S) {
8229 
8230  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Constraints;
8231  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Exprs;
8232  SmallVector<IdentifierInfo *, 4> Names;
8233 
8234  ExprResult AsmString;
8235  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Clobbers;
8236 
8237  bool ExprsChanged = false;
8238 
8239  // Go through the outputs.
8240  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumOutputs(); I != E; ++I) {
8241  Names.push_back(S->getOutputIdentifier(I));
8242 
8243  // No need to transform the constraint literal.
8244  Constraints.push_back(S->getOutputConstraintLiteral(I));
8245 
8246  // Transform the output expr.
8247  Expr *OutputExpr = S->getOutputExpr(I);
8248  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformExpr(OutputExpr);
8249  if (Result.isInvalid())
8250  return StmtError();
8251 
8252  ExprsChanged |= Result.get() != OutputExpr;
8253 
8254  Exprs.push_back(Result.get());
8255  }
8256 
8257  // Go through the inputs.
8258  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumInputs(); I != E; ++I) {
8259  Names.push_back(S->getInputIdentifier(I));
8260 
8261  // No need to transform the constraint literal.
8262  Constraints.push_back(S->getInputConstraintLiteral(I));
8263 
8264  // Transform the input expr.
8265  Expr *InputExpr = S->getInputExpr(I);
8266  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformExpr(InputExpr);
8267  if (Result.isInvalid())
8268  return StmtError();
8269 
8270  ExprsChanged |= Result.get() != InputExpr;
8271 
8272  Exprs.push_back(Result.get());
8273  }
8274 
8275  // Go through the Labels.
8276  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumLabels(); I != E; ++I) {
8277  Names.push_back(S->getLabelIdentifier(I));
8278 
8279  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getLabelExpr(I));
8280  if (Result.isInvalid())
8281  return StmtError();
8282  ExprsChanged |= Result.get() != S->getLabelExpr(I);
8283  Exprs.push_back(Result.get());
8284  }
8285  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !ExprsChanged)
8286  return S;
8287 
8288  // Go through the clobbers.
8289  for (unsigned I = 0, E = S->getNumClobbers(); I != E; ++I)
8290  Clobbers.push_back(S->getClobberStringLiteral(I));
8291 
8292  // No need to transform the asm string literal.
8293  AsmString = S->getAsmString();
8294  return getDerived().RebuildGCCAsmStmt(S->getAsmLoc(), S->isSimple(),
8295  S->isVolatile(), S->getNumOutputs(),
8296  S->getNumInputs(), Names.data(),
8297  Constraints, Exprs, AsmString.get(),
8298  Clobbers, S->getNumLabels(),
8299  S->getRParenLoc());
8300 }
8301 
8302 template<typename Derived>
8303 StmtResult
8304 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMSAsmStmt(MSAsmStmt *S) {
8305  ArrayRef<Token> AsmToks = llvm::ArrayRef(S->getAsmToks(), S->getNumAsmToks());
8306 
8307  bool HadError = false, HadChange = false;
8308 
8309  ArrayRef<Expr*> SrcExprs = S->getAllExprs();
8310  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> TransformedExprs;
8311  TransformedExprs.reserve(SrcExprs.size());
8312  for (unsigned i = 0, e = SrcExprs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
8313  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformExpr(SrcExprs[i]);
8314  if (!Result.isUsable()) {
8315  HadError = true;
8316  } else {
8317  HadChange |= (Result.get() != SrcExprs[i]);
8318  TransformedExprs.push_back(Result.get());
8319  }
8320  }
8321 
8322  if (HadError) return StmtError();
8323  if (!HadChange && !getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
8324  return Owned(S);
8325 
8326  return getDerived().RebuildMSAsmStmt(S->getAsmLoc(), S->getLBraceLoc(),
8327  AsmToks, S->getAsmString(),
8328  S->getNumOutputs(), S->getNumInputs(),
8329  S->getAllConstraints(), S->getClobbers(),
8330  TransformedExprs, S->getEndLoc());
8331 }
8332 
8333 // C++ Coroutines
8334 template<typename Derived>
8335 StmtResult
8336 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCoroutineBodyStmt(CoroutineBodyStmt *S) {
8337  auto *ScopeInfo = SemaRef.getCurFunction();
8338  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext);
8339  assert(FD && ScopeInfo && !ScopeInfo->CoroutinePromise &&
8340  ScopeInfo->NeedsCoroutineSuspends &&
8341  ScopeInfo->CoroutineSuspends.first == nullptr &&
8342  ScopeInfo->CoroutineSuspends.second == nullptr &&
8343  "expected clean scope info");
8344 
8345  // Set that we have (possibly-invalid) suspend points before we do anything
8346  // that may fail.
8347  ScopeInfo->setNeedsCoroutineSuspends(false);
8348 
8349  // We re-build the coroutine promise object (and the coroutine parameters its
8350  // type and constructor depend on) based on the types used in our current
8351  // function. We must do so, and set it on the current FunctionScopeInfo,
8352  // before attempting to transform the other parts of the coroutine body
8353  // statement, such as the implicit suspend statements (because those
8354  // statements reference the FunctionScopeInfo::CoroutinePromise).
8355  if (!SemaRef.buildCoroutineParameterMoves(FD->getLocation()))
8356  return StmtError();
8357  auto *Promise = SemaRef.buildCoroutinePromise(FD->getLocation());
8358  if (!Promise)
8359  return StmtError();
8360  getDerived().transformedLocalDecl(S->getPromiseDecl(), {Promise});
8361  ScopeInfo->CoroutinePromise = Promise;
8362 
8363  // Transform the implicit coroutine statements constructed using dependent
8364  // types during the previous parse: initial and final suspensions, the return
8365  // object, and others. We also transform the coroutine function's body.
8366  StmtResult InitSuspend = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getInitSuspendStmt());
8367  if (InitSuspend.isInvalid())
8368  return StmtError();
8369  StmtResult FinalSuspend =
8370  getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getFinalSuspendStmt());
8371  if (FinalSuspend.isInvalid() ||
8372  !SemaRef.checkFinalSuspendNoThrow(FinalSuspend.get()))
8373  return StmtError();
8374  ScopeInfo->setCoroutineSuspends(InitSuspend.get(), FinalSuspend.get());
8375  assert(isa<Expr>(InitSuspend.get()) && isa<Expr>(FinalSuspend.get()));
8376 
8377  StmtResult BodyRes = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8378  if (BodyRes.isInvalid())
8379  return StmtError();
8380 
8381  CoroutineStmtBuilder Builder(SemaRef, *FD, *ScopeInfo, BodyRes.get());
8382  if (Builder.isInvalid())
8383  return StmtError();
8384 
8385  Expr *ReturnObject = S->getReturnValueInit();
8386  assert(ReturnObject && "the return object is expected to be valid");
8387  ExprResult Res = getDerived().TransformInitializer(ReturnObject,
8388  /*NoCopyInit*/ false);
8389  if (Res.isInvalid())
8390  return StmtError();
8391  Builder.ReturnValue = Res.get();
8392 
8393  // If during the previous parse the coroutine still had a dependent promise
8394  // statement, we may need to build some implicit coroutine statements
8395  // (such as exception and fallthrough handlers) for the first time.
8396  if (S->hasDependentPromiseType()) {
8397  // We can only build these statements, however, if the current promise type
8398  // is not dependent.
8399  if (!Promise->getType()->isDependentType()) {
8400  assert(!S->getFallthroughHandler() && !S->getExceptionHandler() &&
8401  !S->getReturnStmtOnAllocFailure() && !S->getDeallocate() &&
8402  "these nodes should not have been built yet");
8403  if (!Builder.buildDependentStatements())
8404  return StmtError();
8405  }
8406  } else {
8407  if (auto *OnFallthrough = S->getFallthroughHandler()) {
8408  StmtResult Res = getDerived().TransformStmt(OnFallthrough);
8409  if (Res.isInvalid())
8410  return StmtError();
8411  Builder.OnFallthrough = Res.get();
8412  }
8413 
8414  if (auto *OnException = S->getExceptionHandler()) {
8415  StmtResult Res = getDerived().TransformStmt(OnException);
8416  if (Res.isInvalid())
8417  return StmtError();
8418  Builder.OnException = Res.get();
8419  }
8420 
8421  if (auto *OnAllocFailure = S->getReturnStmtOnAllocFailure()) {
8422  StmtResult Res = getDerived().TransformStmt(OnAllocFailure);
8423  if (Res.isInvalid())
8424  return StmtError();
8425  Builder.ReturnStmtOnAllocFailure = Res.get();
8426  }
8427 
8428  // Transform any additional statements we may have already built
8429  assert(S->getAllocate() && S->getDeallocate() &&
8430  "allocation and deallocation calls must already be built");
8431  ExprResult AllocRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getAllocate());
8432  if (AllocRes.isInvalid())
8433  return StmtError();
8434  Builder.Allocate = AllocRes.get();
8435 
8436  ExprResult DeallocRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getDeallocate());
8437  if (DeallocRes.isInvalid())
8438  return StmtError();
8439  Builder.Deallocate = DeallocRes.get();
8440 
8441  if (auto *ResultDecl = S->getResultDecl()) {
8442  StmtResult Res = getDerived().TransformStmt(ResultDecl);
8443  if (Res.isInvalid())
8444  return StmtError();
8445  Builder.ResultDecl = Res.get();
8446  }
8447 
8448  if (auto *ReturnStmt = S->getReturnStmt()) {
8449  StmtResult Res = getDerived().TransformStmt(ReturnStmt);
8450  if (Res.isInvalid())
8451  return StmtError();
8452  Builder.ReturnStmt = Res.get();
8453  }
8454  }
8455 
8456  return getDerived().RebuildCoroutineBodyStmt(Builder);
8457 }
8458 
8459 template<typename Derived>
8460 StmtResult
8461 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCoreturnStmt(CoreturnStmt *S) {
8462  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformInitializer(S->getOperand(),
8463  /*NotCopyInit*/false);
8464  if (Result.isInvalid())
8465  return StmtError();
8466 
8467  // Always rebuild; we don't know if this needs to be injected into a new
8468  // context or if the promise type has changed.
8469  return getDerived().RebuildCoreturnStmt(S->getKeywordLoc(), Result.get(),
8470  S->isImplicit());
8471 }

8473 template <typename Derived>
8474 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCoawaitExpr(CoawaitExpr *E) {
8475  ExprResult Operand = getDerived().TransformInitializer(E->getOperand(),
8476  /*NotCopyInit*/ false);
8477  if (Operand.isInvalid())
8478  return ExprError();
8479 
8480  // Rebuild the common-expr from the operand rather than transforming it
8481  // separately.
8482 
8483  // FIXME: getCurScope() should not be used during template instantiation.
8484  // We should pick up the set of unqualified lookup results for operator
8485  // co_await during the initial parse.
8486  ExprResult Lookup = getSema().BuildOperatorCoawaitLookupExpr(
8487  getSema().getCurScope(), E->getKeywordLoc());
8488 
8489  // Always rebuild; we don't know if this needs to be injected into a new
8490  // context or if the promise type has changed.
8491  return getDerived().RebuildCoawaitExpr(
8492  E->getKeywordLoc(), Operand.get(),
8493  cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(Lookup.get()), E->isImplicit());
8494 }

8500  /*NotCopyInit*/ false);

8502  return ExprError();

8508  return ExprError();

8510  // Always rebuild; we don't know if this needs to be injected into a new
8511  // context or if the promise type has changed.

8530 // Objective-C Statements.
8531 
8532 template<typename Derived>
8533 StmtResult
8534 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCAtTryStmt(ObjCAtTryStmt *S) {
8535  // Transform the body of the @try.
8536  StmtResult TryBody = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getTryBody());
8537  if (TryBody.isInvalid())
8538  return StmtError();
8539 
8540  // Transform the @catch statements (if present).
8541  bool AnyCatchChanged = false;
8542  SmallVector<Stmt*, 8> CatchStmts;
8543  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumCatchStmts(); I != N; ++I) {
8544  StmtResult Catch = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getCatchStmt(I));
8545  if (Catch.isInvalid())
8546  return StmtError();
8547  if (Catch.get() != S->getCatchStmt(I))
8548  AnyCatchChanged = true;
8549  CatchStmts.push_back(Catch.get());
8550  }
8551 
8552  // Transform the @finally statement (if present).
8553  StmtResult Finally;
8554  if (S->getFinallyStmt()) {
8555  Finally = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getFinallyStmt());
8556  if (Finally.isInvalid())
8557  return StmtError();
8558  }
8559 
8560  // If nothing changed, just retain this statement.
8561  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8562  TryBody.get() == S->getTryBody() &&
8563  !AnyCatchChanged &&
8564  Finally.get() == S->getFinallyStmt())
8565  return S;
8566 
8567  // Build a new statement.
8568  return getDerived().RebuildObjCAtTryStmt(S->getAtTryLoc(), TryBody.get(),
8569  CatchStmts, Finally.get());
8570 }
8571 
8572 template<typename Derived>
8573 StmtResult
8574 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCAtCatchStmt(ObjCAtCatchStmt *S) {
8575  // Transform the @catch parameter, if there is one.
8576  VarDecl *Var = nullptr;
8577  if (VarDecl *FromVar = S->getCatchParamDecl()) {
8578  TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = nullptr;
8579  if (FromVar->getTypeSourceInfo()) {
8580  TSInfo = getDerived().TransformType(FromVar->getTypeSourceInfo());
8581  if (!TSInfo)
8582  return StmtError();
8583  }
8584 
8585  QualType T;
8586  if (TSInfo)
8587  T = TSInfo->getType();
8588  else {
8589  T = getDerived().TransformType(FromVar->getType());
8590  if (T.isNull())
8591  return StmtError();
8592  }
8593 
8594  Var = getDerived().RebuildObjCExceptionDecl(FromVar, TSInfo, T);
8595  if (!Var)
8596  return StmtError();
8597  }
8598 
8599  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getCatchBody());
8600  if (Body.isInvalid())
8601  return StmtError();
8602 
8603  return getDerived().RebuildObjCAtCatchStmt(S->getAtCatchLoc(),
8604  S->getRParenLoc(),
8605  Var, Body.get());
8606 }

8608 template<typename Derived>
8609 StmtResult
8610 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCAtFinallyStmt(ObjCAtFinallyStmt *S) {
8611  // Transform the body.
8612  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getFinallyBody());
8613  if (Body.isInvalid())
8614  return StmtError();
8615 
8616  // If nothing changed, just retain this statement.
8617  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8618  Body.get() == S->getFinallyBody())
8619  return S;
8620 
8621  // Build a new statement.
8622  return getDerived().RebuildObjCAtFinallyStmt(S->getAtFinallyLoc(),
8623  Body.get());
8624 }

8643 template<typename Derived>
8644 StmtResult
8645 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCAtSynchronizedStmt(
8646  ObjCAtSynchronizedStmt *S) {
8647  // Transform the object we are locking.
8648  ExprResult Object = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getSynchExpr());
8649  if (Object.isInvalid())
8650  return StmtError();
8651  Object =
8652  getDerived().RebuildObjCAtSynchronizedOperand(S->getAtSynchronizedLoc(),
8653  Object.get());
8654  if (Object.isInvalid())
8655  return StmtError();
8656 
8657  // Transform the body.
8658  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getSynchBody());
8659  if (Body.isInvalid())
8660  return StmtError();
8661 
8662  // If nothing change, just retain the current statement.
8663  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8664  Object.get() == S->getSynchExpr() &&
8665  Body.get() == S->getSynchBody())
8666  return S;
8667 
8668  // Build a new statement.
8669  return getDerived().RebuildObjCAtSynchronizedStmt(S->getAtSynchronizedLoc(),
8670  Object.get(), Body.get());
8671 }

8679  if (Body.isInvalid())
8680  return StmtError();

8683  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8684  Body.get() == S->getSubStmt())
8685  return S;
8686 
8687  // Build a new statement.

8692 template<typename Derived>
8693 StmtResult
8694 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCForCollectionStmt(
8695  ObjCForCollectionStmt *S) {
8696  // Transform the element statement.
8697  StmtResult Element =
8698  getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getElement(), SDK_NotDiscarded);
8699  if (Element.isInvalid())
8700  return StmtError();
8701 
8702  // Transform the collection expression.
8703  ExprResult Collection = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getCollection());
8704  if (Collection.isInvalid())
8705  return StmtError();
8706 
8707  // Transform the body.
8708  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8709  if (Body.isInvalid())
8710  return StmtError();
8711 
8712  // If nothing changed, just retain this statement.
8713  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8714  Element.get() == S->getElement() &&
8715  Collection.get() == S->getCollection() &&
8716  Body.get() == S->getBody())
8717  return S;
8718 
8719  // Build a new statement.
8720  return getDerived().RebuildObjCForCollectionStmt(S->getForLoc(),
8721  Element.get(),
8722  Collection.get(),
8723  S->getRParenLoc(),
8724  Body.get());
8725 }

8727 template <typename Derived>
8728 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXCatchStmt(CXXCatchStmt *S) {
8729  // Transform the exception declaration, if any.
8730  VarDecl *Var = nullptr;
8731  if (VarDecl *ExceptionDecl = S->getExceptionDecl()) {
8732  TypeSourceInfo *T =
8733  getDerived().TransformType(ExceptionDecl->getTypeSourceInfo());
8734  if (!T)
8735  return StmtError();
8736 
8737  Var = getDerived().RebuildExceptionDecl(
8738  ExceptionDecl, T, ExceptionDecl->getInnerLocStart(),
8739  ExceptionDecl->getLocation(), ExceptionDecl->getIdentifier());
8740  if (!Var || Var->isInvalidDecl())
8741  return StmtError();
8742  }
8743 
8744  // Transform the actual exception handler.
8745  StmtResult Handler = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getHandlerBlock());
8746  if (Handler.isInvalid())
8747  return StmtError();
8748 
8749  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !Var &&
8750  Handler.get() == S->getHandlerBlock())
8751  return S;
8752 
8753  return getDerived().RebuildCXXCatchStmt(S->getCatchLoc(), Var, Handler.get());
8754 }
8755 
8756 template <typename Derived>
8757 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXTryStmt(CXXTryStmt *S) {
8758  // Transform the try block itself.
8759  StmtResult TryBlock = getDerived().TransformCompoundStmt(S->getTryBlock());
8760  if (TryBlock.isInvalid())
8761  return StmtError();
8762 
8763  // Transform the handlers.
8764  bool HandlerChanged = false;
8765  SmallVector<Stmt *, 8> Handlers;
8766  for (unsigned I = 0, N = S->getNumHandlers(); I != N; ++I) {
8767  StmtResult Handler = getDerived().TransformCXXCatchStmt(S->getHandler(I));
8768  if (Handler.isInvalid())
8769  return StmtError();
8770 
8771  HandlerChanged = HandlerChanged || Handler.get() != S->getHandler(I);
8772  Handlers.push_back(Handler.getAs<Stmt>());
8773  }
8774 
8775  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && TryBlock.get() == S->getTryBlock() &&
8776  !HandlerChanged)
8777  return S;
8778 
8779  return getDerived().RebuildCXXTryStmt(S->getTryLoc(), TryBlock.get(),
8780  Handlers);
8781 }
8782 
8783 template<typename Derived>
8784 StmtResult
8785 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXForRangeStmt(CXXForRangeStmt *S) {
8786  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ForRangeInitContext(
8787  getSema(), Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated,
8788  /*LambdaContextDecl=*/nullptr,
8789  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContextRecord::EK_Other,
8790  getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus23);
8791 
8792  // P2718R0 - Lifetime extension in range-based for loops.
8793  if (getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus23) {
8794  auto &LastRecord = getSema().ExprEvalContexts.back();
8795  LastRecord.InLifetimeExtendingContext = true;
8796  }
8797  StmtResult Init =
8798  S->getInit() ? getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getInit()) : StmtResult();
8799  if (Init.isInvalid())
8800  return StmtError();
8801 
8802  StmtResult Range = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getRangeStmt());
8803  if (Range.isInvalid())
8804  return StmtError();
8805 
8806  // Before c++23, ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps should be empty.
8807  assert(getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus23 ||
8808  getSema().ExprEvalContexts.back().ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps.empty());
8809  auto ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps =
8810  getSema().ExprEvalContexts.back().ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps;
8811 
8812  StmtResult Begin = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBeginStmt());
8813  if (Begin.isInvalid())
8814  return StmtError();
8815  StmtResult End = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getEndStmt());
8816  if (End.isInvalid())
8817  return StmtError();
8818 
8819  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getCond());
8820  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8821  return StmtError();
8822  if (Cond.get())
8823  Cond = SemaRef.CheckBooleanCondition(S->getColonLoc(), Cond.get());
8824  if (Cond.isInvalid())
8825  return StmtError();
8826  if (Cond.get())
8827  Cond = SemaRef.MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Cond.get());
8828 
8829  ExprResult Inc = getDerived().TransformExpr(S->getInc());
8830  if (Inc.isInvalid())
8831  return StmtError();
8832  if (Inc.get())
8833  Inc = SemaRef.MaybeCreateExprWithCleanups(Inc.get());
8834 
8835  StmtResult LoopVar = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getLoopVarStmt());
8836  if (LoopVar.isInvalid())
8837  return StmtError();
8838 
8839  StmtResult NewStmt = S;
8840  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() ||
8841  Init.get() != S->getInit() ||
8842  Range.get() != S->getRangeStmt() ||
8843  Begin.get() != S->getBeginStmt() ||
8844  End.get() != S->getEndStmt() ||
8845  Cond.get() != S->getCond() ||
8846  Inc.get() != S->getInc() ||
8847  LoopVar.get() != S->getLoopVarStmt()) {
8848  NewStmt = getDerived().RebuildCXXForRangeStmt(
8849  S->getForLoc(), S->getCoawaitLoc(), Init.get(), S->getColonLoc(),
8850  Range.get(), Begin.get(), End.get(), Cond.get(), Inc.get(),
8851  LoopVar.get(), S->getRParenLoc(), ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps);
8852  if (NewStmt.isInvalid() && LoopVar.get() != S->getLoopVarStmt()) {
8853  // Might not have attached any initializer to the loop variable.
8854  getSema().ActOnInitializerError(
8855  cast<DeclStmt>(LoopVar.get())->getSingleDecl());
8856  return StmtError();
8857  }
8858  }
8859 
8860  StmtResult Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getBody());
8861  if (Body.isInvalid())
8862  return StmtError();
8863 
8864  // Body has changed but we didn't rebuild the for-range statement. Rebuild
8865  // it now so we have a new statement to attach the body to.
8866  if (Body.get() != S->getBody() && NewStmt.get() == S) {
8867  NewStmt = getDerived().RebuildCXXForRangeStmt(
8868  S->getForLoc(), S->getCoawaitLoc(), Init.get(), S->getColonLoc(),
8869  Range.get(), Begin.get(), End.get(), Cond.get(), Inc.get(),
8870  LoopVar.get(), S->getRParenLoc(), ForRangeLifetimeExtendTemps);
8871  if (NewStmt.isInvalid())
8872  return StmtError();
8873  }
8874 
8875  if (NewStmt.get() == S)
8876  return S;
8877 
8878  return FinishCXXForRangeStmt(NewStmt.get(), Body.get());
8879 }
8880 
8881 template<typename Derived>
8882 StmtResult
8883 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMSDependentExistsStmt(
8884  MSDependentExistsStmt *S) {
8885  // Transform the nested-name-specifier, if any.
8886  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
8887  if (S->getQualifierLoc()) {
8888  QualifierLoc
8889  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(S->getQualifierLoc());
8890  if (!QualifierLoc)
8891  return StmtError();
8892  }
8893 
8894  // Transform the declaration name.
8895  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = S->getNameInfo();
8896  if (NameInfo.getName()) {
8897  NameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo);
8898  if (!NameInfo.getName())
8899  return StmtError();
8900  }
8901 
8902  // Check whether anything changed.
8903  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
8904  QualifierLoc == S->getQualifierLoc() &&
8905  NameInfo.getName() == S->getNameInfo().getName())
8906  return S;
8907 
8908  // Determine whether this name exists, if we can.
8909  CXXScopeSpec SS;
8910  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
8911  bool Dependent = false;
8912  switch (getSema().CheckMicrosoftIfExistsSymbol(/*S=*/nullptr, SS, NameInfo)) {
8913  case Sema::IER_Exists:
8914  if (S->isIfExists())
8915  break;
8916 
8917  return new (getSema().Context) NullStmt(S->getKeywordLoc());
8918 
8919  case Sema::IER_DoesNotExist:
8920  if (S->isIfNotExists())
8921  break;
8922 
8923  return new (getSema().Context) NullStmt(S->getKeywordLoc());
8924 
8925  case Sema::IER_Dependent:
8926  Dependent = true;
8927  break;
8928 
8929  case Sema::IER_Error:
8930  return StmtError();
8931  }
8932 
8933  // We need to continue with the instantiation, so do so now.
8934  StmtResult SubStmt = getDerived().TransformCompoundStmt(S->getSubStmt());
8935  if (SubStmt.isInvalid())
8936  return StmtError();
8937 
8938  // If we have resolved the name, just transform to the substatement.
8939  if (!Dependent)
8940  return SubStmt;
8941 
8942  // The name is still dependent, so build a dependent expression again.
8943  return getDerived().RebuildMSDependentExistsStmt(S->getKeywordLoc(),
8944  S->isIfExists(),
8945  QualifierLoc,
8946  NameInfo,
8947  SubStmt.get());
8948 }

8950 template<typename Derived>
8951 ExprResult
8952 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMSPropertyRefExpr(MSPropertyRefExpr *E) {
8953  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
8954  if (E->getQualifierLoc()) {
8955  QualifierLoc
8956  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
8957  if (!QualifierLoc)
8958  return ExprError();
8959  }
8960 
8961  MSPropertyDecl *PD = cast_or_null<MSPropertyDecl>(
8962  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getMemberLoc(), E->getPropertyDecl()));
8963  if (!PD)
8964  return ExprError();
8965 
8966  ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBaseExpr());
8967  if (Base.isInvalid())
8968  return ExprError();
8969 
8970  return new (SemaRef.getASTContext())
8971  MSPropertyRefExpr(Base.get(), PD, E->isArrow(),
8972  SemaRef.getASTContext().PseudoObjectTy, VK_LValue,
8973  QualifierLoc, E->getMemberLoc());
8974 }

9054 template <typename Derived>
9055 StmtResult
9056 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPCanonicalLoop(OMPCanonicalLoop *L) {
9057  // OMPCanonicalLoops are eliminated during transformation, since they will be

9062 
9063 template <typename Derived>
9064 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPExecutableDirective(
9065  OMPExecutableDirective *D) {
9066 
9067  // Transform the clauses
9068  llvm::SmallVector<OMPClause *, 16> TClauses;
9069  ArrayRef<OMPClause *> Clauses = D->clauses();
9070  TClauses.reserve(Clauses.size());
9071  for (ArrayRef<OMPClause *>::iterator I = Clauses.begin(), E = Clauses.end();
9072  I != E; ++I) {
9073  if (*I) {
9074  getDerived().getSema().OpenMP().StartOpenMPClause((*I)->getClauseKind());
9075  OMPClause *Clause = getDerived().TransformOMPClause(*I);
9076  getDerived().getSema().OpenMP().EndOpenMPClause();
9077  if (Clause)
9078  TClauses.push_back(Clause);
9079  } else {
9080  TClauses.push_back(nullptr);
9081  }
9082  }
9083  StmtResult AssociatedStmt;
9084  if (D->hasAssociatedStmt() && D->getAssociatedStmt()) {
9085  getDerived().getSema().OpenMP().ActOnOpenMPRegionStart(
9086  D->getDirectiveKind(),
9087  /*CurScope=*/nullptr);
9088  StmtResult Body;
9089  {
9090  Sema::CompoundScopeRAII CompoundScope(getSema());
9091  Stmt *CS;
9092  if (D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_atomic ||
9093  D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_critical ||
9094  D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_section ||
9095  D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_master)
9096  CS = D->getAssociatedStmt();
9097  else
9098  CS = D->getRawStmt();
9099  Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(CS);
9100  if (Body.isUsable() && isOpenMPLoopDirective(D->getDirectiveKind()) &&
9101  getSema().getLangOpts().OpenMPIRBuilder)
9102  Body = getDerived().RebuildOMPCanonicalLoop(Body.get());
9103  }
9104  AssociatedStmt =
9105  getDerived().getSema().OpenMP().ActOnOpenMPRegionEnd(Body, TClauses);
9106  if (AssociatedStmt.isInvalid()) {
9107  return StmtError();
9108  }
9109  }
9110  if (TClauses.size() != Clauses.size()) {
9111  return StmtError();
9112  }
9113 
9114  // Transform directive name for 'omp critical' directive.
9115  DeclarationNameInfo DirName;
9116  if (D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_critical) {
9117  DirName = cast<OMPCriticalDirective>(D)->getDirectiveName();
9118  DirName = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(DirName);
9119  }
9120  OpenMPDirectiveKind CancelRegion = OMPD_unknown;
9121  if (D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_cancellation_point) {
9122  CancelRegion = cast<OMPCancellationPointDirective>(D)->getCancelRegion();
9123  } else if (D->getDirectiveKind() == OMPD_cancel) {
9124  CancelRegion = cast<OMPCancelDirective>(D)->getCancelRegion();
9125  }
9126 
9127  return getDerived().RebuildOMPExecutableDirective(
9128  D->getDirectiveKind(), DirName, CancelRegion, TClauses,
9129  AssociatedStmt.get(), D->getBeginLoc(), D->getEndLoc(),
9130  D->getMappedDirective());
9131 }

9136  // TODO: Fix This
9137  SemaRef.Diag(D->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_omp_instantiation_not_supported)
9138  << getOpenMPDirectiveName(D->getDirectiveKind());
9139  return StmtError();
9140 }

9935 template <typename Derived>
9936 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPIfClause(OMPIfClause *C) {
9937  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getCondition());
9938  if (Cond.isInvalid())
9939  return nullptr;
9940  return getDerived().RebuildOMPIfClause(
9941  C->getNameModifier(), Cond.get(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
9942  C->getNameModifierLoc(), C->getColonLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9943 }

9947  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getCondition());
9948  if (Cond.isInvalid())
9949  return nullptr;
9950  return getDerived().RebuildOMPFinalClause(Cond.get(), C->getBeginLoc(),
9951  C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9952 }

9994 template <typename Derived>
9995 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPSizesClause(OMPSizesClause *C) {
9996  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> TransformedSizes;
9997  TransformedSizes.reserve(C->getNumSizes());
9998  bool Changed = false;
9999  for (Expr *E : C->getSizesRefs()) {
10000  if (!E) {
10001  TransformedSizes.push_back(nullptr);
10002  continue;
10003  }
10004 
10005  ExprResult T = getDerived().TransformExpr(E);
10006  if (T.isInvalid())
10007  return nullptr;
10008  if (E != T.get())
10009  Changed = true;
10010  TransformedSizes.push_back(T.get());
10011  }
10012 
10013  if (!Changed && !getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
10014  return C;
10015  return RebuildOMPSizesClause(TransformedSizes, C->getBeginLoc(),
10016  C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10017 }
10018 
10019 template <typename Derived>
10020 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPFullClause(OMPFullClause *C) {
10021  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
10022  return C;
10023  return RebuildOMPFullClause(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10024 }
10025 
10026 template <typename Derived>
10027 OMPClause *
10028 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPPartialClause(OMPPartialClause *C) {
10029  ExprResult T = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getFactor());
10030  if (T.isInvalid())
10031  return nullptr;
10032  Expr *Factor = T.get();
10033  bool Changed = Factor != C->getFactor();
10034 
10035  if (!Changed && !getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
10036  return C;
10037  return RebuildOMPPartialClause(Factor, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
10038  C->getEndLoc());
10039 }

10227 template <typename Derived>
10228 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPInitClause(OMPInitClause *C) {
10229  ExprResult IVR = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getInteropVar());
10230  if (IVR.isInvalid())
10231  return nullptr;
10232 
10233  OMPInteropInfo InteropInfo(C->getIsTarget(), C->getIsTargetSync());
10234  InteropInfo.PreferTypes.reserve(C->varlist_size() - 1);
10235  for (Expr *E : llvm::drop_begin(C->varlists())) {
10236  ExprResult ER = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(E));
10237  if (ER.isInvalid())
10238  return nullptr;
10239  InteropInfo.PreferTypes.push_back(ER.get());
10240  }
10241  return getDerived().RebuildOMPInitClause(IVR.get(), InteropInfo,
10242  C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
10243  C->getVarLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10244 }

10252  C->getLParenLoc(), C->getVarLoc(),

10429 template <typename Derived>
10430 OMPClause *
10431 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPReductionClause(OMPReductionClause *C) {
10432  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10433  Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
10434  for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
10435  ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
10436  if (EVar.isInvalid())
10437  return nullptr;
10438  Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
10439  }
10440  CXXScopeSpec ReductionIdScopeSpec;
10441  ReductionIdScopeSpec.Adopt(C->getQualifierLoc());
10442 
10443  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = C->getNameInfo();
10444  if (NameInfo.getName()) {
10445  NameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo);
10446  if (!NameInfo.getName())
10447  return nullptr;
10448  }
10449  // Build a list of all UDR decls with the same names ranged by the Scopes.
10450  // The Scope boundary is a duplication of the previous decl.
10451  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedReductions;
10452  for (auto *E : C->reduction_ops()) {
10453  // Transform all the decls.
10454  if (E) {
10455  auto *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
10456  UnresolvedSet<8> Decls;
10457  for (auto *D : ULE->decls()) {
10458  NamedDecl *InstD =
10459  cast<NamedDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getExprLoc(), D));
10460  Decls.addDecl(InstD, InstD->getAccess());
10461  }
10462  UnresolvedReductions.push_back(UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
10463  SemaRef.Context, /*NamingClass=*/nullptr,
10464  ReductionIdScopeSpec.getWithLocInContext(SemaRef.Context), NameInfo,
10465  /*ADL=*/true, Decls.begin(), Decls.end(),
10466  /*KnownDependent=*/false));
10467  } else
10468  UnresolvedReductions.push_back(nullptr);
10469  }
10470  return getDerived().RebuildOMPReductionClause(
10471  Vars, C->getModifier(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
10472  C->getModifierLoc(), C->getColonLoc(), C->getEndLoc(),
10473  ReductionIdScopeSpec, NameInfo, UnresolvedReductions);
10474 }
10475

10477 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPTaskReductionClause(
10478  OMPTaskReductionClause *C) {
10479  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10480  Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());

10483  if (EVar.isInvalid())
10484  return nullptr;

10493  if (!NameInfo.getName())
10494  return nullptr;
10495  }

10497  // The Scope boundary is a duplication of the previous decl.

10661 template <typename Derived>
10662 OMPClause *
10663 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPDependClause(OMPDependClause *C) {
10664  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10665  Expr *DepModifier = C->getModifier();
10666  if (DepModifier) {
10667  ExprResult DepModRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(DepModifier);
10668  if (DepModRes.isInvalid())
10669  return nullptr;
10670  DepModifier = DepModRes.get();
10671  }
10672  Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
10673  for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
10674  ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
10675  if (EVar.isInvalid())
10676  return nullptr;
10677  Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
10678  }
10679  return getDerived().RebuildOMPDependClause(
10680  {C->getDependencyKind(), C->getDependencyLoc(), C->getColonLoc(),
10681  C->getOmpAllMemoryLoc()},
10682  DepModifier, Vars, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10683 }

10685 template <typename Derived>
10686 OMPClause *
10687 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPDeviceClause(OMPDeviceClause *C) {
10688  ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getDevice());
10689  if (E.isInvalid())
10690  return nullptr;
10691  return getDerived().RebuildOMPDeviceClause(
10692  C->getModifier(), E.get(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
10693  C->getModifierLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10694 }
10695 
10696 template <typename Derived, class T>
10697 bool transformOMPMappableExprListClause(
10698  TreeTransform<Derived> &TT, OMPMappableExprListClause<T> *C,
10699  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Vars, CXXScopeSpec &MapperIdScopeSpec,
10700  DeclarationNameInfo &MapperIdInfo,
10701  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &UnresolvedMappers) {
10702  // Transform expressions in the list.
10703  Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
10704  for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
10705  ExprResult EVar = TT.getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
10706  if (EVar.isInvalid())
10707  return true;
10708  Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
10709  }
10710  // Transform mapper scope specifier and identifier.
10711  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
10712  if (C->getMapperQualifierLoc()) {
10713  QualifierLoc = TT.getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(
10714  C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
10715  if (!QualifierLoc)
10716  return true;
10717  }
10718  MapperIdScopeSpec.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
10719  MapperIdInfo = C->getMapperIdInfo();
10720  if (MapperIdInfo.getName()) {
10721  MapperIdInfo = TT.getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(MapperIdInfo);
10722  if (!MapperIdInfo.getName())
10723  return true;
10724  }
10725  // Build a list of all candidate OMPDeclareMapperDecls, which is provided by
10726  // the previous user-defined mapper lookup in dependent environment.
10727  for (auto *E : C->mapperlists()) {
10728  // Transform all the decls.
10729  if (E) {
10730  auto *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
10731  UnresolvedSet<8> Decls;
10732  for (auto *D : ULE->decls()) {
10733  NamedDecl *InstD =
10734  cast<NamedDecl>(TT.getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getExprLoc(), D));
10735  Decls.addDecl(InstD, InstD->getAccess());
10736  }
10737  UnresolvedMappers.push_back(UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
10738  TT.getSema().Context, /*NamingClass=*/nullptr,
10739  MapperIdScopeSpec.getWithLocInContext(TT.getSema().Context),
10740  MapperIdInfo, /*ADL=*/true, Decls.begin(), Decls.end(),
10741  /*KnownDependent=*/false));
10742  } else {
10743  UnresolvedMappers.push_back(nullptr);
10744  }
10745  }
10746  return false;
10747 }
10748 
10749 template <typename Derived>
10750 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPMapClause(OMPMapClause *C) {
10751  OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
10752  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10753  Expr *IteratorModifier = C->getIteratorModifier();
10754  if (IteratorModifier) {
10755  ExprResult MapModRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(IteratorModifier);
10756  if (MapModRes.isInvalid())
10757  return nullptr;
10758  IteratorModifier = MapModRes.get();
10759  }
10760  CXXScopeSpec MapperIdScopeSpec;
10761  DeclarationNameInfo MapperIdInfo;
10762  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedMappers;
10763  if (transformOMPMappableExprListClause<Derived, OMPMapClause>(
10764  *this, C, Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, UnresolvedMappers))
10765  return nullptr;
10766  return getDerived().RebuildOMPMapClause(
10767  IteratorModifier, C->getMapTypeModifiers(), C->getMapTypeModifiersLoc(),
10768  MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, C->getMapType(), C->isImplicitMapType(),
10769  C->getMapLoc(), C->getColonLoc(), Vars, Locs, UnresolvedMappers);
10770 }

10772 template <typename Derived>
10773 OMPClause *
10774 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPAllocateClause(OMPAllocateClause *C) {
10775  Expr *Allocator = C->getAllocator();
10776  if (Allocator) {
10777  ExprResult AllocatorRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(Allocator);
10778  if (AllocatorRes.isInvalid())
10779  return nullptr;
10780  Allocator = AllocatorRes.get();
10781  }
10782  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
10783  Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
10784  for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
10785  ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
10786  if (EVar.isInvalid())
10787  return nullptr;
10788  Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
10789  }
10790  return getDerived().RebuildOMPAllocateClause(
10791  Allocator, Vars, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getColonLoc(),
10792  C->getEndLoc());
10793 }

11016 template <typename Derived>
11017 OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPUsesAllocatorsClause(
11018  OMPUsesAllocatorsClause *C) {
11019  SmallVector<SemaOpenMP::UsesAllocatorsData, 16> Data;
11020  Data.reserve(C->getNumberOfAllocators());
11021  for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumberOfAllocators(); I < E; ++I) {
11022  OMPUsesAllocatorsClause::Data D = C->getAllocatorData(I);
11023  ExprResult Allocator = getDerived().TransformExpr(D.Allocator);
11024  if (Allocator.isInvalid())
11025  continue;
11026  ExprResult AllocatorTraits;
11027  if (Expr *AT = D.AllocatorTraits) {
11028  AllocatorTraits = getDerived().TransformExpr(AT);
11029  if (AllocatorTraits.isInvalid())
11030  continue;
11031  }
11032  SemaOpenMP::UsesAllocatorsData &NewD = Data.emplace_back();
11033  NewD.Allocator = Allocator.get();
11034  NewD.AllocatorTraits = AllocatorTraits.get();
11035  NewD.LParenLoc = D.LParenLoc;
11036  NewD.RParenLoc = D.RParenLoc;
11037  }
11038  return getDerived().RebuildOMPUsesAllocatorsClause(
11039  Data, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
11040 }
11041 
11042 template <typename Derived>
11043 OMPClause *
11044 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPAffinityClause(OMPAffinityClause *C) {
11045  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Locators;
11046  Locators.reserve(C->varlist_size());
11047  ExprResult ModifierRes;
11048  if (Expr *Modifier = C->getModifier()) {
11049  ModifierRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(Modifier);
11050  if (ModifierRes.isInvalid())
11051  return nullptr;
11052  }
11053  for (Expr *E : C->varlists()) {
11054  ExprResult Locator = getDerived().TransformExpr(E);
11055  if (Locator.isInvalid())
11056  continue;
11057  Locators.push_back(Locator.get());
11058  }
11059  return getDerived().RebuildOMPAffinityClause(
11060  C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getColonLoc(), C->getEndLoc(),
11061  ModifierRes.get(), Locators);
11062 }

11119 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
11120 // OpenACC transformation
11121 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
11122 namespace {
11123 template <typename Derived>
11124 class OpenACCClauseTransform final
11125  : public OpenACCClauseVisitor<OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>> {
11126  TreeTransform<Derived> &Self;
11127  SemaOpenACC::OpenACCParsedClause &ParsedClause;
11128  OpenACCClause *NewClause = nullptr;
11129 
11130 public:
11131  OpenACCClauseTransform(TreeTransform<Derived> &Self,
11132  SemaOpenACC::OpenACCParsedClause &PC)
11133  : Self(Self), ParsedClause(PC) {}
11134 
11135  OpenACCClause *CreatedClause() const { return NewClause; }
11136 
11137 #define VISIT_CLAUSE(CLAUSE_NAME) \
11138  void Visit##CLAUSE_NAME##Clause(const OpenACC##CLAUSE_NAME##Clause &Clause);
11139 #include "clang/Basic/OpenACCClauses.def"
11140 };
11141 
11142 template <typename Derived>
11143 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitDefaultClause(
11144  const OpenACCDefaultClause &C) {
11145  ParsedClause.setDefaultDetails(C.getDefaultClauseKind());
11146 
11147  NewClause = OpenACCDefaultClause::Create(
11148  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getDefaultClauseKind(),
11149  ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(), ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(),
11150  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11151 }
11152 
11153 template <typename Derived>
11154 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitIfClause(const OpenACCIfClause &C) {
11155  Expr *Cond = const_cast<Expr *>(C.getConditionExpr());
11156  assert(Cond && "If constructed with invalid Condition");
11157  Sema::ConditionResult Res = Self.TransformCondition(
11158  Cond->getExprLoc(), /*Var=*/nullptr, Cond, Sema::ConditionKind::Boolean);
11159 
11160  if (Res.isInvalid() || !Res.get().second)
11161  return;
11162 
11163  ParsedClause.setConditionDetails(Res.get().second);
11164 
11165  NewClause = OpenACCIfClause::Create(
11166  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(),
11167  ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(), ParsedClause.getConditionExpr(),
11168  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11169 }
11170 
11171 template <typename Derived>
11172 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitSelfClause(
11173  const OpenACCSelfClause &C) {
11174 
11175  if (C.hasConditionExpr()) {
11176  Expr *Cond = const_cast<Expr *>(C.getConditionExpr());
11177  Sema::ConditionResult Res =
11178  Self.TransformCondition(Cond->getExprLoc(), /*Var=*/nullptr, Cond,
11179  Sema::ConditionKind::Boolean);
11180 
11181  if (Res.isInvalid() || !Res.get().second)
11182  return;
11183 
11184  ParsedClause.setConditionDetails(Res.get().second);
11185  }
11186 
11187  NewClause = OpenACCSelfClause::Create(
11188  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(),
11189  ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(), ParsedClause.getConditionExpr(),
11190  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11191 }
11192 
11193 template <typename Derived>
11194 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitNumGangsClause(
11195  const OpenACCNumGangsClause &C) {
11196  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *> InstantiatedIntExprs;
11197 
11198  for (Expr *CurIntExpr : C.getIntExprs()) {
11199  ExprResult Res = Self.TransformExpr(CurIntExpr);
11200 
11201  if (!Res.isUsable())
11202  return;
11203 
11204  Res = Self.getSema().OpenACC().ActOnIntExpr(OpenACCDirectiveKind::Invalid,
11205  C.getClauseKind(),
11206  C.getBeginLoc(), Res.get());
11207  if (!Res.isUsable())
11208  return;
11209 
11210  InstantiatedIntExprs.push_back(Res.get());
11211  }
11212 
11213  ParsedClause.setIntExprDetails(InstantiatedIntExprs);
11214  NewClause = OpenACCNumGangsClause::Create(
11215  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(),
11216  ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(), ParsedClause.getIntExprs(),
11217  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11218 }
11219 template <typename Derived>
11220 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitNumWorkersClause(
11221  const OpenACCNumWorkersClause &C) {
11222  Expr *IntExpr = const_cast<Expr *>(C.getIntExpr());
11223  assert(IntExpr && "num_workers clause constructed with invalid int expr");
11224 
11225  ExprResult Res = Self.TransformExpr(IntExpr);
11226  if (!Res.isUsable())
11227  return;
11228 
11229  Res = Self.getSema().OpenACC().ActOnIntExpr(OpenACCDirectiveKind::Invalid,
11230  C.getClauseKind(),
11231  C.getBeginLoc(), Res.get());
11232  if (!Res.isUsable())
11233  return;
11234 
11235  ParsedClause.setIntExprDetails(Res.get());
11236  NewClause = OpenACCNumWorkersClause::Create(
11237  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(),
11238  ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(), ParsedClause.getIntExprs()[0],
11239  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11240 }
11241 
11242 template <typename Derived>
11243 void OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived>::VisitVectorLengthClause(
11244  const OpenACCVectorLengthClause &C) {
11245  Expr *IntExpr = const_cast<Expr *>(C.getIntExpr());
11246  assert(IntExpr && "vector_length clause constructed with invalid int expr");
11247 
11248  ExprResult Res = Self.TransformExpr(IntExpr);
11249  if (!Res.isUsable())
11250  return;
11251 
11252  Res = Self.getSema().OpenACC().ActOnIntExpr(OpenACCDirectiveKind::Invalid,
11253  C.getClauseKind(),
11254  C.getBeginLoc(), Res.get());
11255  if (!Res.isUsable())
11256  return;
11257 
11258  ParsedClause.setIntExprDetails(Res.get());
11259  NewClause = OpenACCVectorLengthClause::Create(
11260  Self.getSema().getASTContext(), ParsedClause.getBeginLoc(),
11261  ParsedClause.getLParenLoc(), ParsedClause.getIntExprs()[0],
11262  ParsedClause.getEndLoc());
11263 }
11264 } // namespace
11265 template <typename Derived>
11266 OpenACCClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOpenACCClause(
11267  ArrayRef<const OpenACCClause *> ExistingClauses,
11268  OpenACCDirectiveKind DirKind, const OpenACCClause *OldClause) {
11269 
11270  SemaOpenACC::OpenACCParsedClause ParsedClause(
11271  DirKind, OldClause->getClauseKind(), OldClause->getBeginLoc());
11272  ParsedClause.setEndLoc(OldClause->getEndLoc());
11273 
11274  if (const auto *WithParms = dyn_cast<OpenACCClauseWithParams>(OldClause))
11275  ParsedClause.setLParenLoc(WithParms->getLParenLoc());
11276 
11277  OpenACCClauseTransform<Derived> Transform{*this, ParsedClause};
11278  Transform.Visit(OldClause);
11279 
11280  return Transform.CreatedClause();
11281 }
11282 
11283 template <typename Derived>
11284 llvm::SmallVector<OpenACCClause *>
11285 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOpenACCClauseList(
11286  OpenACCDirectiveKind DirKind, ArrayRef<const OpenACCClause *> OldClauses) {
11287  llvm::SmallVector<OpenACCClause *> TransformedClauses;
11288  for (const auto *Clause : OldClauses) {
11289  if (OpenACCClause *TransformedClause = getDerived().TransformOpenACCClause(
11290  TransformedClauses, DirKind, Clause))
11291  TransformedClauses.push_back(TransformedClause);
11292  }
11293  return TransformedClauses;
11294 }

11296 template <typename Derived>
11297 StmtResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOpenACCComputeConstruct(
11298  OpenACCComputeConstruct *C) {
11299  getSema().OpenACC().ActOnConstruct(C->getDirectiveKind(), C->getBeginLoc());
11300  // FIXME: When implementing this for constructs that can take arguments, we
11301  // should do Sema for them here.
11302 
11303  if (getSema().OpenACC().ActOnStartStmtDirective(C->getDirectiveKind(),
11304  C->getBeginLoc()))
11305  return StmtError();
11306 
11307  llvm::SmallVector<OpenACCClause *> TransformedClauses =
11308  getDerived().TransformOpenACCClauseList(C->getDirectiveKind(),
11309  C->clauses());
11310 
11311  // Transform Structured Block.
11312  StmtResult StrBlock = getDerived().TransformStmt(C->getStructuredBlock());
11313  StrBlock =
11314  getSema().OpenACC().ActOnAssociatedStmt(C->getDirectiveKind(), StrBlock);
11315 
11316  return getDerived().RebuildOpenACCComputeConstruct(
11317  C->getDirectiveKind(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getEndLoc(),
11318  TransformedClauses, StrBlock);
11319 }

11348 template <typename Derived>
11349 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformSYCLUniqueStableIdExpr(
11350  SYCLUniqueStableIdExpr *E) {

11352  return E;

11355

11357  return ExprError();
11358

11360

11365  return E;

11382 template<typename Derived>
11383 ExprResult
11384 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
11385  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
11386  if (E->getQualifierLoc()) {
11387  QualifierLoc
11388  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
11389  if (!QualifierLoc)
11390  return ExprError();
11391  }
11392 
11393  ValueDecl *ND
11394  = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getLocation(),
11395  E->getDecl()));
11396  if (!ND)
11397  return ExprError();
11398 
11399  NamedDecl *Found = ND;
11400  if (E->getFoundDecl() != E->getDecl()) {
11401  Found = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(
11402  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getLocation(), E->getFoundDecl()));
11403  if (!Found)
11404  return ExprError();
11405  }
11406 
11407  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = E->getNameInfo();
11408  if (NameInfo.getName()) {
11409  NameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo);
11410  if (!NameInfo.getName())
11411  return ExprError();
11412  }
11413 
11414  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
11415  !E->isCapturedByCopyInLambdaWithExplicitObjectParameter() &&
11416  QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() && ND == E->getDecl() &&
11417  Found == E->getFoundDecl() &&
11418  NameInfo.getName() == E->getDecl()->getDeclName() &&
11419  !E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
11420 
11421  // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
11422  // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
11423  SemaRef.MarkDeclRefReferenced(E);
11424 
11425  return E;
11426  }
11427 
11428  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs, *TemplateArgs = nullptr;
11429  if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
11430  TemplateArgs = &TransArgs;
11431  TransArgs.setLAngleLoc(E->getLAngleLoc());
11432  TransArgs.setRAngleLoc(E->getRAngleLoc());
11433  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(E->getTemplateArgs(),
11434  E->getNumTemplateArgs(),
11435  TransArgs))
11436  return ExprError();
11437  }
11438 
11439  return getDerived().RebuildDeclRefExpr(QualifierLoc, ND, NameInfo,
11440  Found, TemplateArgs);
11441 }

11485 template<typename Derived>
11486 ExprResult
11487 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformGenericSelectionExpr(GenericSelectionExpr *E) {
11488  ExprResult ControllingExpr;
11489  TypeSourceInfo *ControllingType = nullptr;
11490  if (E->isExprPredicate())
11491  ControllingExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getControllingExpr());
11492  else
11493  ControllingType = getDerived().TransformType(E->getControllingType());
11494 
11495  if (ControllingExpr.isInvalid() && !ControllingType)
11496  return ExprError();
11497 
11498  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> AssocExprs;
11499  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> AssocTypes;
11500  for (const GenericSelectionExpr::Association Assoc : E->associations()) {
11501  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = Assoc.getTypeSourceInfo();
11502  if (TSI) {
11503  TypeSourceInfo *AssocType = getDerived().TransformType(TSI);
11504  if (!AssocType)
11505  return ExprError();
11506  AssocTypes.push_back(AssocType);
11507  } else {
11508  AssocTypes.push_back(nullptr);
11509  }
11510 
11511  ExprResult AssocExpr =
11512  getDerived().TransformExpr(Assoc.getAssociationExpr());
11513  if (AssocExpr.isInvalid())
11514  return ExprError();
11515  AssocExprs.push_back(AssocExpr.get());
11516  }
11517 
11518  if (!ControllingType)
11519  return getDerived().RebuildGenericSelectionExpr(E->getGenericLoc(),
11520  E->getDefaultLoc(),
11521  E->getRParenLoc(),
11522  ControllingExpr.get(),
11523  AssocTypes,
11524  AssocExprs);
11525  return getDerived().RebuildGenericSelectionExpr(
11526  E->getGenericLoc(), E->getDefaultLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(),
11527  ControllingType, AssocTypes, AssocExprs);
11528 }

11530 template<typename Derived>
11531 ExprResult
11532 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformParenExpr(ParenExpr *E) {
11533  ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
11534  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
11535  return ExprError();
11536 
11537  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
11538  return E;
11539 
11540  return getDerived().RebuildParenExpr(SubExpr.get(), E->getLParen(),
11541  E->getRParen());
11542 }

11544 /// The operand of a unary address-of operator has special rules: it's
11545 /// allowed to refer to a non-static member of a class even if there's no 'this'
11546 /// object available.
11547 template<typename Derived>
11548 ExprResult
11549 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAddressOfOperand(Expr *E) {
11550  if (DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(E))
11551  return getDerived().TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
11552  DRE, /*IsAddressOfOperand=*/true, nullptr);
11553  else if (UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E))
11554  return getDerived().TransformUnresolvedLookupExpr(
11555  ULE, /*IsAddressOfOperand=*/true);
11556  else
11557  return getDerived().TransformExpr(E);
11558 }

11560 template<typename Derived>
11561 ExprResult
11562 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnaryOperator(UnaryOperator *E) {
11563  ExprResult SubExpr;
11564  if (E->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
11565  SubExpr = TransformAddressOfOperand(E->getSubExpr());
11566  else
11567  SubExpr = TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
11568  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
11569  return ExprError();
11570 
11571  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
11572  return E;
11573 
11574  return getDerived().RebuildUnaryOperator(E->getOperatorLoc(),
11575  E->getOpcode(),
11576  SubExpr.get());
11577 }

11579 template<typename Derived>
11580 ExprResult
11581 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
11582  // Transform the type.
11583  TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeSourceInfo());
11584  if (!Type)
11585  return ExprError();
11586 
11587  // Transform all of the components into components similar to what the
11588  // parser uses.
11589  // FIXME: It would be slightly more efficient in the non-dependent case to
11590  // just map FieldDecls, rather than requiring the rebuilder to look for
11591  // the fields again. However, __builtin_offsetof is rare enough in
11592  // template code that we don't care.
11593  bool ExprChanged = false;
11594  typedef Sema::OffsetOfComponent Component;
11595  SmallVector<Component, 4> Components;
11596  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumComponents(); I != N; ++I) {
11597  const OffsetOfNode &ON = E->getComponent(I);
11598  Component Comp;
11599  Comp.isBrackets = true;
11600  Comp.LocStart = ON.getSourceRange().getBegin();
11601  Comp.LocEnd = ON.getSourceRange().getEnd();
11602  switch (ON.getKind()) {
11603  case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
11604  Expr *FromIndex = E->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
11605  ExprResult Index = getDerived().TransformExpr(FromIndex);
11606  if (Index.isInvalid())
11607  return ExprError();
11608 
11609  ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Index.get() != FromIndex;
11610  Comp.isBrackets = true;
11611  Comp.U.E = Index.get();
11612  break;
11613  }
11614 
11615  case OffsetOfNode::Field:
11616  case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
11617  Comp.isBrackets = false;
11618  Comp.U.IdentInfo = ON.getFieldName();
11619  if (!Comp.U.IdentInfo)
11620  continue;
11621 
11622  break;
11623 
11624  case OffsetOfNode::Base:
11625  // Will be recomputed during the rebuild.
11626  continue;
11627  }
11628 
11629  Components.push_back(Comp);
11630  }
11631 
11632  // If nothing changed, retain the existing expression.
11633  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
11634  Type == E->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
11635  !ExprChanged)
11636  return E;
11637 
11638  // Build a new offsetof expression.
11639  return getDerived().RebuildOffsetOfExpr(E->getOperatorLoc(), Type,
11640  Components, E->getRParenLoc());
11641 }

11647  "opaque value expression requires transformation");
11648  return E;

11657 template <typename Derived>
11658 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformRecoveryExpr(RecoveryExpr *E) {
11659  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 8> Children;
11660  bool Changed = false;
11661  for (Expr *C : E->subExpressions()) {
11662  ExprResult NewC = getDerived().TransformExpr(C);
11663  if (NewC.isInvalid())
11664  return ExprError();
11665  Children.push_back(NewC.get());
11666 
11667  Changed |= NewC.get() != C;
11668  }
11669  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !Changed)
11670  return E;
11671  return getDerived().RebuildRecoveryExpr(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getEndLoc(),
11672  Children, E->getType());
11673 }
