11675 template<typename Derived>
11676 ExprResult
11677 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPseudoObjectExpr(PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
11678  // Rebuild the syntactic form. The original syntactic form has
11679  // opaque-value expressions in it, so strip those away and rebuild
11680  // the result. This is a really awful way of doing this, but the
11681  // better solution (rebuilding the semantic expressions and
11682  // rebinding OVEs as necessary) doesn't work; we'd need
11683  // TreeTransform to not strip away implicit conversions.
11684  Expr *newSyntacticForm = SemaRef.recreateSyntacticForm(E);
11685  ExprResult result = getDerived().TransformExpr(newSyntacticForm);
11686  if (result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
11687 
11688  // If that gives us a pseudo-object result back, the pseudo-object
11689  // expression must have been an lvalue-to-rvalue conversion which we
11690  // should reapply.
11691  if (result.get()->hasPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::PseudoObject))
11692  result = SemaRef.checkPseudoObjectRValue(result.get());
11693 
11694  return result;
11695 }
11696 
11697 template<typename Derived>
11698 ExprResult
11699 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
11700  UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
11701  if (E->isArgumentType()) {
11702  TypeSourceInfo *OldT = E->getArgumentTypeInfo();
11703 
11704  TypeSourceInfo *NewT = getDerived().TransformType(OldT);
11705  if (!NewT)
11706  return ExprError();
11707 
11708  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && OldT == NewT)
11709  return E;
11710 
11711  return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(NewT, E->getOperatorLoc(),
11712  E->getKind(),
11713  E->getSourceRange());
11714  }
11715 
11716  // C++0x [expr.sizeof]p1:
11717  // The operand is either an expression, which is an unevaluated operand
11718  // [...]
11719  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
11720  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
11721  Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
11722 
11723  // Try to recover if we have something like sizeof(T::X) where X is a type.
11724  // Notably, there must be *exactly* one set of parens if X is a type.
11725  TypeSourceInfo *RecoveryTSI = nullptr;
11726  ExprResult SubExpr;
11727  auto *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E->getArgumentExpr());
11728  if (auto *DRE =
11729  PE ? dyn_cast<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(PE->getSubExpr()) : nullptr)
11730  SubExpr = getDerived().TransformParenDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
11731  PE, DRE, false, &RecoveryTSI);
11732  else
11733  SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArgumentExpr());
11734 
11735  if (RecoveryTSI) {
11736  return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(
11737  RecoveryTSI, E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getKind(), E->getSourceRange());
11738  } else if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
11739  return ExprError();
11740 
11741  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getArgumentExpr())
11742  return E;
11743 
11744  return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(SubExpr.get(),
11745  E->getOperatorLoc(),
11746  E->getKind(),
11747  E->getSourceRange());
11748 }

11764  RHS.get() == E->getRHS())

11769  /*FIXME:*/ E->getLHS()->getBeginLoc(), RHS.get(), E->getRBracketLoc());

11795 template <typename Derived>
11796 ExprResult
11797 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPArraySectionExpr(OMPArraySectionExpr *E) {
11798  ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
11799  if (Base.isInvalid())
11800  return ExprError();
11801 
11802  ExprResult LowerBound;
11803  if (E->getLowerBound()) {
11804  LowerBound = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLowerBound());
11805  if (LowerBound.isInvalid())
11806  return ExprError();
11807  }
11808 
11809  ExprResult Length;
11810  if (E->getLength()) {
11811  Length = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLength());
11812  if (Length.isInvalid())
11813  return ExprError();
11814  }
11815 
11816  ExprResult Stride;
11817  if (Expr *Str = E->getStride()) {
11818  Stride = getDerived().TransformExpr(Str);
11819  if (Stride.isInvalid())
11820  return ExprError();
11821  }
11822 
11823  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && Base.get() == E->getBase() &&
11824  LowerBound.get() == E->getLowerBound() && Length.get() == E->getLength())
11825  return E;
11826 
11827  return getDerived().RebuildOMPArraySectionExpr(
11828  Base.get(), E->getBase()->getEndLoc(), LowerBound.get(),
11829  E->getColonLocFirst(), E->getColonLocSecond(), Length.get(), Stride.get(),
11830  E->getRBracketLoc());
11831 }

11833 template <typename Derived>
11834 ExprResult
11835 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPArrayShapingExpr(OMPArrayShapingExpr *E) {
11836  ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
11837  if (Base.isInvalid())
11838  return ExprError();
11839 
11840  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Dims;
11841  bool ErrorFound = false;
11842  for (Expr *Dim : E->getDimensions()) {
11843  ExprResult DimRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(Dim);
11844  if (DimRes.isInvalid()) {
11845  ErrorFound = true;
11846  continue;
11847  }
11848  Dims.push_back(DimRes.get());
11849  }
11850 
11851  if (ErrorFound)
11852  return ExprError();
11853  return getDerived().RebuildOMPArrayShapingExpr(Base.get(), E->getLParenLoc(),
11854  E->getRParenLoc(), Dims,
11855  E->getBracketsRanges());
11856 }
11857 
11858 template <typename Derived>
11859 ExprResult
11860 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPIteratorExpr(OMPIteratorExpr *E) {
11861  unsigned NumIterators = E->numOfIterators();
11862  SmallVector<SemaOpenMP::OMPIteratorData, 4> Data(NumIterators);
11863 
11864  bool ErrorFound = false;
11865  bool NeedToRebuild = getDerived().AlwaysRebuild();
11866  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumIterators; ++I) {
11867  auto *D = cast<VarDecl>(E->getIteratorDecl(I));
11868  Data[I].DeclIdent = D->getIdentifier();
11869  Data[I].DeclIdentLoc = D->getLocation();
11870  if (D->getLocation() == D->getBeginLoc()) {
11871  assert(SemaRef.Context.hasSameType(D->getType(), SemaRef.Context.IntTy) &&
11872  "Implicit type must be int.");
11873  } else {
11874  TypeSourceInfo *TSI = getDerived().TransformType(D->getTypeSourceInfo());
11875  QualType DeclTy = getDerived().TransformType(D->getType());
11876  Data[I].Type = SemaRef.CreateParsedType(DeclTy, TSI);
11877  }
11878  OMPIteratorExpr::IteratorRange Range = E->getIteratorRange(I);
11879  ExprResult Begin = getDerived().TransformExpr(Range.Begin);
11880  ExprResult End = getDerived().TransformExpr(Range.End);
11881  ExprResult Step = getDerived().TransformExpr(Range.Step);
11882  ErrorFound = ErrorFound ||
11883  !(!D->getTypeSourceInfo() || (Data[I].Type.getAsOpaquePtr() &&
11884  !Data[I].Type.get().isNull())) ||
11885  Begin.isInvalid() || End.isInvalid() || Step.isInvalid();
11886  if (ErrorFound)
11887  continue;
11888  Data[I].Range.Begin = Begin.get();
11889  Data[I].Range.End = End.get();
11890  Data[I].Range.Step = Step.get();
11891  Data[I].AssignLoc = E->getAssignLoc(I);
11892  Data[I].ColonLoc = E->getColonLoc(I);
11893  Data[I].SecColonLoc = E->getSecondColonLoc(I);
11894  NeedToRebuild =
11895  NeedToRebuild ||
11896  (D->getTypeSourceInfo() && Data[I].Type.get().getTypePtrOrNull() !=
11897  D->getType().getTypePtrOrNull()) ||
11898  Range.Begin != Data[I].Range.Begin || Range.End != Data[I].Range.End ||
11899  Range.Step != Data[I].Range.Step;
11900  }
11901  if (ErrorFound)
11902  return ExprError();
11903  if (!NeedToRebuild)
11904  return E;
11905 
11906  ExprResult Res = getDerived().RebuildOMPIteratorExpr(
11907  E->getIteratorKwLoc(), E->getLParenLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(), Data);
11908  if (!Res.isUsable())
11909  return Res;
11910  auto *IE = cast<OMPIteratorExpr>(Res.get());
11911  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumIterators; ++I)
11912  getDerived().transformedLocalDecl(E->getIteratorDecl(I),
11913  IE->getIteratorDecl(I));
11914  return Res;
11915 }
11916 
11917 template<typename Derived>
11918 ExprResult
11919 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCallExpr(CallExpr *E) {
11920  // Transform the callee.
11921  ExprResult Callee = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCallee());
11922  if (Callee.isInvalid())
11923  return ExprError();
11924 
11925  // Transform arguments.
11926  bool ArgChanged = false;
11927  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
11928  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
11929  &ArgChanged))
11930  return ExprError();
11931 
11932  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
11933  Callee.get() == E->getCallee() &&
11934  !ArgChanged)
11935  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
11936 
11937  // FIXME: Wrong source location information for the '('.
11938  SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc
11939  = ((Expr *)Callee.get())->getSourceRange().getBegin();
11940 
11941  Sema::FPFeaturesStateRAII FPFeaturesState(getSema());
11942  if (E->hasStoredFPFeatures()) {
11943  FPOptionsOverride NewOverrides = E->getFPFeatures();
11944  getSema().CurFPFeatures =
11945  NewOverrides.applyOverrides(getSema().getLangOpts());
11946  getSema().FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue = NewOverrides;
11947  }
11948 
11949  return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Callee.get(), FakeLParenLoc,
11950  Args,
11951  E->getRParenLoc());
11952 }
11953 
11954 template<typename Derived>
11955 ExprResult
11956 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
11957  ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
11958  if (Base.isInvalid())
11959  return ExprError();
11960 
11961  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
11962  if (E->hasQualifier()) {
11963  QualifierLoc
11964  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
11965 
11966  if (!QualifierLoc)
11967  return ExprError();
11968  }
11969  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = E->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
11970 
11971  ValueDecl *Member
11972  = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getMemberLoc(),
11973  E->getMemberDecl()));
11974  if (!Member)
11975  return ExprError();
11976 
11977  NamedDecl *FoundDecl = E->getFoundDecl();
11978  if (FoundDecl == E->getMemberDecl()) {
11979  FoundDecl = Member;
11980  } else {
11981  FoundDecl = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(
11982  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getMemberLoc(), FoundDecl));
11983  if (!FoundDecl)
11984  return ExprError();
11985  }
11986 
11987  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
11988  Base.get() == E->getBase() &&
11989  QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() &&
11990  Member == E->getMemberDecl() &&
11991  FoundDecl == E->getFoundDecl() &&
11992  !E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
11993 
11994  // Skip for member expression of (this->f), rebuilt thisi->f is needed
11995  // for Openmp where the field need to be privatizized in the case.
11996  if (!(isa<CXXThisExpr>(E->getBase()) &&
11997  getSema().OpenMP().isOpenMPRebuildMemberExpr(
11998  cast<ValueDecl>(Member)))) {
11999  // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
12000  // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
12001  SemaRef.MarkMemberReferenced(E);
12002  return E;
12003  }
12004  }
12005 
12006  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs;
12007  if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
12008  TransArgs.setLAngleLoc(E->getLAngleLoc());
12009  TransArgs.setRAngleLoc(E->getRAngleLoc());
12010  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(E->getTemplateArgs(),
12011  E->getNumTemplateArgs(),
12012  TransArgs))
12013  return ExprError();
12014  }
12015 
12016  // FIXME: Bogus source location for the operator
12017  SourceLocation FakeOperatorLoc =
12018  SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(E->getBase()->getSourceRange().getEnd());
12019 
12020  // FIXME: to do this check properly, we will need to preserve the
12021  // first-qualifier-in-scope here, just in case we had a dependent
12022  // base (and therefore couldn't do the check) and a
12023  // nested-name-qualifier (and therefore could do the lookup).
12024  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr;
12025  DeclarationNameInfo MemberNameInfo = E->getMemberNameInfo();
12026  if (MemberNameInfo.getName()) {
12027  MemberNameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(MemberNameInfo);
12028  if (!MemberNameInfo.getName())
12029  return ExprError();
12030  }
12031 
12032  return getDerived().RebuildMemberExpr(Base.get(), FakeOperatorLoc,
12033  E->isArrow(),
12034  QualifierLoc,
12035  TemplateKWLoc,
12036  MemberNameInfo,
12037  Member,
12038  FoundDecl,
12039  (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()
12040  ? &TransArgs : nullptr),
12041  FirstQualifierInScope);
12042 }
12043 
12044 template<typename Derived>
12045 ExprResult
12046 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformBinaryOperator(BinaryOperator *E) {
12047  ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
12048  if (LHS.isInvalid())
12049  return ExprError();
12050 
12051  ExprResult RHS =
12052  getDerived().TransformInitializer(E->getRHS(), /*NotCopyInit=*/false);
12053  if (RHS.isInvalid())
12054  return ExprError();
12055 
12056  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12057  LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
12058  RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
12059  return E;
12060 
12061  if (E->isCompoundAssignmentOp())
12062  // FPFeatures has already been established from trailing storage
12063  return getDerived().RebuildBinaryOperator(
12064  E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getOpcode(), LHS.get(), RHS.get());
12065  Sema::FPFeaturesStateRAII FPFeaturesState(getSema());
12066  FPOptionsOverride NewOverrides(E->getFPFeatures());
12067  getSema().CurFPFeatures =
12068  NewOverrides.applyOverrides(getSema().getLangOpts());
12069  getSema().FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue = NewOverrides;
12070  return getDerived().RebuildBinaryOperator(E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getOpcode(),
12071  LHS.get(), RHS.get());
12072 }
12073 
12074 template <typename Derived>
12075 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXRewrittenBinaryOperator(
12076  CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator *E) {
12077  CXXRewrittenBinaryOperator::DecomposedForm Decomp = E->getDecomposedForm();
12078 
12079  ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(const_cast<Expr*>(Decomp.LHS));
12080  if (LHS.isInvalid())
12081  return ExprError();
12082 
12083  ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(const_cast<Expr*>(Decomp.RHS));
12084  if (RHS.isInvalid())
12085  return ExprError();
12086 
12087  // Extract the already-resolved callee declarations so that we can restrict
12088  // ourselves to using them as the unqualified lookup results when rebuilding.
12089  UnresolvedSet<2> UnqualLookups;
12090  bool ChangedAnyLookups = false;
12091  Expr *PossibleBinOps[] = {E->getSemanticForm(),
12092  const_cast<Expr *>(Decomp.InnerBinOp)};
12093  for (Expr *PossibleBinOp : PossibleBinOps) {
12094  auto *Op = dyn_cast<CXXOperatorCallExpr>(PossibleBinOp->IgnoreImplicit());
12095  if (!Op)
12096  continue;
12097  auto *Callee = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Op->getCallee()->IgnoreImplicit());
12098  if (!Callee || isa<CXXMethodDecl>(Callee->getDecl()))
12099  continue;
12100 
12101  // Transform the callee in case we built a call to a local extern
12102  // declaration.
12103  NamedDecl *Found = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
12104  E->getOperatorLoc(), Callee->getFoundDecl()));
12105  if (!Found)
12106  return ExprError();
12107  if (Found != Callee->getFoundDecl())
12108  ChangedAnyLookups = true;
12109  UnqualLookups.addDecl(Found);
12110  }
12111 
12112  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !ChangedAnyLookups &&
12113  LHS.get() == Decomp.LHS && RHS.get() == Decomp.RHS) {
12114  // Mark all functions used in the rewrite as referenced. Note that when
12115  // a < b is rewritten to (a <=> b) < 0, both the <=> and the < might be
12116  // function calls, and/or there might be a user-defined conversion sequence
12117  // applied to the operands of the <.
12118  // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
12119  const Expr *StopAt[] = {Decomp.LHS, Decomp.RHS};
12120  SemaRef.MarkDeclarationsReferencedInExpr(E, false, StopAt);
12121  return E;
12122  }
12123 
12124  return getDerived().RebuildCXXRewrittenBinaryOperator(
12125  E->getOperatorLoc(), Decomp.Opcode, UnqualLookups, LHS.get(), RHS.get());
12126 }
12127 
12128 template<typename Derived>
12129 ExprResult
12130 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundAssignOperator(
12131  CompoundAssignOperator *E) {
12132  Sema::FPFeaturesStateRAII FPFeaturesState(getSema());
12133  FPOptionsOverride NewOverrides(E->getFPFeatures());
12134  getSema().CurFPFeatures =
12135  NewOverrides.applyOverrides(getSema().getLangOpts());
12136  getSema().FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue = NewOverrides;
12137  return getDerived().TransformBinaryOperator(E);
12138 }

12140 template<typename Derived>
12141 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::
12142 TransformBinaryConditionalOperator(BinaryConditionalOperator *e) {
12143  // Just rebuild the common and RHS expressions and see whether we
12144  // get any changes.
12145 
12146  ExprResult commonExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(e->getCommon());
12147  if (commonExpr.isInvalid())
12148  return ExprError();
12149 
12150  ExprResult rhs = getDerived().TransformExpr(e->getFalseExpr());
12151  if (rhs.isInvalid())
12152  return ExprError();
12153 
12154  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12155  commonExpr.get() == e->getCommon() &&
12156  rhs.get() == e->getFalseExpr())
12157  return e;
12158 
12159  return getDerived().RebuildConditionalOperator(commonExpr.get(),
12160  e->getQuestionLoc(),
12161  nullptr,
12162  e->getColonLoc(),
12163  rhs.get());
12164 }

12166 template<typename Derived>
12167 ExprResult
12168 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformConditionalOperator(ConditionalOperator *E) {
12169  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCond());
12170  if (Cond.isInvalid())
12171  return ExprError();
12172 
12173  ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
12174  if (LHS.isInvalid())
12175  return ExprError();
12176 
12177  ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
12178  if (RHS.isInvalid())
12179  return ExprError();
12180 
12181  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12182  Cond.get() == E->getCond() &&
12183  LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
12184  RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
12185  return E;
12186 
12187  return getDerived().RebuildConditionalOperator(Cond.get(),
12188  E->getQuestionLoc(),
12189  LHS.get(),
12190  E->getColonLoc(),
12191  RHS.get());
12192 }

12225 template<typename Derived>
12226 ExprResult
12227 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundLiteralExpr(CompoundLiteralExpr *E) {
12228  TypeSourceInfo *OldT = E->getTypeSourceInfo();
12229  TypeSourceInfo *NewT = getDerived().TransformType(OldT);
12230  if (!NewT)
12231  return ExprError();
12232 
12233  ExprResult Init = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInitializer());
12234  if (Init.isInvalid())
12235  return ExprError();

12237  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12238  OldT == NewT &&
12239  Init.get() == E->getInitializer())
12240  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);

12243  // type-as-written, but that's okay, because it should always be
12244  // derivable from the initializer.
12245 
12246  return getDerived().RebuildCompoundLiteralExpr(
12247  E->getLParenLoc(), NewT,
12248  /*FIXME:*/ E->getInitializer()->getEndLoc(), Init.get());

12270 template<typename Derived>
12271 ExprResult
12272 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
12273  if (InitListExpr *Syntactic = E->getSyntacticForm())
12274  E = Syntactic;
12275 
12276  bool InitChanged = false;
12277 
12278  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
12279  getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList);
12280 
12281  SmallVector<Expr*, 4> Inits;
12282  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getInits(), E->getNumInits(), false,
12283  Inits, &InitChanged))
12284  return ExprError();
12285 
12286  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !InitChanged) {
12287  // FIXME: Attempt to reuse the existing syntactic form of the InitListExpr
12288  // in some cases. We can't reuse it in general, because the syntactic and
12289  // semantic forms are linked, and we can't know that semantic form will
12290  // match even if the syntactic form does.
12291  }
12292 
12293  return getDerived().RebuildInitList(E->getLBraceLoc(), Inits,
12294  E->getRBraceLoc());
12295 }

12297 template<typename Derived>
12298 ExprResult
12299 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDesignatedInitExpr(DesignatedInitExpr *E) {
12300  Designation Desig;
12301 
12302  // transform the initializer value
12303  ExprResult Init = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInit());
12304  if (Init.isInvalid())
12305  return ExprError();
12306 
12307  // transform the designators.
12308  SmallVector<Expr*, 4> ArrayExprs;
12309  bool ExprChanged = false;
12310  for (const DesignatedInitExpr::Designator &D : E->designators()) {
12311  if (D.isFieldDesignator()) {
12312  if (D.getFieldDecl()) {
12313  FieldDecl *Field = cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(
12314  getDerived().TransformDecl(D.getFieldLoc(), D.getFieldDecl()));
12315  if (Field != D.getFieldDecl())
12316  // Rebuild the expression when the transformed FieldDecl is
12317  // different to the already assigned FieldDecl.
12318  ExprChanged = true;
12319  if (Field->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
12320  continue;
12321  } else {
12322  // Ensure that the designator expression is rebuilt when there isn't
12323  // a resolved FieldDecl in the designator as we don't want to assign
12324  // a FieldDecl to a pattern designator that will be instantiated again.
12325  ExprChanged = true;
12326  }
12327  Desig.AddDesignator(Designator::CreateFieldDesignator(
12328  D.getFieldName(), D.getDotLoc(), D.getFieldLoc()));
12329  continue;
12330  }
12331 
12332  if (D.isArrayDesignator()) {
12333  ExprResult Index = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayIndex(D));
12334  if (Index.isInvalid())
12335  return ExprError();
12336 
12337  Desig.AddDesignator(
12338  Designator::CreateArrayDesignator(Index.get(), D.getLBracketLoc()));
12339 
12340  ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Init.get() != E->getArrayIndex(D);
12341  ArrayExprs.push_back(Index.get());
12342  continue;
12343  }
12344 
12345  assert(D.isArrayRangeDesignator() && "New kind of designator?");
12346  ExprResult Start
12347  = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayRangeStart(D));
12348  if (Start.isInvalid())
12349  return ExprError();
12350 
12351  ExprResult End = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayRangeEnd(D));
12352  if (End.isInvalid())
12353  return ExprError();
12354 
12355  Desig.AddDesignator(Designator::CreateArrayRangeDesignator(
12356  Start.get(), End.get(), D.getLBracketLoc(), D.getEllipsisLoc()));
12357 
12358  ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Start.get() != E->getArrayRangeStart(D) ||
12359  End.get() != E->getArrayRangeEnd(D);
12360 
12361  ArrayExprs.push_back(Start.get());
12362  ArrayExprs.push_back(End.get());
12363  }
12364 
12365  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12366  Init.get() == E->getInit() &&
12367  !ExprChanged)
12368  return E;
12369 
12370  return getDerived().RebuildDesignatedInitExpr(Desig, ArrayExprs,
12371  E->getEqualOrColonLoc(),
12372  E->usesGNUSyntax(), Init.get());
12373 }

12447 template<typename Derived>
12448 ExprResult
12449 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformParenListExpr(ParenListExpr *E) {
12450  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
12451  SmallVector<Expr*, 4> Inits;
12452  if (TransformExprs(E->getExprs(), E->getNumExprs(), true, Inits,
12453  &ArgumentChanged))
12454  return ExprError();
12455 
12456  return getDerived().RebuildParenListExpr(E->getLParenLoc(),
12457  Inits,
12458  E->getRParenLoc());
12459 }

12461 /// Transform an address-of-label expression.
12462 ///
12463 /// By default, the transformation of an address-of-label expression always
12464 /// rebuilds the expression, so that the label identifier can be resolved to
12465 /// the corresponding label statement by semantic analysis.
12466 template<typename Derived>
12467 ExprResult
12468 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAddrLabelExpr(AddrLabelExpr *E) {
12469  Decl *LD = getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getLabel()->getLocation(),
12470  E->getLabel());
12471  if (!LD)
12472  return ExprError();
12473 
12474  return getDerived().RebuildAddrLabelExpr(E->getAmpAmpLoc(), E->getLabelLoc(),
12475  cast<LabelDecl>(LD));
12476 }

12478 template<typename Derived>
12479 ExprResult
12480 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformStmtExpr(StmtExpr *E) {
12481  SemaRef.ActOnStartStmtExpr();
12482  StmtResult SubStmt
12483  = getDerived().TransformCompoundStmt(E->getSubStmt(), true);
12484  if (SubStmt.isInvalid()) {
12485  SemaRef.ActOnStmtExprError();
12486  return ExprError();
12487  }
12488 
12489  unsigned OldDepth = E->getTemplateDepth();
12490  unsigned NewDepth = getDerived().TransformTemplateDepth(OldDepth);
12491 
12492  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && OldDepth == NewDepth &&
12493  SubStmt.get() == E->getSubStmt()) {
12494  // Calling this an 'error' is unintuitive, but it does the right thing.
12495  SemaRef.ActOnStmtExprError();
12496  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
12497  }
12498 
12499  return getDerived().RebuildStmtExpr(E->getLParenLoc(), SubStmt.get(),
12500  E->getRParenLoc(), NewDepth);
12501 }

12503 template<typename Derived>
12504 ExprResult
12505 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformChooseExpr(ChooseExpr *E) {
12506  ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCond());
12507  if (Cond.isInvalid())
12508  return ExprError();
12509 
12510  ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
12511  if (LHS.isInvalid())
12512  return ExprError();
12513 
12514  ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
12515  if (RHS.isInvalid())
12516  return ExprError();
12517 
12518  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12519  Cond.get() == E->getCond() &&
12520  LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
12521  RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
12522  return E;
12523 
12524  return getDerived().RebuildChooseExpr(E->getBuiltinLoc(),
12525  Cond.get(), LHS.get(), RHS.get(),
12526  E->getRParenLoc());
12527 }

12535 template<typename Derived>
12536 ExprResult
12537 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXOperatorCallExpr(CXXOperatorCallExpr *E) {
12538  switch (E->getOperator()) {
12539  case OO_New:
12540  case OO_Delete:
12541  case OO_Array_New:
12542  case OO_Array_Delete:
12543  llvm_unreachable("new and delete operators cannot use CXXOperatorCallExpr");
12544 
12545  case OO_Subscript:
12546  case OO_Call: {
12547  // This is a call to an object's operator().
12548  assert(E->getNumArgs() >= 1 && "Object call is missing arguments");
12549 
12550  // Transform the object itself.
12551  ExprResult Object = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArg(0));
12552  if (Object.isInvalid())
12553  return ExprError();
12554 
12555  // FIXME: Poor location information
12556  SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc = SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(
12557  static_cast<Expr *>(Object.get())->getEndLoc());
12558 
12559  // Transform the call arguments.
12560  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
12561  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs() + 1, E->getNumArgs() - 1, true,
12562  Args))
12563  return ExprError();
12564 
12565  if (E->getOperator() == OO_Subscript)
12566  return getDerived().RebuildCxxSubscriptExpr(Object.get(), FakeLParenLoc,
12567  Args, E->getEndLoc());
12568 
12569  return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Object.get(), FakeLParenLoc, Args,
12570  E->getEndLoc());
12571  }
12572 
12573 #define OVERLOADED_OPERATOR(Name, Spelling, Token, Unary, Binary, MemberOnly) \
12574  case OO_##Name: \
12575  break;
12576 
12577 #define OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_MULTI(Name,Spelling,Unary,Binary,MemberOnly)
12578 #include "clang/Basic/OperatorKinds.def"
12579 
12580  case OO_Conditional:
12581  llvm_unreachable("conditional operator is not actually overloadable");
12582 
12583  case OO_None:
12584  case NUM_OVERLOADED_OPERATORS:
12585  llvm_unreachable("not an overloaded operator?");
12586  }
12587 
12588  ExprResult First;
12589  if (E->getOperator() == OO_Amp)
12590  First = getDerived().TransformAddressOfOperand(E->getArg(0));
12591  else
12592  First = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArg(0));
12593  if (First.isInvalid())
12594  return ExprError();
12595 
12596  ExprResult Second;
12597  if (E->getNumArgs() == 2) {
12598  Second =
12599  getDerived().TransformInitializer(E->getArg(1), /*NotCopyInit=*/false);
12600  if (Second.isInvalid())
12601  return ExprError();
12602  }
12603 
12604  Sema::FPFeaturesStateRAII FPFeaturesState(getSema());
12605  FPOptionsOverride NewOverrides(E->getFPFeatures());
12606  getSema().CurFPFeatures =
12607  NewOverrides.applyOverrides(getSema().getLangOpts());
12608  getSema().FpPragmaStack.CurrentValue = NewOverrides;
12609 
12610  Expr *Callee = E->getCallee();
12611  if (UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(Callee)) {
12612  LookupResult R(SemaRef, ULE->getName(), ULE->getNameLoc(),
12613  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
12614  if (getDerived().TransformOverloadExprDecls(ULE, ULE->requiresADL(), R))
12615  return ExprError();
12616 
12617  return getDerived().RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(
12618  E->getOperator(), E->getOperatorLoc(), Callee->getBeginLoc(),
12619  ULE->requiresADL(), R.asUnresolvedSet(), First.get(), Second.get());
12620  }
12621 
12622  UnresolvedSet<1> Functions;
12623  if (ImplicitCastExpr *ICE = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(Callee))
12624  Callee = ICE->getSubExprAsWritten();
12625  NamedDecl *DR = cast<DeclRefExpr>(Callee)->getDecl();
12626  ValueDecl *VD = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(
12627  getDerived().TransformDecl(DR->getLocation(), DR));
12628  if (!VD)
12629  return ExprError();
12630 
12631  if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(VD))
12632  Functions.addDecl(VD);
12633 
12634  return getDerived().RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(
12635  E->getOperator(), E->getOperatorLoc(), Callee->getBeginLoc(),
12636  /*RequiresADL=*/false, Functions, First.get(), Second.get());
12637 }

12645 template <typename Derived>
12646 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformSourceLocExpr(SourceLocExpr *E) {
12647  bool NeedRebuildFunc = E->getIdentKind() == SourceLocIdentKind::Function &&
12648  getSema().CurContext != E->getParentContext();
12649 
12650  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !NeedRebuildFunc)
12651  return E;
12652 
12653  return getDerived().RebuildSourceLocExpr(E->getIdentKind(), E->getType(),
12654  E->getBeginLoc(), E->getEndLoc(),
12655  getSema().CurContext);
12656 }

12658 template<typename Derived>
12659 ExprResult
12660 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCUDAKernelCallExpr(CUDAKernelCallExpr *E) {
12661  // Transform the callee.
12662  ExprResult Callee = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCallee());
12663  if (Callee.isInvalid())
12664  return ExprError();
12665 
12666  // Transform exec config.
12667  ExprResult EC = getDerived().TransformCallExpr(E->getConfig());
12668  if (EC.isInvalid())
12669  return ExprError();
12670 
12671  // Transform arguments.
12672  bool ArgChanged = false;
12673  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
12674  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
12675  &ArgChanged))
12676  return ExprError();
12677 
12678  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12679  Callee.get() == E->getCallee() &&
12680  !ArgChanged)
12681  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
12682 
12683  // FIXME: Wrong source location information for the '('.
12684  SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc
12685  = ((Expr *)Callee.get())->getSourceRange().getBegin();
12686  return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Callee.get(), FakeLParenLoc,
12687  Args,
12688  E->getRParenLoc(), EC.get());
12689 }

12691 template<typename Derived>
12692 ExprResult
12693 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXNamedCastExpr(CXXNamedCastExpr *E) {
12694  TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
12695  if (!Type)
12696  return ExprError();
12697 
12698  ExprResult SubExpr
12699  = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExprAsWritten());
12700  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
12701  return ExprError();
12702 
12703  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12704  Type == E->getTypeInfoAsWritten() &&
12705  SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
12706  return E;
12707  return getDerived().RebuildCXXNamedCastExpr(
12708  E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getStmtClass(), E->getAngleBrackets().getBegin(),
12709  Type, E->getAngleBrackets().getEnd(),
12710  // FIXME. this should be '(' location
12711  E->getAngleBrackets().getEnd(), SubExpr.get(), E->getRParenLoc());
12712 }

12845 template<typename Derived>
12846 ExprResult
12847 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXTypeidExpr(CXXTypeidExpr *E) {
12848  if (E->isTypeOperand()) {
12849  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo
12850  = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo());
12851  if (!TInfo)
12852  return ExprError();
12853 
12854  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12855  TInfo == E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo())
12856  return E;
12857 
12858  return getDerived().RebuildCXXTypeidExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
12859  TInfo, E->getEndLoc());
12860  }
12861 
12862  // Typeid's operand is an unevaluated context, unless it's a polymorphic
12863  // type. We must not unilaterally enter unevaluated context here, as then
12864  // semantic processing can re-transform an already transformed operand.
12865  Expr *Op = E->getExprOperand();
12866  auto EvalCtx = Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated;
12867  if (E->isGLValue())
12868  if (auto *RecordT = Op->getType()->getAs<RecordType>())
12869  if (cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordT->getDecl())->isPolymorphic())
12870  EvalCtx = SemaRef.ExprEvalContexts.back().Context;
12871 
12872  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(SemaRef, EvalCtx,
12873  Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
12874 
12875  ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(Op);
12876  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
12877  return ExprError();
12878 
12879  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12880  SubExpr.get() == E->getExprOperand())
12881  return E;
12882 
12883  return getDerived().RebuildCXXTypeidExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
12884  SubExpr.get(), E->getEndLoc());
12885 }

12887 template<typename Derived>
12888 ExprResult
12889 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXUuidofExpr(CXXUuidofExpr *E) {
12890  if (E->isTypeOperand()) {
12891  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo
12892  = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo());
12893  if (!TInfo)
12894  return ExprError();
12895 
12896  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12897  TInfo == E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo())
12898  return E;
12899 
12900  return getDerived().RebuildCXXUuidofExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
12901  TInfo, E->getEndLoc());
12902  }
12903 
12904  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
12905  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
12906 
12907  ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getExprOperand());
12908  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
12909  return ExprError();
12910 
12911  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12912  SubExpr.get() == E->getExprOperand())
12913  return E;
12914 
12915  return getDerived().RebuildCXXUuidofExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),

12932 template<typename Derived>
12933 ExprResult
12934 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXThisExpr(CXXThisExpr *E) {
12935 
12936  // In lambdas, the qualifiers of the type depends of where in
12937  // the call operator `this` appear, and we do not have a good way to
12938  // rebuild this information, so we transform the type.
12939  //
12940  // In other contexts, the type of `this` may be overrided
12941  // for type deduction, so we need to recompute it.
12942  //
12943  // Always recompute the type if we're in the body of a lambda, and
12944  // 'this' is dependent on a lambda's explicit object parameter.
12945  QualType T = [&]() {
12946  auto &S = getSema();
12947  if (E->isCapturedByCopyInLambdaWithExplicitObjectParameter())
12948  return S.getCurrentThisType();
12949  if (S.getCurLambda())
12950  return getDerived().TransformType(E->getType());
12951  return S.getCurrentThisType();
12952  }();
12953 
12954  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && T == E->getType()) {
12955  // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
12956  // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
12957  getSema().MarkThisReferenced(E);
12958  return E;
12959  }
12960 
12961  return getDerived().RebuildCXXThisExpr(E->getBeginLoc(), T, E->isImplicit());
12962 }

12965 ExprResult
12966 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXThrowExpr(CXXThrowExpr *E) {
12967  ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
12968  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
12969  return ExprError();
12970 
12971  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
12972  SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
12973  return E;
12974 
12975  return getDerived().RebuildCXXThrowExpr(E->getThrowLoc(), SubExpr.get(),
12976  E->isThrownVariableInScope());
12977 }

12979 template<typename Derived>
12980 ExprResult
12981 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXDefaultArgExpr(CXXDefaultArgExpr *E) {
12982  ParmVarDecl *Param = cast_or_null<ParmVarDecl>(
12983  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getParam()));
12984  if (!Param)
12985  return ExprError();
12986 
12987  ExprResult InitRes;
12988  if (E->hasRewrittenInit()) {
12989  InitRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRewrittenExpr());
12990  if (InitRes.isInvalid())
12991  return ExprError();
12992  }
12993 
12994  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && Param == E->getParam() &&
12995  E->getUsedContext() == SemaRef.CurContext &&
12996  InitRes.get() == E->getRewrittenExpr())
12997  return E;
12998 
12999  return getDerived().RebuildCXXDefaultArgExpr(E->getUsedLocation(), Param,
13000  InitRes.get());
13001 }

13035 template<typename Derived>
13036 ExprResult
13037 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXNewExpr(CXXNewExpr *E) {
13038  // Transform the type that we're allocating
13039  TypeSourceInfo *AllocTypeInfo =
13040  getDerived().TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(E->getAllocatedTypeSourceInfo());
13041  if (!AllocTypeInfo)
13042  return ExprError();
13043 
13044  // Transform the size of the array we're allocating (if any).
13045  std::optional<Expr *> ArraySize;
13046  if (E->isArray()) {
13047  ExprResult NewArraySize;
13048  if (std::optional<Expr *> OldArraySize = E->getArraySize()) {
13049  NewArraySize = getDerived().TransformExpr(*OldArraySize);
13050  if (NewArraySize.isInvalid())
13051  return ExprError();
13052  }
13053  ArraySize = NewArraySize.get();
13054  }
13055 
13056  // Transform the placement arguments (if any).
13057  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
13058  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> PlacementArgs;
13059  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getPlacementArgs(),
13060  E->getNumPlacementArgs(), true,
13061  PlacementArgs, &ArgumentChanged))
13062  return ExprError();
13063 
13064  // Transform the initializer (if any).
13065  Expr *OldInit = E->getInitializer();
13066  ExprResult NewInit;
13067  if (OldInit)
13068  NewInit = getDerived().TransformInitializer(OldInit, true);
13069  if (NewInit.isInvalid())
13070  return ExprError();
13071 
13072  // Transform new operator and delete operator.
13073  FunctionDecl *OperatorNew = nullptr;
13074  if (E->getOperatorNew()) {
13075  OperatorNew = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(
13076  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getOperatorNew()));
13077  if (!OperatorNew)
13078  return ExprError();
13079  }
13080 
13081  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = nullptr;
13082  if (E->getOperatorDelete()) {
13083  OperatorDelete = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(
13084  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getOperatorDelete()));
13085  if (!OperatorDelete)
13086  return ExprError();
13087  }
13088 
13089  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13090  AllocTypeInfo == E->getAllocatedTypeSourceInfo() &&
13091  ArraySize == E->getArraySize() &&
13092  NewInit.get() == OldInit &&
13093  OperatorNew == E->getOperatorNew() &&
13094  OperatorDelete == E->getOperatorDelete() &&
13095  !ArgumentChanged) {
13096  // Mark any declarations we need as referenced.
13097  // FIXME: instantiation-specific.
13098  if (OperatorNew)
13099  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), OperatorNew);
13100  if (OperatorDelete)
13101  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), OperatorDelete);
13102 
13103  if (E->isArray() && !E->getAllocatedType()->isDependentType()) {
13104  QualType ElementType
13105  = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(E->getAllocatedType());
13106  if (const RecordType *RecordT = ElementType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
13107  CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RecordT->getDecl());
13108  if (CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = SemaRef.LookupDestructor(Record)) {
13109  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), Destructor);
13110  }
13111  }
13112  }
13113 
13114  return E;
13115  }
13116 
13117  QualType AllocType = AllocTypeInfo->getType();
13118  if (!ArraySize) {
13119  // If no array size was specified, but the new expression was
13120  // instantiated with an array type (e.g., "new T" where T is
13121  // instantiated with "int[4]"), extract the outer bound from the
13122  // array type as our array size. We do this with constant and
13123  // dependently-sized array types.
13124  const ArrayType *ArrayT = SemaRef.Context.getAsArrayType(AllocType);
13125  if (!ArrayT) {
13126  // Do nothing
13127  } else if (const ConstantArrayType *ConsArrayT
13128  = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(ArrayT)) {
13129  ArraySize = IntegerLiteral::Create(SemaRef.Context, ConsArrayT->getSize(),
13130  SemaRef.Context.getSizeType(),
13131  /*FIXME:*/ E->getBeginLoc());
13132  AllocType = ConsArrayT->getElementType();
13133  } else if (const DependentSizedArrayType *DepArrayT
13134  = dyn_cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(ArrayT)) {
13135  if (DepArrayT->getSizeExpr()) {
13136  ArraySize = DepArrayT->getSizeExpr();
13137  AllocType = DepArrayT->getElementType();
13138  }
13139  }
13140  }
13141 
13142  return getDerived().RebuildCXXNewExpr(
13143  E->getBeginLoc(), E->isGlobalNew(),
13144  /*FIXME:*/ E->getBeginLoc(), PlacementArgs,
13145  /*FIXME:*/ E->getBeginLoc(), E->getTypeIdParens(), AllocType,
13146  AllocTypeInfo, ArraySize, E->getDirectInitRange(), NewInit.get());
13147 }
13148 
13149 template<typename Derived>
13150 ExprResult
13151 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXDeleteExpr(CXXDeleteExpr *E) {
13152  ExprResult Operand = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArgument());
13153  if (Operand.isInvalid())
13154  return ExprError();
13155 
13156  // Transform the delete operator, if known.
13157  FunctionDecl *OperatorDelete = nullptr;
13158  if (E->getOperatorDelete()) {
13159  OperatorDelete = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(
13160  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getOperatorDelete()));
13161  if (!OperatorDelete)
13162  return ExprError();
13163  }
13164 
13165  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13166  Operand.get() == E->getArgument() &&
13167  OperatorDelete == E->getOperatorDelete()) {
13168  // Mark any declarations we need as referenced.
13169  // FIXME: instantiation-specific.
13170  if (OperatorDelete)
13171  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), OperatorDelete);
13172 
13173  if (!E->getArgument()->isTypeDependent()) {
13174  QualType Destroyed = SemaRef.Context.getBaseElementType(
13175  E->getDestroyedType());
13176  if (const RecordType *DestroyedRec = Destroyed->getAs<RecordType>()) {
13177  CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DestroyedRec->getDecl());
13178  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(),
13179  SemaRef.LookupDestructor(Record));
13180  }
13181  }
13182 
13183  return E;
13184  }
13185 
13186  return getDerived().RebuildCXXDeleteExpr(
13187  E->getBeginLoc(), E->isGlobalDelete(), E->isArrayForm(), Operand.get());
13188 }

13190 template<typename Derived>
13191 ExprResult
13192 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(
13193  CXXPseudoDestructorExpr *E) {
13194  ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
13195  if (Base.isInvalid())
13196  return ExprError();
13197 
13198  ParsedType ObjectTypePtr;
13199  bool MayBePseudoDestructor = false;
13200  Base = SemaRef.ActOnStartCXXMemberReference(nullptr, Base.get(),
13201  E->getOperatorLoc(),
13202  E->isArrow()? tok::arrow : tok::period,
13203  ObjectTypePtr,
13204  MayBePseudoDestructor);
13205  if (Base.isInvalid())
13206  return ExprError();
13207 
13208  QualType ObjectType = ObjectTypePtr.get();
13209  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = E->getQualifierLoc();
13210  if (QualifierLoc) {
13211  QualifierLoc
13212  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc, ObjectType);
13213  if (!QualifierLoc)
13214  return ExprError();
13215  }
13216  CXXScopeSpec SS;
13217  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
13218 
13219  PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destroyed;
13220  if (E->getDestroyedTypeInfo()) {
13221  TypeSourceInfo *DestroyedTypeInfo
13222  = getDerived().TransformTypeInObjectScope(E->getDestroyedTypeInfo(),
13223  ObjectType, nullptr, SS);
13224  if (!DestroyedTypeInfo)
13225  return ExprError();
13226  Destroyed = DestroyedTypeInfo;
13227  } else if (!ObjectType.isNull() && ObjectType->isDependentType()) {
13228  // We aren't likely to be able to resolve the identifier down to a type
13229  // now anyway, so just retain the identifier.
13230  Destroyed = PseudoDestructorTypeStorage(E->getDestroyedTypeIdentifier(),
13231  E->getDestroyedTypeLoc());
13232  } else {
13233  // Look for a destructor known with the given name.
13234  ParsedType T = SemaRef.getDestructorName(
13235  *E->getDestroyedTypeIdentifier(), E->getDestroyedTypeLoc(),
13236  /*Scope=*/nullptr, SS, ObjectTypePtr, false);
13237  if (!T)
13238  return ExprError();
13239 
13240  Destroyed
13241  = SemaRef.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.GetTypeFromParser(T),
13242  E->getDestroyedTypeLoc());
13243  }
13244 
13245  TypeSourceInfo *ScopeTypeInfo = nullptr;
13246  if (E->getScopeTypeInfo()) {
13247  CXXScopeSpec EmptySS;
13248  ScopeTypeInfo = getDerived().TransformTypeInObjectScope(
13249  E->getScopeTypeInfo(), ObjectType, nullptr, EmptySS);
13250  if (!ScopeTypeInfo)
13251  return ExprError();
13252  }
13253 
13254  return getDerived().RebuildCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(Base.get(),
13255  E->getOperatorLoc(),
13256  E->isArrow(),
13257  SS,
13258  ScopeTypeInfo,
13259  E->getColonColonLoc(),
13260  E->getTildeLoc(),
13261  Destroyed);
13262 }
13263 
13264 template <typename Derived>
13265 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOverloadExprDecls(OverloadExpr *Old,
13266  bool RequiresADL,
13267  LookupResult &R) {
13268  // Transform all the decls.
13269  bool AllEmptyPacks = true;
13270  for (auto *OldD : Old->decls()) {
13271  Decl *InstD = getDerived().TransformDecl(Old->getNameLoc(), OldD);
13272  if (!InstD) {
13273  // Silently ignore these if a UsingShadowDecl instantiated to nothing.
13274  // This can happen because of dependent hiding.
13275  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(OldD))
13276  continue;
13277  else {
13278  R.clear();
13279  return true;
13280  }
13281  }
13282 
13283  // Expand using pack declarations.
13284  NamedDecl *SingleDecl = cast<NamedDecl>(InstD);
13285  ArrayRef<NamedDecl*> Decls = SingleDecl;
13286  if (auto *UPD = dyn_cast<UsingPackDecl>(InstD))
13287  Decls = UPD->expansions();
13288 
13289  // Expand using declarations.
13290  for (auto *D : Decls) {
13291  if (auto *UD = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D)) {
13292  for (auto *SD : UD->shadows())
13293  R.addDecl(SD);
13294  } else {
13295  R.addDecl(D);
13296  }
13297  }
13298 
13299  AllEmptyPacks &= Decls.empty();
13300  };
13301 
13302  // C++ [temp.res]/8.4.2:
13303  // The program is ill-formed, no diagnostic required, if [...] lookup for
13304  // a name in the template definition found a using-declaration, but the
13305  // lookup in the corresponding scope in the instantiation odoes not find
13306  // any declarations because the using-declaration was a pack expansion and
13307  // the corresponding pack is empty
13308  if (AllEmptyPacks && !RequiresADL) {
13309  getSema().Diag(Old->getNameLoc(), diag::err_using_pack_expansion_empty)
13310  << isa<UnresolvedMemberExpr>(Old) << Old->getName();
13311  return true;
13312  }
13313 
13314  // Resolve a kind, but don't do any further analysis. If it's
13315  // ambiguous, the callee needs to deal with it.
13316  R.resolveKind();
13317  return false;
13318 }
13319 
13320 template <typename Derived>
13321 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnresolvedLookupExpr(
13322  UnresolvedLookupExpr *Old) {
13323  return TransformUnresolvedLookupExpr(Old, /*IsAddressOfOperand=*/false);
13324 }
13325 
13326 template <typename Derived>
13327 ExprResult
13328 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnresolvedLookupExpr(UnresolvedLookupExpr *Old,
13329  bool IsAddressOfOperand) {
13330  LookupResult R(SemaRef, Old->getName(), Old->getNameLoc(),
13331  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
13332 
13333  // Transform the declaration set.
13334  if (TransformOverloadExprDecls(Old, Old->requiresADL(), R))
13335  return ExprError();
13336 
13337  // Rebuild the nested-name qualifier, if present.
13338  CXXScopeSpec SS;
13339  if (Old->getQualifierLoc()) {
13340  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc
13341  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Old->getQualifierLoc());
13342  if (!QualifierLoc)
13343  return ExprError();
13344 
13345  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
13346  }
13347 
13348  if (Old->getNamingClass()) {
13349  CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass
13350  = cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(
13351  Old->getNameLoc(),
13352  Old->getNamingClass()));
13353  if (!NamingClass) {
13354  R.clear();
13355  return ExprError();
13356  }
13357 
13358  R.setNamingClass(NamingClass);
13359  }
13360 
13361  // Rebuild the template arguments, if any.
13362  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = Old->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
13363  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs(Old->getLAngleLoc(), Old->getRAngleLoc());
13364  if (Old->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() &&
13365  getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(Old->getTemplateArgs(),
13366  Old->getNumTemplateArgs(),
13367  TransArgs)) {
13368  R.clear();
13369  return ExprError();
13370  }
13371 
13372  // An UnresolvedLookupExpr can refer to a class member. This occurs e.g. when
13373  // a non-static data member is named in an unevaluated operand, or when
13374  // a member is named in a dependent class scope function template explicit
13375  // specialization that is neither declared static nor with an explicit object
13376  // parameter.
13377  if (SemaRef.isPotentialImplicitMemberAccess(SS, R, IsAddressOfOperand))
13378  return SemaRef.BuildPossibleImplicitMemberExpr(
13379  SS, TemplateKWLoc, R,
13380  Old->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() ? &TransArgs : nullptr,
13381  /*S=*/nullptr);
13382 
13383  // If we have neither explicit template arguments, nor the template keyword,
13384  // it's a normal declaration name or member reference.
13385  if (!Old->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() && !TemplateKWLoc.isValid())
13386  return getDerived().RebuildDeclarationNameExpr(SS, R, Old->requiresADL());
13387 
13388  // If we have template arguments, then rebuild the template-id expression.
13389  return getDerived().RebuildTemplateIdExpr(SS, TemplateKWLoc, R,
13390  Old->requiresADL(), &TransArgs);
13391 }
13392 
13393 template<typename Derived>
13394 ExprResult
13395 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeTraitExpr(TypeTraitExpr *E) {
13396  bool ArgChanged = false;
13397  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> Args;
13398  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumArgs(); I != N; ++I) {
13399  TypeSourceInfo *From = E->getArg(I);
13400  TypeLoc FromTL = From->getTypeLoc();
13401  if (!FromTL.getAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>()) {
13402  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
13403  TLB.reserve(FromTL.getFullDataSize());
13404  QualType To = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, FromTL);
13405  if (To.isNull())
13406  return ExprError();
13407 
13408  if (To == From->getType())
13409  Args.push_back(From);
13410  else {
13411  Args.push_back(TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, To));
13412  ArgChanged = true;
13413  }
13414  continue;
13415  }
13416 
13417  ArgChanged = true;
13418 
13419  // We have a pack expansion. Instantiate it.
13420  PackExpansionTypeLoc ExpansionTL = FromTL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>();
13421  TypeLoc PatternTL = ExpansionTL.getPatternLoc();
13422  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
13423  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(PatternTL, Unexpanded);
13424 
13425  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
13426  // be expanded.
13427  bool Expand = true;
13428  bool RetainExpansion = false;
13429  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions =
13430  ExpansionTL.getTypePtr()->getNumExpansions();
13431  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
13432  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
13433  PatternTL.getSourceRange(),
13434  Unexpanded,
13435  Expand, RetainExpansion,
13436  NumExpansions))
13437  return ExprError();
13438 
13439  if (!Expand) {
13440  // The transform has determined that we should perform a simple
13441  // transformation on the pack expansion, producing another pack
13442  // expansion.
13443  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
13444 
13445  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
13446  TLB.reserve(From->getTypeLoc().getFullDataSize());
13447 
13448  QualType To = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, PatternTL);
13449  if (To.isNull())
13450  return ExprError();
13451 
13452  To = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansionType(To,
13453  PatternTL.getSourceRange(),
13454  ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
13455  NumExpansions);
13456  if (To.isNull())
13457  return ExprError();
13458 
13459  PackExpansionTypeLoc ToExpansionTL
13460  = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(To);
13461  ToExpansionTL.setEllipsisLoc(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc());
13462  Args.push_back(TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, To));
13463  continue;
13464  }
13465 
13466  // Expand the pack expansion by substituting for each argument in the
13467  // pack(s).
13468  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
13469  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, I);
13470  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
13471  TLB.reserve(PatternTL.getFullDataSize());
13472  QualType To = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, PatternTL);
13473  if (To.isNull())
13474  return ExprError();
13475 
13476  if (To->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
13477  To = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansionType(To,
13478  PatternTL.getSourceRange(),
13479  ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
13480  NumExpansions);
13481  if (To.isNull())
13482  return ExprError();
13483 
13484  PackExpansionTypeLoc ToExpansionTL
13485  = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(To);
13486  ToExpansionTL.setEllipsisLoc(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc());
13487  }
13488 
13489  Args.push_back(TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, To));
13490  }
13491 
13492  if (!RetainExpansion)
13493  continue;
13494 
13495  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
13496  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
13497  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
13498 
13499  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
13500  TLB.reserve(From->getTypeLoc().getFullDataSize());
13501 
13502  QualType To = getDerived().TransformType(TLB, PatternTL);
13503  if (To.isNull())
13504  return ExprError();
13505 
13506  To = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansionType(To,
13507  PatternTL.getSourceRange(),
13508  ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
13509  NumExpansions);
13510  if (To.isNull())
13511  return ExprError();
13512 
13513  PackExpansionTypeLoc ToExpansionTL
13514  = TLB.push<PackExpansionTypeLoc>(To);
13515  ToExpansionTL.setEllipsisLoc(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc());
13516  Args.push_back(TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context, To));
13517  }
13518 
13519  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !ArgChanged)
13520  return E;
13521 
13522  return getDerived().RebuildTypeTrait(E->getTrait(), E->getBeginLoc(), Args,
13523  E->getEndLoc());
13524 }

13527 ExprResult
13528 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformConceptSpecializationExpr(
13529  ConceptSpecializationExpr *E) {
13530  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *Old = E->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
13531  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs(Old->LAngleLoc, Old->RAngleLoc);
13532  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(Old->getTemplateArgs(),
13533  Old->NumTemplateArgs, TransArgs))

13542 template<typename Derived>
13543 ExprResult
13544 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformRequiresExpr(RequiresExpr *E) {
13545  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl*, 4> TransParams;
13546  SmallVector<QualType, 4> TransParamTypes;
13547  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder ExtParamInfos;
13548 
13549  // C++2a [expr.prim.req]p2
13550  // Expressions appearing within a requirement-body are unevaluated operands.
13551  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Ctx(
13552  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
13553  Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
13554 
13555  RequiresExprBodyDecl *Body = RequiresExprBodyDecl::Create(
13556  getSema().Context, getSema().CurContext,
13557  E->getBody()->getBeginLoc());
13558 
13559  Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(getSema(), Body, /*NewThisContext*/false);
13560 
13561  ExprResult TypeParamResult = getDerived().TransformRequiresTypeParams(
13562  E->getRequiresKWLoc(), E->getRBraceLoc(), E, Body,
13563  E->getLocalParameters(), TransParamTypes, TransParams, ExtParamInfos);
13564 
13565  for (ParmVarDecl *Param : TransParams)
13566  if (Param)
13567  Param->setDeclContext(Body);
13568 
13569  // On failure to transform, TransformRequiresTypeParams returns an expression
13570  // in the event that the transformation of the type params failed in some way.
13571  // It is expected that this will result in a 'not satisfied' Requires clause
13572  // when instantiating.
13573  if (!TypeParamResult.isUnset())
13574  return TypeParamResult;
13575 
13576  SmallVector<concepts::Requirement *, 4> TransReqs;
13577  if (getDerived().TransformRequiresExprRequirements(E->getRequirements(),
13578  TransReqs))
13579  return ExprError();
13580 
13581  for (concepts::Requirement *Req : TransReqs) {
13582  if (auto *ER = dyn_cast<concepts::ExprRequirement>(Req)) {
13583  if (ER->getReturnTypeRequirement().isTypeConstraint()) {
13584  ER->getReturnTypeRequirement()
13585  .getTypeConstraintTemplateParameterList()->getParam(0)
13586  ->setDeclContext(Body);
13587  }
13588  }
13589  }
13590 
13591  return getDerived().RebuildRequiresExpr(
13592  E->getRequiresKWLoc(), Body, E->getLParenLoc(), TransParams,
13593  E->getRParenLoc(), TransReqs, E->getRBraceLoc());
13594 }
13595 
13596 template<typename Derived>
13597 bool TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformRequiresExprRequirements(
13598  ArrayRef<concepts::Requirement *> Reqs,
13599  SmallVectorImpl<concepts::Requirement *> &Transformed) {
13600  for (concepts::Requirement *Req : Reqs) {
13601  concepts::Requirement *TransReq = nullptr;
13602  if (auto *TypeReq = dyn_cast<concepts::TypeRequirement>(Req))
13603  TransReq = getDerived().TransformTypeRequirement(TypeReq);
13604  else if (auto *ExprReq = dyn_cast<concepts::ExprRequirement>(Req))
13605  TransReq = getDerived().TransformExprRequirement(ExprReq);
13606  else
13607  TransReq = getDerived().TransformNestedRequirement(
13608  cast<concepts::NestedRequirement>(Req));
13609  if (!TransReq)
13610  return true;
13611  Transformed.push_back(TransReq);
13612  }
13613  return false;
13614 }
13615 
13616 template<typename Derived>
13617 concepts::TypeRequirement *
13618 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformTypeRequirement(
13619  concepts::TypeRequirement *Req) {
13620  if (Req->isSubstitutionFailure()) {
13621  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
13622  return getDerived().RebuildTypeRequirement(
13623  Req->getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
13624  return Req;
13625  }
13626  TypeSourceInfo *TransType = getDerived().TransformType(Req->getType());
13627  if (!TransType)
13628  return nullptr;
13629  return getDerived().RebuildTypeRequirement(TransType);
13630 }
13631 
13632 template<typename Derived>
13633 concepts::ExprRequirement *
13634 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExprRequirement(concepts::ExprRequirement *Req) {
13635  llvm::PointerUnion<Expr *, concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *> TransExpr;
13636  if (Req->isExprSubstitutionFailure())
13637  TransExpr = Req->getExprSubstitutionDiagnostic();
13638  else {
13639  ExprResult TransExprRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(Req->getExpr());
13640  if (TransExprRes.isUsable() && TransExprRes.get()->hasPlaceholderType())
13641  TransExprRes = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(TransExprRes.get());
13642  if (TransExprRes.isInvalid())
13643  return nullptr;
13644  TransExpr = TransExprRes.get();
13645  }
13646 
13647  std::optional<concepts::ExprRequirement::ReturnTypeRequirement> TransRetReq;
13648  const auto &RetReq = Req->getReturnTypeRequirement();
13649  if (RetReq.isEmpty())
13650  TransRetReq.emplace();
13651  else if (RetReq.isSubstitutionFailure())
13652  TransRetReq.emplace(RetReq.getSubstitutionDiagnostic());
13653  else if (RetReq.isTypeConstraint()) {
13654  TemplateParameterList *OrigTPL =
13655  RetReq.getTypeConstraintTemplateParameterList();
13656  TemplateParameterList *TPL =
13657  getDerived().TransformTemplateParameterList(OrigTPL);
13658  if (!TPL)
13659  return nullptr;
13660  TransRetReq.emplace(TPL);
13661  }
13662  assert(TransRetReq && "All code paths leading here must set TransRetReq");
13663  if (Expr *E = TransExpr.dyn_cast<Expr *>())
13664  return getDerived().RebuildExprRequirement(E, Req->isSimple(),
13665  Req->getNoexceptLoc(),
13666  std::move(*TransRetReq));
13667  return getDerived().RebuildExprRequirement(
13668  TransExpr.get<concepts::Requirement::SubstitutionDiagnostic *>(),
13669  Req->isSimple(), Req->getNoexceptLoc(), std::move(*TransRetReq));
13670 }
13671 
13672 template<typename Derived>
13673 concepts::NestedRequirement *
13674 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformNestedRequirement(
13675  concepts::NestedRequirement *Req) {
13676  if (Req->hasInvalidConstraint()) {
13677  if (getDerived().AlwaysRebuild())
13678  return getDerived().RebuildNestedRequirement(
13679  Req->getInvalidConstraintEntity(), Req->getConstraintSatisfaction());
13680  return Req;
13681  }
13682  ExprResult TransConstraint =
13683  getDerived().TransformExpr(Req->getConstraintExpr());
13684  if (TransConstraint.isInvalid())
13685  return nullptr;
13686  return getDerived().RebuildNestedRequirement(TransConstraint.get());
13687 }
13688 
13689 template<typename Derived>
13690 ExprResult
13691 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformArrayTypeTraitExpr(ArrayTypeTraitExpr *E) {
13692  TypeSourceInfo *T = getDerived().TransformType(E->getQueriedTypeSourceInfo());
13693  if (!T)
13694  return ExprError();
13695 
13696  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13697  T == E->getQueriedTypeSourceInfo())
13698  return E;
13699 
13700  ExprResult SubExpr;
13701  {
13702  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
13703  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
13704  SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getDimensionExpression());
13705  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
13706  return ExprError();
13707 
13708  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getDimensionExpression())
13709  return E;
13710  }
13711 
13712  return getDerived().RebuildArrayTypeTrait(E->getTrait(), E->getBeginLoc(), T,
13713  SubExpr.get(), E->getEndLoc());
13714 }
13715 
13716 template<typename Derived>
13717 ExprResult
13718 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExpressionTraitExpr(ExpressionTraitExpr *E) {
13719  ExprResult SubExpr;
13720  {
13721  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
13722  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
13723  SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getQueriedExpression());
13724  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
13725  return ExprError();
13726 
13727  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getQueriedExpression())
13728  return E;
13729  }
13730 
13731  return getDerived().RebuildExpressionTrait(E->getTrait(), E->getBeginLoc(),
13732  SubExpr.get(), E->getEndLoc());
13733 }
13734 
13735 template <typename Derived>
13736 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformParenDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13737  ParenExpr *PE, DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *DRE, bool AddrTaken,
13738  TypeSourceInfo **RecoveryTSI) {
13739  ExprResult NewDRE = getDerived().TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13740  DRE, AddrTaken, RecoveryTSI);
13741 
13742  // Propagate both errors and recovered types, which return ExprEmpty.
13743  if (!NewDRE.isUsable())
13744  return NewDRE;
13745 
13746  // We got an expr, wrap it up in parens.
13747  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && NewDRE.get() == DRE)
13748  return PE;
13749  return getDerived().RebuildParenExpr(NewDRE.get(), PE->getLParen(),
13750  PE->getRParen());
13751 }
13752 
13753 template <typename Derived>
13754 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13755  DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *E) {
13756  return TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(E, /*IsAddressOfOperand=*/false,
13757  nullptr);
13758 }
13759 
13760 template <typename Derived>
13761 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13762  DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *E, bool IsAddressOfOperand,
13763  TypeSourceInfo **RecoveryTSI) {
13764  assert(E->getQualifierLoc());
13765  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc =
13766  getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
13767  if (!QualifierLoc)
13768  return ExprError();
13769  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = E->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
13770 
13771  // TODO: If this is a conversion-function-id, verify that the
13772  // destination type name (if present) resolves the same way after
13773  // instantiation as it did in the local scope.
13774 
13775  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo =
13776  getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(E->getNameInfo());
13777  if (!NameInfo.getName())
13778  return ExprError();
13779 
13780  if (!E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
13781  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() &&
13782  // Note: it is sufficient to compare the Name component of NameInfo:
13783  // if name has not changed, DNLoc has not changed either.
13784  NameInfo.getName() == E->getDeclName())
13785  return E;
13786 
13787  return getDerived().RebuildDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13788  QualifierLoc, TemplateKWLoc, NameInfo, /*TemplateArgs=*/nullptr,
13789  IsAddressOfOperand, RecoveryTSI);
13790  }
13791 
13792  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs(E->getLAngleLoc(), E->getRAngleLoc());
13793  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(
13794  E->getTemplateArgs(), E->getNumTemplateArgs(), TransArgs))
13795  return ExprError();
13796 
13797  return getDerived().RebuildDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
13798  QualifierLoc, TemplateKWLoc, NameInfo, &TransArgs, IsAddressOfOperand,
13799  RecoveryTSI);
13800 }
13801 
13802 template<typename Derived>
13803 ExprResult
13804 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXConstructExpr(CXXConstructExpr *E) {
13805  // CXXConstructExprs other than for list-initialization and
13806  // CXXTemporaryObjectExpr are always implicit, so when we have
13807  // a 1-argument construction we just transform that argument.
13808  if (getDerived().AllowSkippingCXXConstructExpr() &&
13809  ((E->getNumArgs() == 1 ||
13810  (E->getNumArgs() > 1 && getDerived().DropCallArgument(E->getArg(1)))) &&
13811  (!getDerived().DropCallArgument(E->getArg(0))) &&
13812  !E->isListInitialization()))
13813  return getDerived().TransformInitializer(E->getArg(0),
13814  /*DirectInit*/ false);
13815 
13816  TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, /*FIXME*/ E->getBeginLoc(), DeclarationName());
13817 
13818  QualType T = getDerived().TransformType(E->getType());
13819  if (T.isNull())
13820  return ExprError();
13821 
13822  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(
13823  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getConstructor()));
13824  if (!Constructor)
13825  return ExprError();
13826 
13827  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
13828  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
13829  {
13830  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
13831  getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
13832  E->isListInitialization());
13833  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
13834  &ArgumentChanged))
13835  return ExprError();
13836  }
13837 
13838  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13839  T == E->getType() &&
13840  Constructor == E->getConstructor() &&
13841  !ArgumentChanged) {
13842  // Mark the constructor as referenced.
13843  // FIXME: Instantiation-specific
13844  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), Constructor);
13845  return E;
13846  }
13847 
13848  return getDerived().RebuildCXXConstructExpr(
13849  T, /*FIXME:*/ E->getBeginLoc(), Constructor, E->isElidable(), Args,
13850  E->hadMultipleCandidates(), E->isListInitialization(),
13851  E->isStdInitListInitialization(), E->requiresZeroInitialization(),
13852  E->getConstructionKind(), E->getParenOrBraceRange());
13853 }
13854 
13855 template<typename Derived>
13856 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXInheritedCtorInitExpr(
13857  CXXInheritedCtorInitExpr *E) {
13858  QualType T = getDerived().TransformType(E->getType());
13859  if (T.isNull())
13860  return ExprError();
13861 
13862  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(
13863  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getConstructor()));
13864  if (!Constructor)
13865  return ExprError();
13866 
13867  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13868  T == E->getType() &&
13869  Constructor == E->getConstructor()) {
13870  // Mark the constructor as referenced.
13871  // FIXME: Instantiation-specific
13872  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), Constructor);
13873  return E;
13874  }
13875 
13876  return getDerived().RebuildCXXInheritedCtorInitExpr(
13877  T, E->getLocation(), Constructor,
13878  E->constructsVBase(), E->inheritedFromVBase());
13879 }
