13881 /// Transform a C++ temporary-binding expression.
13882 ///
13883 /// Since CXXBindTemporaryExpr nodes are implicitly generated, we just
13884 /// transform the subexpression and return that.
13885 template<typename Derived>
13886 ExprResult
13887 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXBindTemporaryExpr(CXXBindTemporaryExpr *E) {
13888  if (auto *Dtor = E->getTemporary()->getDestructor())
13889  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(),
13890  const_cast<CXXDestructorDecl *>(Dtor));
13891  return getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
13892 }
13893 
13894 /// Transform a C++ expression that contains cleanups that should
13895 /// be run after the expression is evaluated.
13896 ///
13897 /// Since ExprWithCleanups nodes are implicitly generated, we
13898 /// just transform the subexpression and return that.
13899 template<typename Derived>
13900 ExprResult
13901 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExprWithCleanups(ExprWithCleanups *E) {
13902  return getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
13903 }
13904 
13905 template<typename Derived>
13906 ExprResult
13907 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXTemporaryObjectExpr(
13908  CXXTemporaryObjectExpr *E) {
13909  TypeSourceInfo *T =
13910  getDerived().TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(E->getTypeSourceInfo());
13911  if (!T)
13912  return ExprError();
13913 
13914  CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = cast_or_null<CXXConstructorDecl>(
13915  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getBeginLoc(), E->getConstructor()));
13916  if (!Constructor)
13917  return ExprError();
13918 
13919  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
13920  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
13921  Args.reserve(E->getNumArgs());
13922  {
13923  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
13924  getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
13925  E->isListInitialization());
13926  if (TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
13927  &ArgumentChanged))
13928  return ExprError();
13929  }
13930 
13931  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
13932  T == E->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
13933  Constructor == E->getConstructor() &&
13934  !ArgumentChanged) {
13935  // FIXME: Instantiation-specific
13936  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(E->getBeginLoc(), Constructor);
13937  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
13938  }
13939 
13940  // FIXME: We should just pass E->isListInitialization(), but we're not
13941  // prepared to handle list-initialization without a child InitListExpr.
13942  SourceLocation LParenLoc = T->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc();
13943  return getDerived().RebuildCXXTemporaryObjectExpr(
13944  T, LParenLoc, Args, E->getEndLoc(),
13945  /*ListInitialization=*/LParenLoc.isInvalid());
13946 }
13947 
13948 template<typename Derived>
13949 ExprResult
13950 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformLambdaExpr(LambdaExpr *E) {
13951  // Transform any init-capture expressions before entering the scope of the
13952  // lambda body, because they are not semantically within that scope.
13953  typedef std::pair<ExprResult, QualType> InitCaptureInfoTy;
13954  struct TransformedInitCapture {
13955  // The location of the ... if the result is retaining a pack expansion.
13956  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
13957  // Zero or more expansions of the init-capture.
13958  SmallVector<InitCaptureInfoTy, 4> Expansions;
13959  };
13960  SmallVector<TransformedInitCapture, 4> InitCaptures;
13961  InitCaptures.resize(E->explicit_capture_end() - E->explicit_capture_begin());
13962  for (LambdaExpr::capture_iterator C = E->capture_begin(),
13963  CEnd = E->capture_end();
13964  C != CEnd; ++C) {
13965  if (!E->isInitCapture(C))
13966  continue;
13967 
13968  TransformedInitCapture &Result = InitCaptures[C - E->capture_begin()];
13969  auto *OldVD = cast<VarDecl>(C->getCapturedVar());
13970 
13971  auto SubstInitCapture = [&](SourceLocation EllipsisLoc,
13972  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions) {
13973  ExprResult NewExprInitResult = getDerived().TransformInitializer(
13974  OldVD->getInit(), OldVD->getInitStyle() == VarDecl::CallInit);
13975 
13976  if (NewExprInitResult.isInvalid()) {
13977  Result.Expansions.push_back(InitCaptureInfoTy(ExprError(), QualType()));
13978  return;
13979  }
13980  Expr *NewExprInit = NewExprInitResult.get();
13981 
13982  QualType NewInitCaptureType =
13983  getSema().buildLambdaInitCaptureInitialization(
13984  C->getLocation(), C->getCaptureKind() == LCK_ByRef,
13985  EllipsisLoc, NumExpansions, OldVD->getIdentifier(),
13986  cast<VarDecl>(C->getCapturedVar())->getInitStyle() !=
13987  VarDecl::CInit,
13988  NewExprInit);
13989  Result.Expansions.push_back(
13990  InitCaptureInfoTy(NewExprInit, NewInitCaptureType));
13991  };
13992 
13993  // If this is an init-capture pack, consider expanding the pack now.
13994  if (OldVD->isParameterPack()) {
13995  PackExpansionTypeLoc ExpansionTL = OldVD->getTypeSourceInfo()
13996  ->getTypeLoc()
13997  .castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>();
13998  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
13999  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(OldVD->getInit(), Unexpanded);
14000 
14001  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
14002  // be expanded.
14003  bool Expand = true;
14004  bool RetainExpansion = false;
14005  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions =
14006  ExpansionTL.getTypePtr()->getNumExpansions();
14007  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
14008  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(
14009  ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(),
14010  OldVD->getInit()->getSourceRange(), Unexpanded, Expand,
14011  RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
14012  return ExprError();
14013  if (Expand) {
14014  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
14015  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
14016  SubstInitCapture(SourceLocation(), std::nullopt);
14017  }
14018  }
14019  if (!Expand || RetainExpansion) {
14020  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
14021  SubstInitCapture(ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc(), NumExpansions);
14022  Result.EllipsisLoc = ExpansionTL.getEllipsisLoc();
14023  }
14024  } else {
14025  SubstInitCapture(SourceLocation(), std::nullopt);
14026  }
14027  }
14028 
14029  LambdaScopeInfo *LSI = getSema().PushLambdaScope();
14030  Sema::FunctionScopeRAII FuncScopeCleanup(getSema());
14031 
14032  // Create the local class that will describe the lambda.
14033 
14034  // FIXME: DependencyKind below is wrong when substituting inside a templated
14035  // context that isn't a DeclContext (such as a variable template), or when
14036  // substituting an unevaluated lambda inside of a function's parameter's type
14037  // - as parameter types are not instantiated from within a function's DC. We
14038  // use evaluation contexts to distinguish the function parameter case.
14039  CXXRecordDecl::LambdaDependencyKind DependencyKind =
14040  CXXRecordDecl::LDK_Unknown;
14041  DeclContext *DC = getSema().CurContext;
14042  // A RequiresExprBodyDecl is not interesting for dependencies.
14043  // For the following case,
14044  //
14045  // template <typename>
14046  // concept C = requires { [] {}; };
14047  //
14048  // template <class F>
14049  // struct Widget;
14050  //
14051  // template <C F>
14052  // struct Widget<F> {};
14053  //
14054  // While we are substituting Widget<F>, the parent of DC would be
14055  // the template specialization itself. Thus, the lambda expression
14056  // will be deemed as dependent even if there are no dependent template
14057  // arguments.
14058  // (A ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl is always a dependent context.)
14059  while (DC->getDeclKind() == Decl::Kind::RequiresExprBody)
14060  DC = DC->getParent();
14061  if ((getSema().isUnevaluatedContext() ||
14062  getSema().isConstantEvaluatedContext()) &&
14063  (DC->isFileContext() || !DC->getParent()->isDependentContext()))
14064  DependencyKind = CXXRecordDecl::LDK_NeverDependent;
14065 
14066  CXXRecordDecl *OldClass = E->getLambdaClass();
14067  CXXRecordDecl *Class = getSema().createLambdaClosureType(
14068  E->getIntroducerRange(), /*Info=*/nullptr, DependencyKind,
14069  E->getCaptureDefault());
14070  getDerived().transformedLocalDecl(OldClass, {Class});
14071 
14072  CXXMethodDecl *NewCallOperator =
14073  getSema().CreateLambdaCallOperator(E->getIntroducerRange(), Class);
14074  NewCallOperator->setLexicalDeclContext(getSema().CurContext);
14075 
14076  // Enter the scope of the lambda.
14077  getSema().buildLambdaScope(LSI, NewCallOperator, E->getIntroducerRange(),
14078  E->getCaptureDefault(), E->getCaptureDefaultLoc(),
14079  E->hasExplicitParameters(), E->isMutable());
14080 
14081  // Introduce the context of the call operator.
14082  Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(getSema(), NewCallOperator,
14083  /*NewThisContext*/false);
14084 
14085  bool Invalid = false;
14086 
14087  // Transform captures.
14088  for (LambdaExpr::capture_iterator C = E->capture_begin(),
14089  CEnd = E->capture_end();
14090  C != CEnd; ++C) {
14091  // When we hit the first implicit capture, tell Sema that we've finished
14092  // the list of explicit captures.
14093  if (C->isImplicit())
14094  break;
14095 
14096  // Capturing 'this' is trivial.
14097  if (C->capturesThis()) {
14098  // If this is a lambda that is part of a default member initialiser
14099  // and which we're instantiating outside the class that 'this' is
14100  // supposed to refer to, adjust the type of 'this' accordingly.
14101  //
14102  // Otherwise, leave the type of 'this' as-is.
14103  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(
14104  getSema(),
14105  dyn_cast_if_present<CXXRecordDecl>(
14106  getSema().getFunctionLevelDeclContext()),
14107  Qualifiers());
14108  getSema().CheckCXXThisCapture(C->getLocation(), C->isExplicit(),
14109  /*BuildAndDiagnose*/ true, nullptr,
14110  C->getCaptureKind() == LCK_StarThis);
14111  continue;
14112  }
14113  // Captured expression will be recaptured during captured variables
14114  // rebuilding.
14115  if (C->capturesVLAType())
14116  continue;
14117 
14118  // Rebuild init-captures, including the implied field declaration.
14119  if (E->isInitCapture(C)) {
14120  TransformedInitCapture &NewC = InitCaptures[C - E->capture_begin()];
14121 
14122  auto *OldVD = cast<VarDecl>(C->getCapturedVar());
14123  llvm::SmallVector<Decl*, 4> NewVDs;
14124 
14125  for (InitCaptureInfoTy &Info : NewC.Expansions) {
14126  ExprResult Init = Info.first;
14127  QualType InitQualType = Info.second;
14128  if (Init.isInvalid() || InitQualType.isNull()) {
14129  Invalid = true;
14130  break;
14131  }
14132  VarDecl *NewVD = getSema().createLambdaInitCaptureVarDecl(
14133  OldVD->getLocation(), InitQualType, NewC.EllipsisLoc,
14134  OldVD->getIdentifier(), OldVD->getInitStyle(), Init.get(),
14135  getSema().CurContext);
14136  if (!NewVD) {
14137  Invalid = true;
14138  break;
14139  }
14140  NewVDs.push_back(NewVD);
14141  getSema().addInitCapture(LSI, NewVD, C->getCaptureKind() == LCK_ByRef);
14142  }
14143 
14144  if (Invalid)
14145  break;
14146 
14147  getDerived().transformedLocalDecl(OldVD, NewVDs);
14148  continue;
14149  }
14150 
14151  assert(C->capturesVariable() && "unexpected kind of lambda capture");
14152 
14153  // Determine the capture kind for Sema.
14154  Sema::TryCaptureKind Kind
14155  = C->isImplicit()? Sema::TryCapture_Implicit
14156  : C->getCaptureKind() == LCK_ByCopy
14157  ? Sema::TryCapture_ExplicitByVal
14158  : Sema::TryCapture_ExplicitByRef;
14159  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
14160  if (C->isPackExpansion()) {
14161  UnexpandedParameterPack Unexpanded(C->getCapturedVar(), C->getLocation());
14162  bool ShouldExpand = false;
14163  bool RetainExpansion = false;
14164  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
14165  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(C->getEllipsisLoc(),
14166  C->getLocation(),
14167  Unexpanded,
14168  ShouldExpand, RetainExpansion,
14169  NumExpansions)) {
14170  Invalid = true;
14171  continue;
14172  }
14173 
14174  if (ShouldExpand) {
14175  // The transform has determined that we should perform an expansion;
14176  // transform and capture each of the arguments.
14177  // expansion of the pattern. Do so.
14178  auto *Pack = cast<VarDecl>(C->getCapturedVar());
14179  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
14180  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
14181  VarDecl *CapturedVar
14182  = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(C->getLocation(),
14183  Pack));
14184  if (!CapturedVar) {
14185  Invalid = true;
14186  continue;
14187  }
14188 
14189  // Capture the transformed variable.
14190  getSema().tryCaptureVariable(CapturedVar, C->getLocation(), Kind);
14191  }
14192 
14193  // FIXME: Retain a pack expansion if RetainExpansion is true.
14194 
14195  continue;
14196  }
14197 
14198  EllipsisLoc = C->getEllipsisLoc();
14199  }
14200 
14201  // Transform the captured variable.
14202  auto *CapturedVar = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(
14203  getDerived().TransformDecl(C->getLocation(), C->getCapturedVar()));
14204  if (!CapturedVar || CapturedVar->isInvalidDecl()) {
14205  Invalid = true;
14206  continue;
14207  }
14208 
14209  // Capture the transformed variable.
14210  getSema().tryCaptureVariable(CapturedVar, C->getLocation(), Kind,
14211  EllipsisLoc);
14212  }
14213  getSema().finishLambdaExplicitCaptures(LSI);
14214 
14215  // Transform the template parameters, and add them to the current
14216  // instantiation scope. The null case is handled correctly.
14217  auto TPL = getDerived().TransformTemplateParameterList(
14218  E->getTemplateParameterList());
14219  LSI->GLTemplateParameterList = TPL;
14220  if (TPL)
14221  getSema().AddTemplateParametersToLambdaCallOperator(NewCallOperator, Class,
14222  TPL);
14223 
14224  // Transform the type of the original lambda's call operator.
14225  // The transformation MUST be done in the CurrentInstantiationScope since
14226  // it introduces a mapping of the original to the newly created
14227  // transformed parameters.
14228  TypeSourceInfo *NewCallOpTSI = nullptr;
14229  {
14230  auto OldCallOpTypeLoc =
14231  E->getCallOperator()->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc();
14232 
14233  auto TransformFunctionProtoTypeLoc =
14234  [this](TypeLocBuilder &TLB, FunctionProtoTypeLoc FPTL) -> QualType {
14235  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ExceptionStorage;
14236  return this->TransformFunctionProtoType(
14237  TLB, FPTL, nullptr, Qualifiers(),
14238  [&](FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI, bool &Changed) {
14239  return TransformExceptionSpec(FPTL.getBeginLoc(), ESI,
14240  ExceptionStorage, Changed);
14241  });
14242  };
14243 
14244  QualType NewCallOpType;
14245  TypeLocBuilder NewCallOpTLBuilder;
14246 
14247  if (auto ATL = OldCallOpTypeLoc.getAs<AttributedTypeLoc>()) {
14248  NewCallOpType = this->TransformAttributedType(
14249  NewCallOpTLBuilder, ATL,
14250  [&](TypeLocBuilder &TLB, TypeLoc TL) -> QualType {
14251  return TransformFunctionProtoTypeLoc(
14252  TLB, TL.castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>());
14253  });
14254  } else {
14255  auto FPTL = OldCallOpTypeLoc.castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
14256  NewCallOpType = TransformFunctionProtoTypeLoc(NewCallOpTLBuilder, FPTL);
14257  }
14258 
14259  if (NewCallOpType.isNull())
14260  return ExprError();
14261  NewCallOpTSI =
14262  NewCallOpTLBuilder.getTypeSourceInfo(getSema().Context, NewCallOpType);
14263  }
14264 
14265  ArrayRef<ParmVarDecl *> Params;
14266  if (auto ATL = NewCallOpTSI->getTypeLoc().getAs<AttributedTypeLoc>()) {
14267  Params = ATL.getModifiedLoc().castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>().getParams();
14268  } else {
14269  auto FPTL = NewCallOpTSI->getTypeLoc().castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
14270  Params = FPTL.getParams();
14271  }
14272 
14273  getSema().CompleteLambdaCallOperator(
14274  NewCallOperator, E->getCallOperator()->getLocation(),
14275  E->getCallOperator()->getInnerLocStart(),
14276  E->getCallOperator()->getTrailingRequiresClause(), NewCallOpTSI,
14277  E->getCallOperator()->getConstexprKind(),
14278  E->getCallOperator()->getStorageClass(), Params,
14279  E->hasExplicitResultType());
14280 
14281  getDerived().transformAttrs(E->getCallOperator(), NewCallOperator);
14282  getDerived().transformedLocalDecl(E->getCallOperator(), {NewCallOperator});
14283 
14284  {
14285  // Number the lambda for linkage purposes if necessary.
14286  Sema::ContextRAII ManglingContext(getSema(), Class->getDeclContext());
14287 
14288  std::optional<CXXRecordDecl::LambdaNumbering> Numbering;
14289  if (getDerived().ReplacingOriginal()) {
14290  Numbering = OldClass->getLambdaNumbering();
14291  }
14292 
14293  getSema().handleLambdaNumbering(Class, NewCallOperator, Numbering);
14294  }
14295 
14296  // FIXME: Sema's lambda-building mechanism expects us to push an expression
14297  // evaluation context even if we're not transforming the function body.
14298  getSema().PushExpressionEvaluationContext(
14299  Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
14300 
14301  Sema::CodeSynthesisContext C;
14302  C.Kind = clang::Sema::CodeSynthesisContext::LambdaExpressionSubstitution;
14303  C.PointOfInstantiation = E->getBody()->getBeginLoc();
14304  getSema().pushCodeSynthesisContext(C);
14305 
14306  // Instantiate the body of the lambda expression.
14307  StmtResult Body =
14308  Invalid ? StmtError() : getDerived().TransformLambdaBody(E, E->getBody());
14309 
14310  getSema().popCodeSynthesisContext();
14311 
14312  // ActOnLambda* will pop the function scope for us.
14313  FuncScopeCleanup.disable();
14314 
14315  if (Body.isInvalid()) {
14316  SavedContext.pop();
14317  getSema().ActOnLambdaError(E->getBeginLoc(), /*CurScope=*/nullptr,
14318  /*IsInstantiation=*/true);
14319  return ExprError();
14320  }
14321 
14322  // Copy the LSI before ActOnFinishFunctionBody removes it.
14323  // FIXME: This is dumb. Store the lambda information somewhere that outlives
14324  // the call operator.
14325  auto LSICopy = *LSI;
14326  getSema().ActOnFinishFunctionBody(NewCallOperator, Body.get(),
14327  /*IsInstantiation*/ true);
14328  SavedContext.pop();
14329 
14330  // Recompute the dependency of the lambda so that we can defer the lambda call
14331  // construction until after we have all the necessary template arguments. For
14332  // example, given
14333  //
14334  // template <class> struct S {
14335  // template <class U>
14336  // using Type = decltype([](U){}(42.0));
14337  // };
14338  // void foo() {
14339  // using T = S<int>::Type<float>;
14340  // ^~~~~~
14341  // }
14342  //
14343  // We would end up here from instantiating S<int> when ensuring its
14344  // completeness. That would transform the lambda call expression regardless of
14345  // the absence of the corresponding argument for U.
14346  //
14347  // Going ahead with unsubstituted type U makes things worse: we would soon
14348  // compare the argument type (which is float) against the parameter U
14349  // somewhere in Sema::BuildCallExpr. Then we would quickly run into a bogus
14350  // error suggesting unmatched types 'U' and 'float'!
14351  //
14352  // That said, everything will be fine if we defer that semantic checking.
14353  // Fortunately, we have such a mechanism that bypasses it if the CallExpr is
14354  // dependent. Since the CallExpr's dependency boils down to the lambda's
14355  // dependency in this case, we can harness that by recomputing the dependency
14356  // from the instantiation arguments.
14357  //
14358  // FIXME: Creating the type of a lambda requires us to have a dependency
14359  // value, which happens before its substitution. We update its dependency
14360  // *after* the substitution in case we can't decide the dependency
14361  // so early, e.g. because we want to see if any of the *substituted*
14362  // parameters are dependent.
14363  DependencyKind = getDerived().ComputeLambdaDependency(&LSICopy);
14364  Class->setLambdaDependencyKind(DependencyKind);
14365  // Clean up the type cache created previously. Then, we re-create a type for
14366  // such Decl with the new DependencyKind.
14367  Class->setTypeForDecl(nullptr);
14368  getSema().Context.getTypeDeclType(Class);
14369 
14370  return getSema().BuildLambdaExpr(E->getBeginLoc(), Body.get()->getEndLoc(),
14371  &LSICopy);
14372 }
14373 
14374 template<typename Derived>
14375 StmtResult
14376 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformLambdaBody(LambdaExpr *E, Stmt *S) {
14377  return TransformStmt(S);
14378 }
14379 
14380 template<typename Derived>
14381 StmtResult
14382 TreeTransform<Derived>::SkipLambdaBody(LambdaExpr *E, Stmt *S) {
14383  // Transform captures.
14384  for (LambdaExpr::capture_iterator C = E->capture_begin(),
14385  CEnd = E->capture_end();
14386  C != CEnd; ++C) {
14387  // When we hit the first implicit capture, tell Sema that we've finished
14388  // the list of explicit captures.
14389  if (!C->isImplicit())
14390  continue;
14391 
14392  // Capturing 'this' is trivial.
14393  if (C->capturesThis()) {
14394  getSema().CheckCXXThisCapture(C->getLocation(), C->isExplicit(),
14395  /*BuildAndDiagnose*/ true, nullptr,
14396  C->getCaptureKind() == LCK_StarThis);
14397  continue;
14398  }
14399  // Captured expression will be recaptured during captured variables
14400  // rebuilding.
14401  if (C->capturesVLAType())
14402  continue;
14403 
14404  assert(C->capturesVariable() && "unexpected kind of lambda capture");
14405  assert(!E->isInitCapture(C) && "implicit init-capture?");
14406 
14407  // Transform the captured variable.
14408  VarDecl *CapturedVar = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(
14409  getDerived().TransformDecl(C->getLocation(), C->getCapturedVar()));
14410  if (!CapturedVar || CapturedVar->isInvalidDecl())
14411  return StmtError();
14412 
14413  // Capture the transformed variable.
14414  getSema().tryCaptureVariable(CapturedVar, C->getLocation());
14415  }
14416 
14417  return S;
14418 }

14420 template<typename Derived>
14421 ExprResult
14422 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXUnresolvedConstructExpr(
14423  CXXUnresolvedConstructExpr *E) {
14424  TypeSourceInfo *T =
14425  getDerived().TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(E->getTypeSourceInfo());
14426  if (!T)
14427  return ExprError();
14428 
14429  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
14430  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
14431  Args.reserve(E->getNumArgs());
14432  {
14433  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
14434  getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList,
14435  E->isListInitialization());
14436  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->arg_begin(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
14437  &ArgumentChanged))
14438  return ExprError();
14439  }
14440 
14441  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
14442  T == E->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
14443  !ArgumentChanged)
14444  return E;
14445 
14446  // FIXME: we're faking the locations of the commas
14447  return getDerived().RebuildCXXUnresolvedConstructExpr(
14448  T, E->getLParenLoc(), Args, E->getRParenLoc(), E->isListInitialization());
14449 }

14451 template<typename Derived>
14452 ExprResult
14453 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXDependentScopeMemberExpr(
14454  CXXDependentScopeMemberExpr *E) {
14455  // Transform the base of the expression.
14456  ExprResult Base((Expr*) nullptr);
14457  Expr *OldBase;
14458  QualType BaseType;
14459  QualType ObjectType;
14460  if (!E->isImplicitAccess()) {
14461  OldBase = E->getBase();
14462  Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(OldBase);
14463  if (Base.isInvalid())
14464  return ExprError();
14465 
14466  // Start the member reference and compute the object's type.
14467  ParsedType ObjectTy;
14468  bool MayBePseudoDestructor = false;
14469  Base = SemaRef.ActOnStartCXXMemberReference(nullptr, Base.get(),
14470  E->getOperatorLoc(),
14471  E->isArrow()? tok::arrow : tok::period,
14472  ObjectTy,
14473  MayBePseudoDestructor);
14474  if (Base.isInvalid())
14475  return ExprError();
14476 
14477  ObjectType = ObjectTy.get();
14478  BaseType = ((Expr*) Base.get())->getType();
14479  } else {
14480  OldBase = nullptr;
14481  BaseType = getDerived().TransformType(E->getBaseType());
14482  ObjectType = BaseType->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
14483  }
14484 
14485  // Transform the first part of the nested-name-specifier that qualifies
14486  // the member name.
14487  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope
14488  = getDerived().TransformFirstQualifierInScope(
14489  E->getFirstQualifierFoundInScope(),
14490  E->getQualifierLoc().getBeginLoc());
14491 
14492  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
14493  if (E->getQualifier()) {
14494  QualifierLoc
14495  = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc(),
14496  ObjectType,
14497  FirstQualifierInScope);
14498  if (!QualifierLoc)
14499  return ExprError();
14500  }
14501 
14502  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = E->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
14503 
14504  // TODO: If this is a conversion-function-id, verify that the
14505  // destination type name (if present) resolves the same way after
14506  // instantiation as it did in the local scope.
14507 
14508  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo
14509  = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(E->getMemberNameInfo());
14510  if (!NameInfo.getName())
14511  return ExprError();
14512 
14513  if (!E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
14514  // This is a reference to a member without an explicitly-specified
14515  // template argument list. Optimize for this common case.
14516  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
14517  Base.get() == OldBase &&
14518  BaseType == E->getBaseType() &&
14519  QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() &&
14520  NameInfo.getName() == E->getMember() &&
14521  FirstQualifierInScope == E->getFirstQualifierFoundInScope())
14522  return E;
14523 
14524  return getDerived().RebuildCXXDependentScopeMemberExpr(Base.get(),
14525  BaseType,
14526  E->isArrow(),
14527  E->getOperatorLoc(),
14528  QualifierLoc,
14529  TemplateKWLoc,
14530  FirstQualifierInScope,
14531  NameInfo,
14532  /*TemplateArgs*/nullptr);
14533  }
14534 
14535  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs(E->getLAngleLoc(), E->getRAngleLoc());
14536  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(E->getTemplateArgs(),
14537  E->getNumTemplateArgs(),
14538  TransArgs))
14539  return ExprError();
14540 
14541  return getDerived().RebuildCXXDependentScopeMemberExpr(Base.get(),
14542  BaseType,
14543  E->isArrow(),
14544  E->getOperatorLoc(),
14545  QualifierLoc,
14546  TemplateKWLoc,
14547  FirstQualifierInScope,
14548  NameInfo,
14549  &TransArgs);
14550 }
14551 
14552 template <typename Derived>
14553 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnresolvedMemberExpr(
14554  UnresolvedMemberExpr *Old) {
14555  // Transform the base of the expression.
14556  ExprResult Base((Expr *)nullptr);
14557  QualType BaseType;
14558  if (!Old->isImplicitAccess()) {
14559  Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(Old->getBase());
14560  if (Base.isInvalid())
14561  return ExprError();
14562  Base =
14563  getSema().PerformMemberExprBaseConversion(Base.get(), Old->isArrow());
14564  if (Base.isInvalid())
14565  return ExprError();
14566  BaseType = Base.get()->getType();
14567  } else {
14568  BaseType = getDerived().TransformType(Old->getBaseType());
14569  }
14570 
14571  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
14572  if (Old->getQualifierLoc()) {
14573  QualifierLoc =
14574  getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(Old->getQualifierLoc());
14575  if (!QualifierLoc)
14576  return ExprError();
14577  }
14578 
14579  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = Old->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
14580 
14581  LookupResult R(SemaRef, Old->getMemberNameInfo(), Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
14582 
14583  // Transform the declaration set.
14584  if (TransformOverloadExprDecls(Old, /*RequiresADL*/ false, R))
14585  return ExprError();
14586 
14587  // Determine the naming class.
14588  if (Old->getNamingClass()) {
14589  CXXRecordDecl *NamingClass = cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(
14590  getDerived().TransformDecl(Old->getMemberLoc(), Old->getNamingClass()));
14591  if (!NamingClass)
14592  return ExprError();
14593 
14594  R.setNamingClass(NamingClass);
14595  }
14596 
14597  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs;
14598  if (Old->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
14599  TransArgs.setLAngleLoc(Old->getLAngleLoc());
14600  TransArgs.setRAngleLoc(Old->getRAngleLoc());
14601  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(
14602  Old->getTemplateArgs(), Old->getNumTemplateArgs(), TransArgs))
14603  return ExprError();
14604  }
14605 
14606  // FIXME: to do this check properly, we will need to preserve the
14607  // first-qualifier-in-scope here, just in case we had a dependent
14608  // base (and therefore couldn't do the check) and a
14609  // nested-name-qualifier (and therefore could do the lookup).
14610  NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr;
14611 
14612  return getDerived().RebuildUnresolvedMemberExpr(
14613  Base.get(), BaseType, Old->getOperatorLoc(), Old->isArrow(), QualifierLoc,
14614  TemplateKWLoc, FirstQualifierInScope, R,
14615  (Old->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() ? &TransArgs : nullptr));
14616 }

14618 template<typename Derived>
14619 ExprResult
14620 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXNoexceptExpr(CXXNoexceptExpr *E) {
14621  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
14622  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
14623  ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getOperand());
14624  if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
14625  return ExprError();
14626 
14627  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getOperand())
14628  return E;
14629 
14630  return getDerived().RebuildCXXNoexceptExpr(E->getSourceRange(),SubExpr.get());
14631 }

14633 template<typename Derived>
14634 ExprResult
14635 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPackExpansionExpr(PackExpansionExpr *E) {
14636  ExprResult Pattern = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getPattern());
14637  if (Pattern.isInvalid())
14638  return ExprError();
14639 
14640  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && Pattern.get() == E->getPattern())
14641  return E;
14642 
14643  return getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(Pattern.get(), E->getEllipsisLoc(),
14644  E->getNumExpansions());
14645 }
14646 
14647 template<typename Derived>
14648 ExprResult
14649 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformSizeOfPackExpr(SizeOfPackExpr *E) {
14650  // If E is not value-dependent, then nothing will change when we transform it.
14651  // Note: This is an instantiation-centric view.
14652  if (!E->isValueDependent())
14653  return E;
14654 
14655  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
14656  getSema(), Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
14657 
14658  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> PackArgs;
14659  TemplateArgument ArgStorage;
14660 
14661  // Find the argument list to transform.
14662  if (E->isPartiallySubstituted()) {
14663  PackArgs = E->getPartialArguments();
14664  } else if (E->isValueDependent()) {
14665  UnexpandedParameterPack Unexpanded(E->getPack(), E->getPackLoc());
14666  bool ShouldExpand = false;
14667  bool RetainExpansion = false;
14668  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
14669  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getPackLoc(),
14670  Unexpanded,
14671  ShouldExpand, RetainExpansion,
14672  NumExpansions))
14673  return ExprError();
14674 
14675  // If we need to expand the pack, build a template argument from it and
14676  // expand that.
14677  if (ShouldExpand) {
14678  auto *Pack = E->getPack();
14679  if (auto *TTPD = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Pack)) {
14680  ArgStorage = getSema().Context.getPackExpansionType(
14681  getSema().Context.getTypeDeclType(TTPD), std::nullopt);
14682  } else if (auto *TTPD = dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Pack)) {
14683  ArgStorage = TemplateArgument(TemplateName(TTPD), std::nullopt);
14684  } else {
14685  auto *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(Pack);
14686  ExprResult DRE = getSema().BuildDeclRefExpr(
14687  VD, VD->getType().getNonLValueExprType(getSema().Context),
14688  VD->getType()->isReferenceType() ? VK_LValue : VK_PRValue,
14689  E->getPackLoc());
14690  if (DRE.isInvalid())
14691  return ExprError();
14692  ArgStorage = new (getSema().Context)
14693  PackExpansionExpr(getSema().Context.DependentTy, DRE.get(),
14694  E->getPackLoc(), std::nullopt);
14695  }
14696  PackArgs = ArgStorage;
14697  }
14698  }
14699 
14700  // If we're not expanding the pack, just transform the decl.
14701  if (!PackArgs.size()) {
14702  auto *Pack = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(
14703  getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getPackLoc(), E->getPack()));
14704  if (!Pack)
14705  return ExprError();
14706  return getDerived().RebuildSizeOfPackExpr(
14707  E->getOperatorLoc(), Pack, E->getPackLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(),
14708  std::nullopt, std::nullopt);
14709  }
14710 
14711  // Try to compute the result without performing a partial substitution.
14712  std::optional<unsigned> Result = 0;
14713  for (const TemplateArgument &Arg : PackArgs) {
14714  if (!Arg.isPackExpansion()) {
14715  Result = *Result + 1;
14716  continue;
14717  }
14718 
14719  TemplateArgumentLoc ArgLoc;
14720  InventTemplateArgumentLoc(Arg, ArgLoc);
14721 
14722  // Find the pattern of the pack expansion.
14723  SourceLocation Ellipsis;
14724  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions;
14725  TemplateArgumentLoc Pattern =
14726  getSema().getTemplateArgumentPackExpansionPattern(ArgLoc, Ellipsis,
14727  OrigNumExpansions);
14728 
14729  // Substitute under the pack expansion. Do not expand the pack (yet).
14730  TemplateArgumentLoc OutPattern;
14731  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
14732  if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArgument(Pattern, OutPattern,
14733  /*Uneval*/ true))
14734  return true;
14735 
14736  // See if we can determine the number of arguments from the result.
14737  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions =
14738  getSema().getFullyPackExpandedSize(OutPattern.getArgument());
14739  if (!NumExpansions) {
14740  // No: we must be in an alias template expansion, and we're going to need
14741  // to actually expand the packs.
14742  Result = std::nullopt;
14743  break;
14744  }
14745 
14746  Result = *Result + *NumExpansions;
14747  }
14748 
14749  // Common case: we could determine the number of expansions without
14750  // substituting.
14751  if (Result)
14752  return getDerived().RebuildSizeOfPackExpr(
14753  E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getPack(), E->getPackLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(),
14754  *Result, std::nullopt);
14755 
14756  TemplateArgumentListInfo TransformedPackArgs(E->getPackLoc(),
14757  E->getPackLoc());
14758  {
14759  TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, E->getPackLoc(), getBaseEntity());
14760  typedef TemplateArgumentLocInventIterator<
14761  Derived, const TemplateArgument*> PackLocIterator;
14762  if (TransformTemplateArguments(PackLocIterator(*this, PackArgs.begin()),
14763  PackLocIterator(*this, PackArgs.end()),
14764  TransformedPackArgs, /*Uneval*/true))
14765  return ExprError();
14766  }
14767 
14768  // Check whether we managed to fully-expand the pack.
14769  // FIXME: Is it possible for us to do so and not hit the early exit path?
14770  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 8> Args;
14771  bool PartialSubstitution = false;
14772  for (auto &Loc : TransformedPackArgs.arguments()) {
14773  Args.push_back(Loc.getArgument());
14774  if (Loc.getArgument().isPackExpansion())
14775  PartialSubstitution = true;
14776  }
14777 
14778  if (PartialSubstitution)
14779  return getDerived().RebuildSizeOfPackExpr(
14780  E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getPack(), E->getPackLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(),
14781  std::nullopt, Args);
14782 
14783  return getDerived().RebuildSizeOfPackExpr(E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getPack(),
14784  E->getPackLoc(), E->getRParenLoc(),
14785  Args.size(), std::nullopt);
14786 }
14787 
14788 template <typename Derived>
14789 ExprResult
14790 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPackIndexingExpr(PackIndexingExpr *E) {
14791  if (!E->isValueDependent())
14792  return E;
14793 
14794  // Transform the index
14795  ExprResult IndexExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getIndexExpr());
14796  if (IndexExpr.isInvalid())
14797  return ExprError();
14798 
14799  SmallVector<Expr *, 5> ExpandedExprs;
14800  if (E->getExpressions().empty()) {
14801  Expr *Pattern = E->getPackIdExpression();
14802  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
14803  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(E->getPackIdExpression(),
14804  Unexpanded);
14805  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
14806 
14807  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
14808  // be expanded.
14809  bool ShouldExpand = true;
14810  bool RetainExpansion = false;
14811  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions;
14812  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
14813  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(
14814  E->getEllipsisLoc(), Pattern->getSourceRange(), Unexpanded,
14815  ShouldExpand, RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
14816  return true;
14817  if (!ShouldExpand) {
14818  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
14819  ExprResult Pack = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
14820  if (Pack.isInvalid())
14821  return ExprError();
14822  return getDerived().RebuildPackIndexingExpr(
14823  E->getEllipsisLoc(), E->getRSquareLoc(), Pack.get(), IndexExpr.get(),
14824  std::nullopt);
14825  }
14826  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
14827  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
14828  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
14829  if (Out.isInvalid())
14830  return true;
14831  if (Out.get()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
14832  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(Out.get(), E->getEllipsisLoc(),
14833  OrigNumExpansions);
14834  if (Out.isInvalid())
14835  return true;
14836  }
14837  ExpandedExprs.push_back(Out.get());
14838  }
14839  // If we're supposed to retain a pack expansion, do so by temporarily
14840  // forgetting the partially-substituted parameter pack.
14841  if (RetainExpansion) {
14842  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
14843 
14844  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
14845  if (Out.isInvalid())
14846  return true;
14847 
14848  Out = getDerived().RebuildPackExpansion(Out.get(), E->getEllipsisLoc(),
14849  OrigNumExpansions);
14850  if (Out.isInvalid())
14851  return true;
14852  ExpandedExprs.push_back(Out.get());
14853  }
14854  }
14855 
14856  else {
14857  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getExpressions().data(),
14858  E->getExpressions().size(), false,
14859  ExpandedExprs))
14860  return ExprError();
14861  }
14862 
14863  return getDerived().RebuildPackIndexingExpr(
14864  E->getEllipsisLoc(), E->getRSquareLoc(), E->getPackIdExpression(),
14865  IndexExpr.get(), ExpandedExprs,
14866  /*EmptyPack=*/ExpandedExprs.size() == 0);
14867 }
14868

14899 template<typename Derived>
14900 ExprResult
14901 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXFoldExpr(CXXFoldExpr *E) {
14902  UnresolvedLookupExpr *Callee = nullptr;
14903  if (Expr *OldCallee = E->getCallee()) {
14904  ExprResult CalleeResult = getDerived().TransformExpr(OldCallee);
14905  if (CalleeResult.isInvalid())
14906  return ExprError();
14907  Callee = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(CalleeResult.get());
14908  }
14909 
14910  Expr *Pattern = E->getPattern();
14911 
14912  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
14913  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
14914  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
14915 
14916  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
14917  // be expanded.
14918  bool Expand = true;
14919  bool RetainExpansion = false;
14920  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions = E->getNumExpansions(),
14921  NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
14922  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(E->getEllipsisLoc(),
14923  Pattern->getSourceRange(),
14924  Unexpanded,
14925  Expand, RetainExpansion,
14926  NumExpansions))
14927  return true;
14928 
14929  if (!Expand) {
14930  // Do not expand any packs here, just transform and rebuild a fold
14931  // expression.
14932  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
14933 
14934  ExprResult LHS =
14935  E->getLHS() ? getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS()) : ExprResult();
14936  if (LHS.isInvalid())
14937  return true;
14938 
14939  ExprResult RHS =
14940  E->getRHS() ? getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS()) : ExprResult();
14941  if (RHS.isInvalid())
14942  return true;
14943 
14944  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
14945  LHS.get() == E->getLHS() && RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
14946  return E;
14947 
14948  return getDerived().RebuildCXXFoldExpr(
14949  Callee, E->getBeginLoc(), LHS.get(), E->getOperator(),
14950  E->getEllipsisLoc(), RHS.get(), E->getEndLoc(), NumExpansions);
14951  }
14952 
14953  // Formally a fold expression expands to nested parenthesized expressions.
14954  // Enforce this limit to avoid creating trees so deep we can't safely traverse
14955  // them.
14956  if (NumExpansions && SemaRef.getLangOpts().BracketDepth < NumExpansions) {
14957  SemaRef.Diag(E->getEllipsisLoc(),
14958  clang::diag::err_fold_expression_limit_exceeded)
14959  << *NumExpansions << SemaRef.getLangOpts().BracketDepth
14960  << E->getSourceRange();
14961  SemaRef.Diag(E->getEllipsisLoc(), diag::note_bracket_depth);
14962  return ExprError();
14963  }
14964 
14965  // The transform has determined that we should perform an elementwise
14966  // expansion of the pattern. Do so.
14967  ExprResult Result = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInit());
14968  if (Result.isInvalid())
14969  return true;
14970  bool LeftFold = E->isLeftFold();
14971 
14972  // If we're retaining an expansion for a right fold, it is the innermost
14973  // component and takes the init (if any).
14974  if (!LeftFold && RetainExpansion) {
14975  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
14976 
14977  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
14978  if (Out.isInvalid())
14979  return true;
14980 
14981  Result = getDerived().RebuildCXXFoldExpr(
14982  Callee, E->getBeginLoc(), Out.get(), E->getOperator(),
14983  E->getEllipsisLoc(), Result.get(), E->getEndLoc(), OrigNumExpansions);
14984  if (Result.isInvalid())
14985  return true;
14986  }
14987 
14988  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
14989  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(
14990  getSema(), LeftFold ? I : *NumExpansions - I - 1);
14991  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
14992  if (Out.isInvalid())
14993  return true;
14994 
14995  if (Out.get()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
14996  // We still have a pack; retain a pack expansion for this slice.
14997  Result = getDerived().RebuildCXXFoldExpr(
14998  Callee, E->getBeginLoc(), LeftFold ? Result.get() : Out.get(),
14999  E->getOperator(), E->getEllipsisLoc(),
15000  LeftFold ? Out.get() : Result.get(), E->getEndLoc(),
15001  OrigNumExpansions);
15002  } else if (Result.isUsable()) {
15003  // We've got down to a single element; build a binary operator.
15004  Expr *LHS = LeftFold ? Result.get() : Out.get();
15005  Expr *RHS = LeftFold ? Out.get() : Result.get();
15006  if (Callee) {
15007  UnresolvedSet<16> Functions;
15008  Functions.append(Callee->decls_begin(), Callee->decls_end());
15009  Result = getDerived().RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(
15010  BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOperator(E->getOperator()),
15011  E->getEllipsisLoc(), Callee->getBeginLoc(), Callee->requiresADL(),
15012  Functions, LHS, RHS);
15013  } else {
15014  Result = getDerived().RebuildBinaryOperator(E->getEllipsisLoc(),
15015  E->getOperator(), LHS, RHS);
15016  }
15017  } else
15018  Result = Out;
15019 
15020  if (Result.isInvalid())
15021  return true;
15022  }
15023 
15024  // If we're retaining an expansion for a left fold, it is the outermost
15025  // component and takes the complete expansion so far as its init (if any).
15026  if (LeftFold && RetainExpansion) {
15027  ForgetPartiallySubstitutedPackRAII Forget(getDerived());
15028 
15029  ExprResult Out = getDerived().TransformExpr(Pattern);
15030  if (Out.isInvalid())
15031  return true;
15032 
15033  Result = getDerived().RebuildCXXFoldExpr(
15034  Callee, E->getBeginLoc(), Result.get(), E->getOperator(),
15035  E->getEllipsisLoc(), Out.get(), E->getEndLoc(), OrigNumExpansions);
15036  if (Result.isInvalid())
15037  return true;
15038  }
15039 
15040  // If we had no init and an empty pack, and we're not retaining an expansion,
15041  // then produce a fallback value or error.
15042  if (Result.isUnset())
15043  return getDerived().RebuildEmptyCXXFoldExpr(E->getEllipsisLoc(),
15044  E->getOperator());
15045 
15046  return Result;
15047 }
15048

15051 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXParenListInitExpr(CXXParenListInitExpr *E) {

15053  ArrayRef<Expr *> InitExprs = E->getInitExprs();
15054  if (TransformExprs(InitExprs.data(), InitExprs.size(), true,
15055  TransformedInits))
15056  return ExprError();
15057 
15058  return getDerived().RebuildParenListExpr(E->getBeginLoc(), TransformedInits,
15059  E->getEndLoc());
15060 }

15095 template<typename Derived>
15096 ExprResult
15097 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCArrayLiteral(ObjCArrayLiteral *E) {
15098  // Transform each of the elements.
15099  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> Elements;
15100  bool ArgChanged = false;
15101  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getElements(), E->getNumElements(),
15102  /*IsCall=*/false, Elements, &ArgChanged))
15103  return ExprError();
15104 
15105  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !ArgChanged)
15106  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
15107 
15108  return getDerived().RebuildObjCArrayLiteral(E->getSourceRange(),
15109  Elements.data(),
15110  Elements.size());
15111 }
15112 
15113 template<typename Derived>
15114 ExprResult
15115 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCDictionaryLiteral(
15116  ObjCDictionaryLiteral *E) {
15117  // Transform each of the elements.
15118  SmallVector<ObjCDictionaryElement, 8> Elements;
15119  bool ArgChanged = false;
15120  for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumElements(); I != N; ++I) {
15121  ObjCDictionaryElement OrigElement = E->getKeyValueElement(I);
15122 
15123  if (OrigElement.isPackExpansion()) {
15124  // This key/value element is a pack expansion.
15125  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
15126  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(OrigElement.Key, Unexpanded);
15127  getSema().collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(OrigElement.Value, Unexpanded);
15128  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
15129 
15130  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can
15131  // and should be expanded.
15132  bool Expand = true;
15133  bool RetainExpansion = false;
15134  std::optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions = OrigElement.NumExpansions;
15135  std::optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
15136  SourceRange PatternRange(OrigElement.Key->getBeginLoc(),
15137  OrigElement.Value->getEndLoc());
15138  if (getDerived().TryExpandParameterPacks(OrigElement.EllipsisLoc,
15139  PatternRange, Unexpanded, Expand,
15140  RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
15141  return ExprError();
15142 
15143  if (!Expand) {
15144  // The transform has determined that we should perform a simple
15145  // transformation on the pack expansion, producing another pack
15146  // expansion.
15147  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), -1);
15148  ExprResult Key = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Key);
15149  if (Key.isInvalid())
15150  return ExprError();
15151 
15152  if (Key.get() != OrigElement.Key)
15153  ArgChanged = true;
15154 
15155  ExprResult Value = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Value);
15156  if (Value.isInvalid())
15157  return ExprError();
15158 
15159  if (Value.get() != OrigElement.Value)
15160  ArgChanged = true;
15161 
15162  ObjCDictionaryElement Expansion = {
15163  Key.get(), Value.get(), OrigElement.EllipsisLoc, NumExpansions
15164  };
15165  Elements.push_back(Expansion);
15166  continue;
15167  }
15168 
15169  // Record right away that the argument was changed. This needs
15170  // to happen even if the array expands to nothing.
15171  ArgChanged = true;
15172 
15173  // The transform has determined that we should perform an elementwise
15174  // expansion of the pattern. Do so.
15175  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
15176  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(getSema(), I);
15177  ExprResult Key = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Key);
15178  if (Key.isInvalid())
15179  return ExprError();
15180 
15181  ExprResult Value = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Value);
15182  if (Value.isInvalid())
15183  return ExprError();
15184 
15185  ObjCDictionaryElement Element = {
15186  Key.get(), Value.get(), SourceLocation(), NumExpansions
15187  };
15188 
15189  // If any unexpanded parameter packs remain, we still have a
15190  // pack expansion.
15191  // FIXME: Can this really happen?
15192  if (Key.get()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack() ||
15193  Value.get()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
15194  Element.EllipsisLoc = OrigElement.EllipsisLoc;
15195 
15196  Elements.push_back(Element);
15197  }
15198 
15199  // FIXME: Retain a pack expansion if RetainExpansion is true.
15200 
15201  // We've finished with this pack expansion.
15202  continue;
15203  }
15204 
15205  // Transform and check key.
15206  ExprResult Key = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Key);
15207  if (Key.isInvalid())
15208  return ExprError();
15209 
15210  if (Key.get() != OrigElement.Key)
15211  ArgChanged = true;
15212 
15213  // Transform and check value.
15214  ExprResult Value
15215  = getDerived().TransformExpr(OrigElement.Value);
15216  if (Value.isInvalid())
15217  return ExprError();
15218 
15219  if (Value.get() != OrigElement.Value)
15220  ArgChanged = true;
15221 
15222  ObjCDictionaryElement Element = {Key.get(), Value.get(), SourceLocation(),
15223  std::nullopt};
15224  Elements.push_back(Element);
15225  }
15226 
15227  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !ArgChanged)
15228  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
15229 
15230  return getDerived().RebuildObjCDictionaryLiteral(E->getSourceRange(),
15231  Elements);
15232 }

15289 template<typename Derived>
15290 ExprResult
15291 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCMessageExpr(ObjCMessageExpr *E) {
15292  // Transform arguments.
15293  bool ArgChanged = false;
15294  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
15295  Args.reserve(E->getNumArgs());
15296  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), false, Args,
15297  &ArgChanged))
15298  return ExprError();
15299 
15300  if (E->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::Class) {
15301  // Class message: transform the receiver type.
15302  TypeSourceInfo *ReceiverTypeInfo
15303  = getDerived().TransformType(E->getClassReceiverTypeInfo());
15304  if (!ReceiverTypeInfo)
15305  return ExprError();
15306 
15307  // If nothing changed, just retain the existing message send.
15308  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
15309  ReceiverTypeInfo == E->getClassReceiverTypeInfo() && !ArgChanged)
15310  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
15311 
15312  // Build a new class message send.
15313  SmallVector<SourceLocation, 16> SelLocs;
15314  E->getSelectorLocs(SelLocs);
15315  return getDerived().RebuildObjCMessageExpr(ReceiverTypeInfo,
15316  E->getSelector(),
15317  SelLocs,
15318  E->getMethodDecl(),
15319  E->getLeftLoc(),
15320  Args,
15321  E->getRightLoc());
15322  }
15323  else if (E->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::SuperClass ||
15324  E->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::SuperInstance) {
15325  if (!E->getMethodDecl())
15326  return ExprError();
15327 
15328  // Build a new class message send to 'super'.
15329  SmallVector<SourceLocation, 16> SelLocs;
15330  E->getSelectorLocs(SelLocs);
15331  return getDerived().RebuildObjCMessageExpr(E->getSuperLoc(),
15332  E->getSelector(),
15333  SelLocs,
15334  E->getReceiverType(),
15335  E->getMethodDecl(),
15336  E->getLeftLoc(),
15337  Args,
15338  E->getRightLoc());
15339  }
15340 
15341  // Instance message: transform the receiver
15342  assert(E->getReceiverKind() == ObjCMessageExpr::Instance &&
15343  "Only class and instance messages may be instantiated");
15344  ExprResult Receiver
15345  = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInstanceReceiver());
15346  if (Receiver.isInvalid())
15347  return ExprError();
15348 
15349  // If nothing changed, just retain the existing message send.
15350  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
15351  Receiver.get() == E->getInstanceReceiver() && !ArgChanged)
15352  return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
15353 
15354  // Build a new instance message send.
15355  SmallVector<SourceLocation, 16> SelLocs;
15356  E->getSelectorLocs(SelLocs);
15357  return getDerived().RebuildObjCMessageExpr(Receiver.get(),
15358  E->getSelector(),
15359  SelLocs,
15360  E->getMethodDecl(),
15361  E->getLeftLoc(),
15362  Args,
15363  E->getRightLoc());
15364 }

15400 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformObjCPropertyRefExpr(ObjCPropertyRefExpr *E) {

15410

15415  Base.get() == E->getBase())
15416  return E;

15491 template<typename Derived>
15492 ExprResult
15493 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformConvertVectorExpr(ConvertVectorExpr *E) {
15494  ExprResult SrcExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
15495  if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
15496  return ExprError();
15497 
15498  TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeSourceInfo());
15499  if (!Type)
15500  return ExprError();
15501 
15502  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
15503  Type == E->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
15504  SrcExpr.get() == E->getSrcExpr())
15505  return E;
15506 
15507  return getDerived().RebuildConvertVectorExpr(E->getBuiltinLoc(),
15508  SrcExpr.get(), Type,
15509  E->getRParenLoc());
15510 }
15511 
15512 template<typename Derived>
15513 ExprResult
15514 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformBlockExpr(BlockExpr *E) {
15515  BlockDecl *oldBlock = E->getBlockDecl();
15516 
15517  SemaRef.ActOnBlockStart(E->getCaretLocation(), /*Scope=*/nullptr);
15518  BlockScopeInfo *blockScope = SemaRef.getCurBlock();
15519 
15520  blockScope->TheDecl->setIsVariadic(oldBlock->isVariadic());
15521  blockScope->TheDecl->setBlockMissingReturnType(
15522  oldBlock->blockMissingReturnType());
15523 
15524  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl*, 4> params;
15525  SmallVector<QualType, 4> paramTypes;
15526 
15527  const FunctionProtoType *exprFunctionType = E->getFunctionType();
15528 
15529  // Parameter substitution.
15530  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder extParamInfos;
15531  if (getDerived().TransformFunctionTypeParams(
15532  E->getCaretLocation(), oldBlock->parameters(), nullptr,
15533  exprFunctionType->getExtParameterInfosOrNull(), paramTypes, &params,
15534  extParamInfos)) {
15535  getSema().ActOnBlockError(E->getCaretLocation(), /*Scope=*/nullptr);
15536  return ExprError();
15537  }
15538 
15539  QualType exprResultType =
15540  getDerived().TransformType(exprFunctionType->getReturnType());
15541 
15542  auto epi = exprFunctionType->getExtProtoInfo();
15543  epi.ExtParameterInfos = extParamInfos.getPointerOrNull(paramTypes.size());
15544 
15545  QualType functionType =
15546  getDerived().RebuildFunctionProtoType(exprResultType, paramTypes, epi);
15547  blockScope->FunctionType = functionType;
15548 
15549  // Set the parameters on the block decl.
15550  if (!params.empty())
15551  blockScope->TheDecl->setParams(params);
15552 
15553  if (!oldBlock->blockMissingReturnType()) {
15554  blockScope->HasImplicitReturnType = false;
15555  blockScope->ReturnType = exprResultType;
15556  }
15557 
15558  // Transform the body
15559  StmtResult body = getDerived().TransformStmt(E->getBody());
15560  if (body.isInvalid()) {
15561  getSema().ActOnBlockError(E->getCaretLocation(), /*Scope=*/nullptr);
15562  return ExprError();
15563  }
15564 
15565 #ifndef NDEBUG
15566  // In builds with assertions, make sure that we captured everything we
15567  // captured before.
15568  if (!SemaRef.getDiagnostics().hasErrorOccurred()) {
15569  for (const auto &I : oldBlock->captures()) {
15570  VarDecl *oldCapture = I.getVariable();
15571 
15572  // Ignore parameter packs.
15573  if (oldCapture->isParameterPack())
15574  continue;
15575 
15576  VarDecl *newCapture =
15577  cast<VarDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getCaretLocation(),
15578  oldCapture));
15579  assert(blockScope->CaptureMap.count(newCapture));
15580  }
15581 
15582  // The this pointer may not be captured by the instantiated block, even when
15583  // it's captured by the original block, if the expression causing the
15584  // capture is in the discarded branch of a constexpr if statement.
15585  assert((!blockScope->isCXXThisCaptured() || oldBlock->capturesCXXThis()) &&
15586  "this pointer isn't captured in the old block");
15587  }
15588 #endif
15589 
15590  return SemaRef.ActOnBlockStmtExpr(E->getCaretLocation(), body.get(),
15591  /*Scope=*/nullptr);
15592 }
15593 
15594 template<typename Derived>
15595 ExprResult
15596 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAsTypeExpr(AsTypeExpr *E) {
15597  ExprResult SrcExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSrcExpr());
15598  if (SrcExpr.isInvalid())
15599  return ExprError();
15600 
15601  QualType Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getType());
15602 
15603  return SemaRef.BuildAsTypeExpr(SrcExpr.get(), Type, E->getBuiltinLoc(),
15604  E->getRParenLoc());
15605 }
15606 
15607 template<typename Derived>
15608 ExprResult
15609 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAtomicExpr(AtomicExpr *E) {
15610  bool ArgumentChanged = false;
15611  SmallVector<Expr*, 8> SubExprs;
15612  SubExprs.reserve(E->getNumSubExprs());
15613  if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getSubExprs(), E->getNumSubExprs(), false,
15614  SubExprs, &ArgumentChanged))
15615  return ExprError();
15616 
15617  if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
15618  !ArgumentChanged)
15619  return E;
15620 
15621  return getDerived().RebuildAtomicExpr(E->getBuiltinLoc(), SubExprs,
15622  E->getOp(), E->getRParenLoc());
15623 }

15699 template <typename Derived>
15700 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildArrayType(
15701  QualType ElementType, ArraySizeModifier SizeMod, const llvm::APInt *Size,
15702  Expr *SizeExpr, unsigned IndexTypeQuals, SourceRange BracketsRange) {
15703  if (SizeExpr || !Size)
15704  return SemaRef.BuildArrayType(ElementType, SizeMod, SizeExpr,
15705  IndexTypeQuals, BracketsRange,
15706  getDerived().getBaseEntity());
15707 
15708  QualType Types[] = {
15709  SemaRef.Context.UnsignedCharTy, SemaRef.Context.UnsignedShortTy,
15710  SemaRef.Context.UnsignedIntTy, SemaRef.Context.UnsignedLongTy,
15711  SemaRef.Context.UnsignedLongLongTy, SemaRef.Context.UnsignedInt128Ty
15712  };
15713  QualType SizeType;
15714  for (const auto &T : Types)
15715  if (Size->getBitWidth() == SemaRef.Context.getIntWidth(T)) {
15716  SizeType = T;
15717  break;
15718  }
15719 
15720  // Note that we can return a VariableArrayType here in the case where
15721  // the element type was a dependent VariableArrayType.
15722  IntegerLiteral *ArraySize
15723  = IntegerLiteral::Create(SemaRef.Context, *Size, SizeType,
15724  /*FIXME*/BracketsRange.getBegin());
15725  return SemaRef.BuildArrayType(ElementType, SizeMod, ArraySize,
15726  IndexTypeQuals, BracketsRange,
15727  getDerived().getBaseEntity());
15728 }

15836 
15837 template<typename Derived>
15838 QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildUnresolvedUsingType(SourceLocation Loc,
15839  Decl *D) {
15840  assert(D && "no decl found");
15841  if (D->isInvalidDecl()) return QualType();
15842 
15843  // FIXME: Doesn't account for ObjCInterfaceDecl!
15844  if (auto *UPD = dyn_cast<UsingPackDecl>(D)) {
15845  // A valid resolved using typename pack expansion decl can have multiple
15846  // UsingDecls, but they must each have exactly one type, and it must be
15847  // the same type in every case. But we must have at least one expansion!
15848  if (UPD->expansions().empty()) {
15849  getSema().Diag(Loc, diag::err_using_pack_expansion_empty)
15850  << UPD->isCXXClassMember() << UPD;
15851  return QualType();
15852  }
15853 
15854  // We might still have some unresolved types. Try to pick a resolved type
15855  // if we can. The final instantiation will check that the remaining
15856  // unresolved types instantiate to the type we pick.
15857  QualType FallbackT;
15858  QualType T;
15859  for (auto *E : UPD->expansions()) {
15860  QualType ThisT = RebuildUnresolvedUsingType(Loc, E);
15861  if (ThisT.isNull())
15862  continue;
15863  else if (ThisT->getAs<UnresolvedUsingType>())
15864  FallbackT = ThisT;
15865  else if (T.isNull())
15866  T = ThisT;
15867  else
15868  assert(getSema().Context.hasSameType(ThisT, T) &&
15869  "mismatched resolved types in using pack expansion");
15870  }
15871  return T.isNull() ? FallbackT : T;
15872  } else if (auto *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D)) {
15873  assert(Using->hasTypename() &&
15874  "UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl transformed to non-typename using");
15875 
15876  // A valid resolved using typename decl points to exactly one type decl.
15877  assert(++Using->shadow_begin() == Using->shadow_end());
15878 
15879  UsingShadowDecl *Shadow = *Using->shadow_begin();
15880  if (SemaRef.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(Shadow->getTargetDecl(), Loc))
15881  return QualType();
15882  return SemaRef.Context.getUsingType(
15883  Shadow, SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(
15884  cast<TypeDecl>(Shadow->getTargetDecl())));
15885  } else {
15886  assert(isa<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D) &&
15887  "UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl transformed to non-using decl");
15888  return SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(
15889  cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D));
15890  }
15891 }

16011 
16012 template <typename Derived>
16013 ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(
16014  OverloadedOperatorKind Op, SourceLocation OpLoc, SourceLocation CalleeLoc,
16015  bool RequiresADL, const UnresolvedSetImpl &Functions, Expr *First,
16016  Expr *Second) {
16017  bool isPostIncDec = Second && (Op == OO_PlusPlus || Op == OO_MinusMinus);
16018 
16019  if (First->getObjectKind() == OK_ObjCProperty) {
16020  BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
16021  if (BinaryOperator::isAssignmentOp(Opc))
16022  return SemaRef.checkPseudoObjectAssignment(/*Scope=*/nullptr, OpLoc, Opc,
16023  First, Second);
16024  ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(First);
16025  if (Result.isInvalid())
16026  return ExprError();
16027  First = Result.get();
16028  }
16029 
16030  if (Second && Second->getObjectKind() == OK_ObjCProperty) {
16031  ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(Second);
16032  if (Result.isInvalid())
16033  return ExprError();
16034  Second = Result.get();
16035  }
16036 
16037  // Determine whether this should be a builtin operation.
16038  if (Op == OO_Subscript) {
16039  if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() &&
16040  !Second->getType()->isOverloadableType())
16041  return getSema().CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(First, CalleeLoc, Second,
16042  OpLoc);
16043  } else if (Op == OO_Arrow) {
16044  // It is possible that the type refers to a RecoveryExpr created earlier
16045  // in the tree transformation.
16046  if (First->getType()->isDependentType())
16047  return ExprError();
16048  // -> is never a builtin operation.
16049  return SemaRef.BuildOverloadedArrowExpr(nullptr, First, OpLoc);
16050  } else if (Second == nullptr || isPostIncDec) {
16051  if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() ||
16052  (Op == OO_Amp && getSema().isQualifiedMemberAccess(First))) {
16053  // The argument is not of overloadable type, or this is an expression
16054  // of the form &Class::member, so try to create a built-in unary
16055  // operation.
16056  UnaryOperatorKind Opc
16057  = UnaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op, isPostIncDec);
16058 
16059  return getSema().CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(OpLoc, Opc, First);
16060  }
16061  } else {
16062  if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() &&
16063  !Second->getType()->isOverloadableType()) {
16064  // Neither of the arguments is an overloadable type, so try to
16065  // create a built-in binary operation.
16066  BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
16067  ExprResult Result
16068  = SemaRef.CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, First, Second);
16069  if (Result.isInvalid())
16070  return ExprError();
16071 
16072  return Result;
16073  }
16074  }
16075 
16076  // Add any functions found via argument-dependent lookup.
16077  Expr *Args[2] = { First, Second };
16078  unsigned NumArgs = 1 + (Second != nullptr);
16079 
16080  // Create the overloaded operator invocation for unary operators.
16081  if (NumArgs == 1 || isPostIncDec) {
16082  UnaryOperatorKind Opc
16083  = UnaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op, isPostIncDec);
16084  return SemaRef.CreateOverloadedUnaryOp(OpLoc, Opc, Functions, First,
16085  RequiresADL);
16086  }
16087 
16088  // Create the overloaded operator invocation for binary operators.
16089  BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
16090  ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CreateOverloadedBinOp(
16091  OpLoc, Opc, Functions, Args[0], Args[1], RequiresADL);
16092  if (Result.isInvalid())
16093  return ExprError();
16094 
16095  return Result;
16096 }
16097 
16098 template<typename Derived>
16099 ExprResult
16100 TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(Expr *Base,
16101  SourceLocation OperatorLoc,
16102  bool isArrow,
16103  CXXScopeSpec &SS,
16104  TypeSourceInfo *ScopeType,
16105  SourceLocation CCLoc,
16106  SourceLocation TildeLoc,
16107  PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destroyed) {
16108  QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
16109  if (Base->isTypeDependent() || Destroyed.getIdentifier() ||
16110  (!isArrow && !BaseType->getAs<RecordType>()) ||
16111  (isArrow && BaseType->getAs<PointerType>() &&
16112  !BaseType->castAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()
16113  ->template getAs<RecordType>())){
16114  // This pseudo-destructor expression is still a pseudo-destructor.
16115  return SemaRef.BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(
16116  Base, OperatorLoc, isArrow ? tok::arrow : tok::period, SS, ScopeType,
16117  CCLoc, TildeLoc, Destroyed);
16118  }
16119 
16120  TypeSourceInfo *DestroyedType = Destroyed.getTypeSourceInfo();
16121  DeclarationName Name(SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(
16122  SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(DestroyedType->getType())));
16123  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(Name, Destroyed.getLocation());
16124  NameInfo.setNamedTypeInfo(DestroyedType);
16125 
16126  // The scope type is now known to be a valid nested name specifier
16127  // component. Tack it on to the end of the nested name specifier.
16128  if (ScopeType) {
16129  if (!ScopeType->getType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
16130  getSema().Diag(ScopeType->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
16131  diag::err_expected_class_or_namespace)
16132  << ScopeType->getType() << getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
16133  return ExprError();
16134  }
16135  SS.Extend(SemaRef.Context, SourceLocation(), ScopeType->getTypeLoc(),
16136  CCLoc);
16137  }
16138 
16139  SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc; // FIXME: retrieve it from caller.
16140  return getSema().BuildMemberReferenceExpr(Base, BaseType,
16141  OperatorLoc, isArrow,
16142  SS, TemplateKWLoc,
16143  /*FIXME: FirstQualifier*/ nullptr,
16144  NameInfo,
16145  /*TemplateArgs*/ nullptr,
16146  /*S*/nullptr);
16147 }
16148 
16149 template<typename Derived>
16150 StmtResult
16151 TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCapturedStmt(CapturedStmt *S) {
16152  SourceLocation Loc = S->getBeginLoc();
16153  CapturedDecl *CD = S->getCapturedDecl();
16154  unsigned NumParams = CD->getNumParams();
16155  unsigned ContextParamPos = CD->getContextParamPosition();
16156  SmallVector<Sema::CapturedParamNameType, 4> Params;
16157  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumParams; ++I) {
16158  if (I != ContextParamPos) {
16159  Params.push_back(
16160  std::make_pair(
16161  CD->getParam(I)->getName(),
16162  getDerived().TransformType(CD->getParam(I)->getType())));
16163  } else {
16164  Params.push_back(std::make_pair(StringRef(), QualType()));
16165  }
16166  }
16167  getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionStart(Loc, /*CurScope*/nullptr,
16168  S->getCapturedRegionKind(), Params);
16169  StmtResult Body;
16170  {
16171  Sema::CompoundScopeRAII CompoundScope(getSema());
16172  Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getCapturedStmt());
16173  }
16174 
16175  if (Body.isInvalid()) {
16176  getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionError();
16177  return StmtError();
16178  }
16179 
16180  return getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionEnd(Body.get());
16181 }
16182 
16183 } // end namespace clang
